79 #define COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM(node) \
80  (pt_is_expr_node (node) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C))
81 
82 #define NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM(node) \
83  (pt_is_dot_node (node) || pt_is_attr (node) || pt_is_correlated_subquery (node) \
84  || (pt_is_expr_node (node) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC)))
85 
86 #define COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM(node) \
87  ((pt_is_function (node) && node->info.function.function_type == PT_GROUPBY_NUM) \
88  || (pt_is_expr_node (node) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C)))
89 
90 #define NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM(node) \
91  (pt_is_dot_node (node) || pt_is_attr (node) || pt_is_query (node) \
92  || (pt_is_expr_node (node) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC)))

197 /*
198  * pt_make_integer_value () -
199  * return: return a PT_NODE for the integer value
200  * parser(in): parser context
201  * value_int(in): integer value to make up a PT_NODE
202  */
203 PT_NODE *
204 pt_make_integer_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const int value_int)
205 {
206  PT_NODE *node;
207 
208  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
209  if (node)
210  {
211  node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
212  node->info.value.data_value.i = value_int;
213  }
214  return node;
215 }
216 
217 /*
218  * pt_make_string_value () -
219  * return: return a PT_NODE for the string value
220  * parser(in): parser context
221  * value_string(in): string value to make up a PT_NODE
222  */
223 
224 PT_NODE *
225 pt_make_string_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *value_string)
226 {
227  PT_NODE *node;
228 
229  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
230  if (node)
231  {
232  if (value_string == NULL)
233  {
234  node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
235  }
236  else
237  {
238  node->info.value.data_value.str = pt_append_bytes (parser, NULL, value_string, strlen (value_string));
239  node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_CHAR;
240  node->info.value.string_type = ' ';
241  PT_NODE_PRINT_VALUE_TO_TEXT (parser, node);
242  }
243  }
244  return node;
245 }

247 /*
248  * pt_and () - Create a PT_AND node with arguments of the nodes passed in
249  * return:
250  * parser(in):
251  * arg1(in):
252  * arg2(in):
253  */
254 PT_NODE *
255 pt_and (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * arg1, const PT_NODE * arg2)
256 {
257  PT_NODE *node;
258 
259  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
260  if (node)
261  {
262  parser_init_node (node);
263  node->info.expr.op = PT_AND;
264  node->info.expr.arg1 = (PT_NODE *) arg1;
265  node->info.expr.arg2 = (PT_NODE *) arg2;
266  }
267 
268  return node;
269 }
270 
271 /*
272  * pt_union () - Create a PT_UNION node with arguments of the nodes passed in
273  * return:
274  * parser(in):
275  * arg1(in/out):
276  * arg2(in/out):
277  */
278 PT_NODE *
279 pt_union (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * arg1, PT_NODE * arg2)
280 {
281  PT_NODE *node;
282  int arg1_corr = 0, arg2_corr = 0, corr;
283 
284  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_UNION);
285 
286  if (node)
287  {
288  parser_init_node (node);
289  /* set query id # */
290  node->info.query.id = (UINTPTR) node;
291 
292  node->info.query.q.union_.arg1 = arg1;
293  node->info.query.q.union_.arg2 = arg2;
294 
295  if (arg1)
296  {
297  arg1->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_UNION_SUBQUERY;
298  arg1_corr = arg1->info.query.correlation_level;
299  }
300  if (arg2)
301  {
302  arg2->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_UNION_SUBQUERY;
303  arg2_corr = arg2->info.query.correlation_level;
304  }
305  if (arg1_corr)
306  {
307  corr = arg1_corr;
308  if (arg2_corr && arg2_corr < corr)
309  {
310  corr = arg2_corr;
311  }
312  }
313  else
314  {
315  corr = arg2_corr;
316  }
317 
318  if (corr)
319  {
320  corr--;
321  }
322 
323  node->info.query.correlation_level = corr;
324  }
325 
326  return node;
327 }

330  * pt_name () - Create a PT_NAME node using the name string passed in

345  }
346 
347  return node;
348 }

496 /*
497  * pt_insert_value () - Creates an insert value setting node argument as
498  * original node.
499  *
500  * return : PT_INSERT_VALUE node.
501  * parser (in) : Parser context.
502  * node (in) : Original node.
503  */
504 PT_NODE *
505 pt_insert_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
506 {
507  PT_NODE *insert_val = parser_new_node (parser, PT_INSERT_VALUE);
508  if (insert_val != NULL)
509  {
510  parser_init_node (insert_val);
511  insert_val->info.insert_value.original_node = node;
512  }
513  return insert_val;
514 }

516 /*
517  * pt_datatypes_match () -
518  * return: 1 if the two data types are not virtual objects or the same
519  * class of virtual object. 0 otherwise.
520  * a(in):
521  * b(in): data types to compare
522  */
523 
524 static bool
525 pt_datatypes_match (const PT_NODE * a, const PT_NODE * b)
526 {
527  if (!a && !b)
528  {
529  return true; /* both non objects, ok */
530  }
531  if (!a || !b)
532  {
533  return true; /* typed and untyped node, ignore difference */
534  }
535  if (a->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT && b->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
536  {
537  return true; /* both non objects again, ok */
538  }
539 
540  if (a->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT || b->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
541  {
542  return false;
543  }
544  if (a->info.data_type.virt_object != b->info.data_type.virt_object)
545  {
546  return false;
547  }
548 
549  /* both the same flavor virtual objects */
550  return true;
551 }
552 
553 /*
554  * pt_name_equal () - Tests name nodes for equality
555  * return: true on equal
556  * parser(in):
557  * name1(in):
558  * name2(in):
559  *
560  * Note :
561  * Assumes semantic processing has resolved name information
562  */
563 bool
564 pt_name_equal (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * name1, const PT_NODE * name2)
565 {
566  if (!name1 || !name2)
567  {
568  return false;
569  }
570 
571  CAST_POINTER_TO_NODE (name1);
572  CAST_POINTER_TO_NODE (name2);
573 
574  if (name1->node_type != PT_NAME)
575  {
576  return false;
577  }
578 
579  if (name2->node_type != PT_NAME)
580  {
581  return false;
582  }
583 
584  /* identity */
585  if (name1 == name2)
586  {
587  return true;
588  }
589 
590  /* are the id's equal? */
591  if (name1->info.name.spec_id != name2->info.name.spec_id)
592  {
593  return false;
594  }
595 
596  /* raw names the same? (NULL not allowed here) */
597  if (!name1->info.name.original)
598  {
599  return false;
600  }
601  if (!name2->info.name.original)
602  {
603  return false;
604  }
605 
606  if (name1->info.name.meta_class != name2->info.name.meta_class)
607  {
608  /* check for equivalence class PT_SHARED == PT_NORMAL */
609  if (name1->info.name.meta_class != PT_SHARED && name1->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
610  {
611  return false;
612  }
613  if (name2->info.name.meta_class != PT_SHARED && name2->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
614  {
615  return false;
616  }
617  }
618 
619  if (intl_identifier_casecmp (name1->info.name.original, name2->info.name.original) != 0)
620  {
621  return false;
622  }
623 
624 
625  if (!pt_datatypes_match (name1->data_type, name2->data_type))
626  {
627  return false;
628  }
629 
630  return true;
631 }
632 
633 /*
634  * pt_find_name () - Looks for a name on a list
635  * return:
636  * parser(in):
637  * name(in):
638  * list(in):
639  */
640 PT_NODE *
641 pt_find_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * name, const PT_NODE * list)
642 {
643  while (list)
644  {
645  if (pt_name_equal (parser, name, list))
646  {
647  return (PT_NODE *) list;
648  }
649  list = list->next;
650  }
651 
652  return NULL;
653 }
654 
655 /*
656  * pt_is_aggregate_function () -
657  * return: true in arg if node is a PT_FUNCTION
658  * node with a PT_MIN, PT_MAX, PT_SUM, PT_AVG, or PT_COUNT type
659  * parser(in):
660  * node(in):
661  */
662 bool
663 pt_is_aggregate_function (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * node)
664 {
665  FUNC_TYPE function_type;
666 
667  if (node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION)
668  {
669  function_type = node->info.function.function_type;
670  if (!node->info.function.analytic.is_analytic
671  && (function_type == PT_MIN || function_type == PT_MAX || function_type == PT_SUM || function_type == PT_AVG
672  || function_type == PT_STDDEV || function_type == PT_STDDEV_POP || function_type == PT_STDDEV_SAMP
673  || function_type == PT_VARIANCE || function_type == PT_VAR_POP || function_type == PT_VAR_SAMP
674  || function_type == PT_GROUPBY_NUM || function_type == PT_COUNT || function_type == PT_COUNT_STAR
675  || function_type == PT_AGG_BIT_AND || function_type == PT_AGG_BIT_OR || function_type == PT_AGG_BIT_XOR
676  || function_type == PT_GROUP_CONCAT || function_type == PT_MEDIAN || function_type == PT_PERCENTILE_CONT
677  || function_type == PT_PERCENTILE_DISC || function_type == PT_CUME_DIST
678  || function_type == PT_PERCENT_RANK))
679  {
680  return true;
681  }
682  }
683 
684  return false;
685 }
686 
687 /*
688  * pt_is_analytic_function () -
689  * return: true in arg if node is an analytic function
690  * parser(in):
691  * node(in):
692  */
693 bool
694 pt_is_analytic_function (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * node)
695 {
696  if (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION && node->info.function.analytic.is_analytic)
697  {
698  return true;
699  }
700  else
701  {
702  return false;
703  }
704 }
705 
706 /*
707  * pt_is_expr_wrapped_function () -
708  * return: true if node is a PT_FUNCTION node with which may be evaluated
709  * like an expression
710  * parser(in): parser context
711  * node(in): PT_FUNTION node
712  */
713 bool
714 pt_is_expr_wrapped_function (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * node)
715 {
716  FUNC_TYPE function_type;
717 
718  if (node->node_type == PT_FUNCTION)
719  {
720  function_type = node->info.function.function_type;
721  if (function_type == F_INSERT_SUBSTRING || function_type == F_ELT || function_type == F_JSON_OBJECT
722  || function_type == F_JSON_ARRAY || function_type == F_JSON_INSERT || function_type == F_JSON_REMOVE
723  || function_type == F_JSON_MERGE || function_type == F_JSON_ARRAY_APPEND
724  || function_type == F_JSON_GET_ALL_PATHS || function_type == F_JSON_REPLACE || function_type == F_JSON_SET
725  || function_type == F_JSON_KEYS)
726  {
727  return true;
728  }
729  }
730 
731  return false;
732 }
733 
734 /*
735  * pt_find_spec_in_statement () - find the node spec in given statement
736  * return: the spec with same id as the name, or NULL
737  * parser(in):
738  * stmt(in):
739  * name(in):
740  */
741 PT_NODE *
742 pt_find_spec_in_statement (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * stmt, const PT_NODE * name)
743 {
744  PT_NODE *spec = NULL;
745 
746  switch (stmt->node_type)
747  {
748  case PT_SPEC:
749  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt, name);
750  break;
751 
752  case PT_DELETE:
753  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.delete_.spec, name);
754  if (spec == NULL)
755  {
756  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.delete_.class_specs, name);
757  }
758  break;
759 
760  case PT_UPDATE:
761  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.update.spec, name);
762  if (spec == NULL)
763  {
764  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.update.class_specs, name);
765  }
766  break;
767 
768  case PT_MERGE:
769  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.merge.into, name);
770  if (spec == NULL)
771  {
772  spec = pt_find_spec (parser, stmt->info.merge.using_clause, name);
773  }
774  break;
775 
776  default:
777  break;
778  }
779 
780  return (PT_NODE *) spec;
781 }
782 
783 /*
784  * pt_find_spec () -
785  * return: the spec in the from list with same id as the name, or NULL
786  * parser(in):
787  * from(in):
788  * name(in):
789  */
790 PT_NODE *
791 pt_find_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * from, const PT_NODE * name)
792 {
793  while (from && from->info.spec.id != name->info.name.spec_id)
794  {
795  /* check for path-entities */
796  if (from->info.spec.path_entities && pt_find_spec (parser, from->info.spec.path_entities, name))
797  {
798  break;
799  }
800  from = from->next;
801  }
802 
803  return (PT_NODE *) from;
804 }
805 
806 /*
807  * pt_find_aggregate_names - find names within select_stack
808  * returns: unmodified tree
809  * parser(in): parser context
810  * tree(in): tree to search into
811  * arg(in/out): a PT_AGG_NAME_INFO structure
812  * continue_walk(in/out): walk type
813  *
814  * NOTE: this function is called on an aggregate function or it's arguments
815  * and it returns the maximum level within the stack that owns PT_NAMEs within
816  * the called-on tree.
817  */
818 PT_NODE *
819 pt_find_aggregate_names (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
820 {
821  PT_AGG_NAME_INFO *info = (PT_AGG_NAME_INFO *) arg;
822  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *select_stack;
823  int level = 0;
824  bool max_level_has_gby = false;
825 
826  switch (tree->node_type)
827  {
828  case PT_SELECT:
829  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
830  break;
831 
832  case PT_DOT_:
833  node = tree->info.dot.arg2;
834  break;
835 
836  case PT_NAME:
837  node = tree;
838  break;
839 
840  default:
841  break;
842  }
843 
844  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_NAME)
845  {
846  /* nothing to do */
847  return tree;
848  }
849  else
850  {
851  info->name_count++;
852  }
853 
854  select_stack = info->select_stack;
855  while (select_stack != NULL)
856  {
857  PT_NODE *select = select_stack->info.pointer.node;
858 
859  if (select == NULL || select->node_type != PT_SELECT)
860  {
861  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "stack entry is not SELECT");
862  return tree;
863  }
864 
865  if (level > info->max_level && pt_find_spec (parser, select->info.query.q.select.from, node))
866  {
867  /* found! */
868  info->max_level = level;
869  max_level_has_gby = (select->info.query.q.select.group_by != NULL);
870  }
871 
872  /* next stack level */
873  select_stack = select_stack->next;
874  level++;
875  }
876 
877  /* Note: we need to deal with corelated queries when an aggregate function in the subquery contains arguments in
878  * outer-level queries. For example: 'select (select sum(t1.i) from t2) from t1;' It should be evaluted over the
879  * rows of the nearest outer level. */
880  if (!max_level_has_gby)
881  {
882  info->max_level = level - 1;
883  }
884 
885  return tree;
886 }
887 
888 /*
889  * pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre () - finds aggregate functions in a tree
890  * returns: unmodified tree
891  * parser(in): parser context
892  * tree(in): tree to search into
893  * arg(in/out): a PT_AGG_FIND_INFO structure
894  * continue_walk(in/out): walk type
895  *
896  * NOTE: this routine searches for aggregate functions that belong to the
897  * SELECT statement at the base of the stack
898  */
899 PT_NODE *
900 pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
901 {
902  PT_AGG_FIND_INFO *info = (PT_AGG_FIND_INFO *) arg;
903  PT_NODE *select_stack = info->select_stack;
904  PT_NODE *stack_top = select_stack;
905 
906  if (tree == NULL)
907  {
908  /* nothing to do */
909  return tree;
910  }
911 
912  while (stack_top != NULL && stack_top->next != NULL)
913  {
914  stack_top = stack_top->next;
915  }
916  if (stack_top && stack_top->info.pointer.node && stack_top->info.pointer.node->node_type == PT_SELECT
917  && stack_top->info.pointer.node->info.query.q.select.where == tree)
918  {
919  /* subqueries of WHERE clause will not be walked for this parent query; they must be treated separately as they
920  * own any aggregates referring upper-level names */
921  info->stop_on_subquery = true;
922  }
923 
924  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, tree))
925  {
926  if (tree->info.function.function_type == PT_COUNT_STAR || tree->info.function.function_type == PT_GROUPBY_NUM)
927  {
928  /* found count(*), groupby_num() */
929  if (select_stack == NULL)
930  {
931  /* no spec stack, this was not called on a select */
932  info->out_of_context_count++;
933  }
934  else if (select_stack->next == NULL)
935  {
936  /* first level on spec stack, this function belongs to the callee statement */
937  info->base_count++;
938 
939  if (tree->info.function.function_type == PT_COUNT_STAR)
940  {
941  /* can't use count star in loose scan */
942  info->disable_loose_scan = true;
943  }
944  }
945  }
946  else
947  {
948  PT_AGG_NAME_INFO name_info;
949  name_info.select_stack = info->select_stack;
950  name_info.max_level = -1;
951  name_info.name_count = 0;
952 
953  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->info.function.arg_list, pt_find_aggregate_names, &name_info,
954  pt_continue_walk, NULL);
955 
956  if (name_info.max_level == 0)
957  {
958  /* only names from base SELECT were found */
959  info->base_count++;
960 
961  if (tree->info.function.all_or_distinct == PT_ALL && tree->info.function.function_type != PT_MIN
962  && tree->info.function.function_type != PT_MAX)
963  {
964  /* only DISTINCT allowed for functions other than MIN/MAX */
965  info->disable_loose_scan = true;
966  }
967  }
968  else if (name_info.max_level < 0 && name_info.name_count > 0)
969  {
970  /* no names within stack limit were found */
971  info->out_of_context_count++;
972  }
973  else if (name_info.name_count == 0)
974  {
975  /* no names were found at all */
976  if (select_stack == NULL)
977  {
978  info->out_of_context_count++;
979  }
980  else if (select_stack->next == NULL)
981  {
982  info->base_count++;
983  }
984  }
985  }
986  }
987  else if (tree->node_type == PT_SELECT)
988  {
989  PT_NODE *spec;
990 
991  /* we must evaluate nexts before pushing SELECT on stack */
992  if (tree->next)
993  {
994  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree->next, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, info,
995  pt_find_aggregate_functions_post, info);
996  *continue_walk = PT_LEAF_WALK;
997  }
998 
999  /* if we encountered a subquery while walking where clause, stop this walk and make subquery owner of all
1000  * aggregate functions that reference upper-level names */
1001  if (info->stop_on_subquery)
1002  {
1003  PT_AGG_FIND_INFO sub_info;
1004  sub_info.base_count = 0;
1005  sub_info.out_of_context_count = 0;
1006  sub_info.select_stack = NULL;
1007  sub_info.stop_on_subquery = false;
1008 
1009  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, tree, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &sub_info,
1010  pt_find_aggregate_functions_post, &sub_info);
1011 
1012  if (sub_info.out_of_context_count > 0)
1013  {
1014  /* mark as agg select; base_count > 0 case will be handled later on */
1015  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (tree, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_AGG);
1016  }
1017 
1018  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1019  }
1020 
1021  /* don't get confused by uncorrelated, set-derived subqueries. */
1022  if (tree->info.query.correlation_level == 0 && (spec = tree->info.query.q.select.from)
1023  && spec->info.spec.derived_table && spec->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SET_EXPR)
1024  {
1025  /* no need to dive into the uncorrelated, set-derived subqueries */
1026  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1027  }
1028 
1029  /* stack push */
1030  info->select_stack = pt_pointer_stack_push (parser, info->select_stack, tree);
1031  }
1032 
1033  return tree;
1034 }
1035 
1036 /*
1037  * pt_find_aggregate_functions_post () - finds aggregate functions in a tree
1038  * returns: unmodified tree
1039  * parser(in): parser context
1040  * tree(in): tree to search into
1041  * arg(in/out): a PT_AGG_FIND_INFO structure
1042  * continue_walk(in/out): walk type
1043  */
1044 PT_NODE *
1045 pt_find_aggregate_functions_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1046 {
1047  PT_AGG_FIND_INFO *info = (PT_AGG_FIND_INFO *) arg;
1048 
1049  if (tree->node_type == PT_SELECT)
1050  {
1051  info->select_stack = pt_pointer_stack_pop (parser, info->select_stack, NULL);
1052  }
1053  else
1054  {
1055  PT_NODE *stack_top = info->select_stack;
1056 
1057  while (stack_top != NULL && stack_top->next != NULL)
1058  {
1059  stack_top = stack_top->next;
1060  }
1061  if (stack_top && stack_top->info.pointer.node && stack_top->info.pointer.node->node_type == PT_SELECT
1062  && stack_top->info.pointer.node->info.query.q.select.where == tree)
1063  {
1064  info->stop_on_subquery = false;
1065  }
1066  }
1067 
1068  /* nothing can stop us! */
1069  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1070 
1071  return tree;
1072 }
1073 
1074 /*
1075  * pt_is_analytic_node_post () -
1076  * return:
1077  * parser(in):
1078  * tree(in):
1079  * arg(in/out):
1080  * continue_walk(in/out):
1081  */
1082 PT_NODE *
1083 pt_is_analytic_node_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1084 {
1085  bool *has_analytic = (bool *) arg;
1086 
1087  if (*has_analytic)
1088  {
1089  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1090  }
1091  else
1092  {
1093  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1094  }
1095 
1096  return tree;
1097 }
1098 
1099 /*
1100  * pt_is_analytic_node () -
1101  * return:
1102  * parser(in):
1103  * tree(in):
1104  * arg(in/out): true if node is an analytic function node
1105  * continue_walk(in/out):
1106  */
1107 PT_NODE *
1108 pt_is_analytic_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1109 {
1110  bool *has_analytic = (bool *) arg;
1111 
1112  if (tree && tree->node_type == PT_FUNCTION && tree->info.function.analytic.is_analytic)
1113  {
1114  *has_analytic = true;
1115  }
1116 
1117  if (*has_analytic)
1118  {
1119  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1120  }
1121  else if (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (tree->node_type))
1122  {
1123  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
1124  }
1125 
1126  return tree;
1127 }
1128 
1129 /*
1130  * pt_has_non_idx_sarg_coll_pre () - pre function for determining if a tree has
1131  * contains a node with a collation that
1132  * renders it unusable for key range/filter
1133  * returns: input node
1134  * parser(in): parser to use
1135  * tree(in): tree node to analyze
1136  * arg(out): integer, will be set to "1" if node is found unfit
1137  * continue_walk(out): to be set to PT_STOP_WALK where necessary
1138  */
1139 PT_NODE *
1140 pt_has_non_idx_sarg_coll_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1141 {
1142  int *mark = (int *) arg;
1143 
1144  assert (tree != NULL);
1145  assert (arg != NULL);
1146  assert (continue_walk != NULL);
1147 
1148  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (tree->type_enum) && (tree->data_type != NULL))
1149  {
1150  int collation_id = tree->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
1151  LANG_COLLATION *lang_coll = lang_get_collation (collation_id);
1152 
1153  if (!lang_coll->options.allow_index_opt)
1154  {
1155  *mark = 1;
1156  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1157  }
1158  }
1159 
1160  return tree;
1161 }
1162 
1163 /*
1164  * pt_is_inst_or_orderby_num_node_post () -
1165  * return:
1166  * parser(in):
1167  * tree(in):
1168  * arg(in/out):
1169  * continue_walk(in/out):
1170  */
1171 PT_NODE *
1172 pt_is_inst_or_orderby_num_node_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1173 {
1174  bool *has_inst_orderby_num = (bool *) arg;
1175 
1176  if (*has_inst_orderby_num)
1177  {
1178  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1179  }
1180  else
1181  {
1182  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
1183  }
1184 
1185  return tree;
1186 }
1187 
1188 /*
1189  * pt_is_inst_or_orderby_num_node () -
1190  * return:
1191  * parser(in):
1192  * tree(in):
1193  * arg(in/out): true if node is an INST_NUM or ORDERBY_NUM expression node
1194  * continue_walk(in/out):
1195  */
1196 PT_NODE *
1197 pt_is_inst_or_orderby_num_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1198 {
1199  bool *has_inst_orderby_num = (bool *) arg;
1200 
1201  if (PT_IS_INSTNUM (tree) || PT_IS_ORDERBYNUM (tree))
1202  {
1203  *has_inst_orderby_num = true;
1204  }
1205 
1206  if (*has_inst_orderby_num)
1207  {
1208  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1209  }
1210  else if (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (tree->node_type))
1211  {
1212  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
1213  }
1214 
1215  return tree;
1216 }

1218 /*
1219  * pt_is_ddl_statement () - test PT_NODE statement types,
1220  * without exposing internals
1221  * return:
1222  * node(in):
1223  */
1224 int
1225 pt_is_ddl_statement (const PT_NODE * node)
1226 {
1227  if (node)
1228  {
1229  switch (node->node_type)
1230  {
1231  case PT_ALTER:
1232  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
1233  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
1234  case PT_ALTER_STORED_PROCEDURE:
1235  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
1236  case PT_ALTER_USER:
1237  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
1238  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
1239  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
1240  case PT_CREATE_STORED_PROCEDURE:
1241  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
1242  case PT_CREATE_USER:
1243  case PT_DROP:
1244  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
1245  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
1246  case PT_DROP_STORED_PROCEDURE:
1247  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
1248  case PT_DROP_USER:
1249  case PT_GRANT:
1250  case PT_RENAME:
1251  case PT_REVOKE:
1252  case PT_REMOVE_TRIGGER:
1253  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
1254  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
1255  return true;
1256  default:
1257  break;
1258  }
1259  }
1260  return false;
1261 }
1262 
1263 /*
1264  * pt_is_method_call () -
1265  * return:
1266  * node(in/out):
1267  */
1268 int
1269 pt_is_method_call (PT_NODE * node)
1270 {
1271  if (node == NULL)
1272  {
1273  return false;
1274  }
1275 
1276  node = pt_get_end_path_node (node);
1277  return (node->node_type == PT_METHOD_CALL);
1278 }
1279 
1280 /*
1281  * pt_is_attr () -
1282  * return:
1283  * node(in/out):
1284  */
1285 int
1286 pt_is_attr (PT_NODE * node)
1287 {
1288  if (node == NULL)
1289  {
1290  return false;
1291  }
1292 
1293  node = pt_get_end_path_node (node);
1294 
1295  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME)
1296  {
1297  if (node->info.name.meta_class == PT_NORMAL || node->info.name.meta_class == PT_SHARED
1298  || node->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR || node->info.name.meta_class == PT_VID_ATTR)
1299  {
1300  return true;
1301  }
1302  }
1303  return false;
1304 }
1305 
1306 /*
1307  * pt_is_function_index_expression () - check for function index expression
1308  * return: true if function index expression, false otherwise
1309  * node(in/out): PT_EXPR node
1310  */
1311 int
1312 pt_is_function_index_expression (PT_NODE * node)
1313 {
1314  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_EXPR)
1315  {
1316  return false;
1317  }
1318 
1319  if (!PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_FUNCTION_INDEX))
1320  {
1321  return false;
1322  }
1323 
1324  return true;
1325 }
1326 
1327 /*
1328  * pt_is_pseudocolumn_node() -
1329  * return:
1330  * tree(in/out):
1331  * arg(in/out):
1332  * continue_walk(in/out):
1333  */
1334 PT_NODE *
1335 pt_is_pseudocolumn_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1336 {
1337  int *found = (int *) arg;
1338 
1339  if (tree->node_type == PT_EXPR)
1340  {
1341  if (tree->info.expr.op == PT_LEVEL || tree->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISLEAF
1342  || tree->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISCYCLE)
1343  {
1344  *found = 1;
1345  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
1346  }
1347  }
1348 
1349  return tree;
1350 }
1351 
1352 /*
1353  * pt_instnum_compatibility () -
1354  * return:
1355  * expr(in/out):
1356  */
1357 int
1358 pt_instnum_compatibility (PT_NODE * expr)
1359 {
1360  PT_NODE *arg1 = NULL, *arg2 = NULL, *arg3 = NULL;
1361 
1362  if (expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
1363  {
1364  return true;
1365  }
1366 
1367  /* attr and subquery is not compatible with inst_num() */
1368 
1369  if (expr->info.expr.op != PT_IF)
1370  {
1371  arg1 = expr->info.expr.arg1;
1372  if (arg1)
1373  {
1374  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg1))
1375  {
1376  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C);
1377  }
1378  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg1))
1379  {
1380  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1381  }
1382  }
1383  }
1384 
1385  arg2 = expr->info.expr.arg2;
1386  if (arg2)
1387  {
1388  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg2))
1389  {
1390  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C);
1391  }
1392  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg2))
1393  {
1394  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1395  }
1396  }
1397 
1398  if (expr->info.expr.op != PT_CASE && expr->info.expr.op != PT_DECODE)
1399  {
1400  arg3 = expr->info.expr.arg3;
1401  if (arg3)
1402  {
1403  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg3))
1404  {
1405  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C);
1406  }
1407  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_INSTNUM (arg3))
1408  {
1409  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1410  }
1411  }
1412  }
1413 
1414  switch (expr->info.expr.op)
1415  {
1416  case PT_AND:
1417  /* AND hides inst_num() compatibility */
1418  return true;
1419  case PT_IS_NULL:
1420  case PT_IS_NOT_NULL:
1421  case PT_EXISTS:
1422  case PT_ASSIGN:
1423  case PT_IFNULL:
1424  /* those operator cannot have inst_num() */
1425  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1426  break;
1427  default:
1428  break;
1429  }
1430 
1431  /* detect semantic error in pt_semantic_check_local */
1432  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC))
1433  {
1434  if (expr->info.expr.op != PT_IF)
1435  {
1436  if (arg1 && pt_is_instnum (arg1))
1437  {
1438  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg1, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1439  }
1440  }
1441  if (arg2 && pt_is_instnum (arg2))
1442  {
1443  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg2, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1444  }
1445  if (expr->info.expr.op != PT_CASE && expr->info.expr.op != PT_DECODE)
1446  {
1447  if (arg3 && pt_is_instnum (arg3))
1448  {
1449  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (arg3, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC);
1450  }
1451  }
1452  }
1453 
1454  /* expression is not compatible with inst_num() */
1455  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC))
1456  {
1457  /* to prevent repeated error */
1458  PT_EXPR_INFO_CLEAR_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_C);
1459  return false;
1460  }
1461 
1462  return true;
1463 }
1464 
1465 /*
1466  * pt_groupbynum_compatibility () -
1467  * return:
1468  * expr(in):
1469  */
1470 int
1471 pt_groupbynum_compatibility (PT_NODE * expr)
1472 {
1473  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *arg3;
1474 
1475  if (expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
1476  {
1477  return true;
1478  }
1479 
1480  /* attr and subquery is not compatible with groupby_num() */
1481  arg1 = expr->info.expr.arg1;
1482  if (arg1)
1483  {
1484  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg1))
1485  {
1486  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C);
1487  }
1488  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg1))
1489  {
1490  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC);
1491  }
1492  }
1493 
1494  arg2 = expr->info.expr.arg2;
1495  if (arg2)
1496  {
1497  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg2))
1498  {
1499  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C);
1500  }
1501  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg2))
1502  {
1503  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC);
1504  }
1505  }
1506 
1507  arg3 = expr->info.expr.arg3;
1508  if (arg3)
1509  {
1510  if (COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg3))
1511  {
1512  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C);
1513  }
1514  if (NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_GROUPBYNUM (arg3))
1515  {
1516  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC);
1517  }
1518  }
1519 
1520  switch (expr->info.expr.op)
1521  {
1522  case PT_AND:
1523  /* AND hides groupby_num() compatibility */
1524  return true;
1525  case PT_IS_NULL:
1526  case PT_IS_NOT_NULL:
1527  case PT_EXISTS:
1528  case PT_ASSIGN:
1529  /* those operator cannot have groupby_num() */
1530  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC);
1531  break;
1532  default:
1533  break;
1534  }
1535 
1536  /* expression is not compatible with groupby_num() */
1537  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C)
1538  && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_NC))
1539  {
1540  /* to prevent repeated error */
1541  PT_EXPR_INFO_CLEAR_FLAG (expr, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_C);
1542  return false;
1543  }
1544 
1545  return true;
1546 }
1547

1555  */

1586  {

1588  }

1710 PT_NODE *

1712 {

1730 /*
1731  * pt_expr_disallow_op_pre () - looks if the expression op is in the list
1732  * given as argument and throws an error if
1733  * found
1734  *
1735  * return: node
1736  * parser(in):
1737  * node(in):
1738  * arg(in): integer list with forbidden operators. arg[0] keeps the number of
1739  * operators
1740  * continue_wals (in/out):
1741  */
1742 PT_NODE *
1743 pt_expr_disallow_op_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
1744 {
1745  int *op_list = (int *) arg;
1746  int i;
1747 
1748  if (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (node))
1749  {
1750  return node;
1751  }
1752 
1753  if (*continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK)
1754  {
1755  return node;
1756  }
1757 
1758  assert (op_list != NULL);
1759 
1760  for (i = 1; i <= op_list[0]; i++)
1761  {
1762  if (op_list[i] == node->info.expr.op)
1763  {
1764  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_ALLOWED_HERE,
1765  pt_show_binopcode (node->info.expr.op));
1766  }
1767  }
1768  return node;
1769 }
1770 
1771 /*
1772  * pt_check_level_expr () - check if expression can be reduced to "LEVEL <= x
1773  * AND ..." or to "LEVEL >= x AND ...".
1774  *
1775  * parser(in): PARSER_CONTEXT
1776  * expr(in): expression PT_NODE
1777  * has_greater(out): can be reduced to LEVEL >= x
1778  * has_lesser(out): can be reduced to LEVEL <= x
1779  *
1780  * NOTE: this was originally designed to check connect by clause in order to
1781  * determine if cycles can be allowed or if we risk to generate infinite
1782  * loops
1783  */
1784 void
1785 pt_check_level_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * expr, bool * has_greater, bool * has_lesser)
1786 {
1787  bool has_greater_1;
1788  bool has_lesser_1;
1789  bool has_greater_2;
1790  bool has_lesser_2;
1791  int op;
1792  PT_NODE *arg1;
1793  PT_NODE *arg2;
1794 
1795  *has_greater = 0;
1796  *has_lesser = 0;
1797 
1798  if (!expr)
1799  {
1800  return;
1801  }
1802  if (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (expr))
1803  {
1804  return;
1805  }
1806 
1807  op = expr->info.expr.op;
1808  arg1 = expr->info.expr.arg1;
1809  arg2 = expr->info.expr.arg2;
1810  switch (expr->info.expr.op)
1811  {
1812  case PT_NOT:
1813  /* NOT greater => lesser */
1814  /* NOT lesser => greater */
1815  pt_check_level_expr (parser, arg1, &has_greater_1, &has_lesser_1);
1816  *has_greater = has_lesser_1;
1817  *has_lesser = has_greater_1;
1818  break;
1819  case PT_OR:
1820  /* the OR EXPR will have as result a lesser value or a greater value for LEVEL if both branches have lesser,
1821  * respective greater values for LEVEL */
1822  pt_check_level_expr (parser, arg1, &has_greater_1, &has_lesser_1);
1823  pt_check_level_expr (parser, arg2, &has_greater_2, &has_lesser_2);
1824  *has_greater = has_greater_1 && has_greater_2;
1825  *has_lesser = has_lesser_1 && has_lesser_2;
1826  break;
1827  case PT_AND:
1828  /* the AND EXPR will have as result a lesser value or a greater value for LEVEL if any branch has a lesser,
1829  * respective a greater value for LEVEL */
1830  pt_check_level_expr (parser, arg1, &has_greater_1, &has_lesser_1);
1831  pt_check_level_expr (parser, arg2, &has_greater_2, &has_lesser_2);
1832  *has_greater = has_greater_1 || has_greater_2;
1833  *has_lesser = has_lesser_1 || has_lesser_2;
1834  break;
1835  case PT_EQ:
1836  case PT_LT:
1837  case PT_GT:
1838  case PT_LE:
1839  case PT_GE:
1840  {
1841  bool lhs_level = arg1->info.expr.op == PT_LEVEL;
1842  bool rhs_level = arg2->info.expr.op == PT_LEVEL;
1843  if ((lhs_level && rhs_level) || (!lhs_level && !rhs_level))
1844  {
1845  /* leave both has_greater and has_lesser as false */
1846  return;
1847  }
1848  if (op == PT_EQ)
1849  {
1850  *has_lesser = true;
1851  *has_greater = true;
1852  }
1853  else if (op == PT_GE || op == PT_GT)
1854  {
1855  if (lhs_level)
1856  {
1857  *has_greater = true;
1858  }
1859  else
1860  {
1861  *has_lesser = true;
1862  }
1863  }
1864  else if (op == PT_LE || op == PT_LT)
1865  {
1866  if (lhs_level)
1867  {
1868  *has_lesser = true;
1869  }
1870  else
1871  {
1872  *has_greater = true;
1873  }
1874  }
1875  }
1876  break;
1877  case PT_BETWEEN:
1878  case PT_RANGE:
1879  case PT_EQ_SOME:
1880  case PT_IS_IN:
1881  if (arg1->info.expr.op == PT_LEVEL)
1882  {
1883  *has_lesser = true;
1884  *has_greater = true;
1885  }
1886  break;
1887  default:
1888  /* leave both has_greater and has_lesser as false */
1889  break;
1890  }
1891 }
1892

2115 /*
2116  * pt_get_first_arg_ignore_prior () -
2117  * return: the first argument of an expression node; if the argument is
2118  * PRIOR (arg) then PRIOR's argument is returned instead
2119  * node(in):
2120  * Note: Also see the related PT_IS_EXPR_WITH_PRIOR_ARG macro.
2121  */
2122 PT_NODE *
2123 pt_get_first_arg_ignore_prior (PT_NODE * node)
2124 {
2125  PT_NODE *arg1 = NULL;
2126 
2127  assert (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (node));
2128 
2129  if (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (node))
2130  {
2131  return NULL;
2132  }
2133 
2134  arg1 = node->info.expr.arg1;
2135  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (arg1, PT_PRIOR))
2136  {
2137  arg1 = arg1->info.expr.arg1;
2138  }
2139  /* Although semantically valid, PRIOR(PRIOR(expr)) is not allowed at runtime so this combination is restricted during
2140  * parsing. See the parser rule for PRIOR for details. */
2141  assert (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (arg1, PT_PRIOR));
2142 
2143  return arg1;
2144 }

2359 /*
2360  * pt_must_be_filtering () - Finds expressions that are incompatible with
2361  * executing joins before a hierarchical query (connect by). If such
2362  * expressions are found the predicate must be executed after connect by
2363  * (it is a filtering predicate, not a join predicate).
2364  * In addition, it figures out if the predicate refers to only one spec_id
2365  * or more. This is needed to correctly classify the predicate as a join
2366  * predicate.
2367  */
2368 static PT_NODE *
2369 pt_must_be_filtering (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
2370 {
2371  MUST_BE_FILTERING_INFO *info = (MUST_BE_FILTERING_INFO *) arg;
2372 
2373  if (info->must_be_filtering)
2374  {
2375  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2376  return node;
2377  }
2378 
2379  if (PT_IS_QUERY (node))
2380  {
2381  info->must_be_filtering = true;
2382  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2383  return node;
2384  }
2385 
2386  if (PT_IS_NAME_NODE (node))
2387  {
2388  if (node->info.name.spec_id != 0 && node->info.name.correlation_level == 0)
2389  {
2390  if (info->first_spec_id == 0)
2391  {
2392  info->first_spec_id = node->info.name.spec_id;
2393  }
2394  else if (info->first_spec_id != node->info.name.spec_id)
2395  {
2396  info->has_second_spec_id = true;
2397  }
2398  }
2399  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
2400  return node;
2401  }
2402 
2403  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (node)
2404  && (PT_IS_SERIAL (node->info.expr.op) || PT_IS_NUMBERING_AFTER_EXECUTION (node->info.expr.op)
2405  || PT_REQUIRES_HIERARCHICAL_QUERY (node->info.expr.op)))
2406  {
2407  info->must_be_filtering = true;
2408  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2409  return node;
2410  }
2411 
2412  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
2413 
2414  return node;
2415 }
2416 
2417 /*
2418  * pt_is_filtering_predicate ()
2419  * return: Whether the given predicate is to be executed as filtering after
2420  * the hierarchical query or as a join predicate before the
2421  * hierarchical query.
2422  */
2423 static bool
2424 pt_is_filtering_predicate (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * predicate)
2425 {
2426  MUST_BE_FILTERING_INFO info;
2427 
2428  info.must_be_filtering = false;
2429  info.first_spec_id = 0;
2430  info.has_second_spec_id = false;
2431 
2432  parser_walk_tree (parser, predicate, pt_must_be_filtering, &info, NULL, NULL);
2433 
2434  if (!info.has_second_spec_id)
2435  {
2436  /* It's not a join predicate as it has references to one spec only. */
2437  return true;
2438  }
2439  else
2440  {
2441  /* It references more than one spec (like a join predicate), but we consider it to be a filtering predicate if it
2442  * contains certain expressions. */
2443  return info.must_be_filtering;
2444  }
2445 }
2446 
2447 /*
2448  * pt_is_filtering_skip_and_or () Checks for the existence of at least a
2449  * filtering predicate in a tree of predicates.
2450  */
2451 static PT_NODE *
2452 pt_is_filtering_skip_and_or (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
2453 {
2454  bool *already_found_filtering = (bool *) arg;
2455 
2456  if (*already_found_filtering)
2457  {
2458  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2459  return node;
2460  }
2461  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (node, PT_AND) || PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (node, PT_OR))
2462  {
2463  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
2464  return node;
2465  }
2466 
2467  if (pt_is_filtering_predicate (parser, node))
2468  {
2469  *already_found_filtering = true;
2470  }
2471 
2472  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
2473 
2474  return node;
2475 }
2476 
2477 /*
2478  * pt_is_filtering_expression ()
2479  * return: Whether the given expression is to be executed as filtering after
2480  * the hierarchical query or as a join expression before the
2481  * hierarchical query.
2482  * Unfortunately this expression can contain PT_AND and PT_OR because
2483  * CNF is not performed in some cases; see TRANSFORM_CNF_OR_COMPACT.
2484  * Because of this we must dig inside the tree to find the predicates.
2485  */
2486 static bool
2487 pt_is_filtering_expression (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * expression)
2488 {
2489  PT_NODE *or_next_save;
2490  bool result = false;
2491 
2492  assert (expression->next == NULL);
2493  or_next_save = expression->or_next;
2494  expression->or_next = NULL;
2495 
2496  parser_walk_tree (parser, expression, pt_is_filtering_skip_and_or, &result, NULL, NULL);
2497 
2498  expression->or_next = or_next_save;
2499  return result;
2500 }
2501 
2502 /*
2503  * pt_is_filtering_expression ()
2504  * return: Splits the given predicate list into two: a part to be executed
2505  * before the hierarchical query as it defines the join conditions and
2506  * a second part to be executed as filtering after the connect by
2507  * execution.
2508  */
2509 void
2510 pt_split_join_preds (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * predicates, PT_NODE ** join_part, PT_NODE ** after_cb_filter)
2511 {
2512  PT_NODE *current_conj, *current_pred;
2513  PT_NODE *next_conj = NULL;
2514 
2515  for (current_conj = predicates; current_conj != NULL; current_conj = next_conj)
2516  {
2517  bool has_filter_pred = false;
2518 
2519  assert (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (current_conj));
2520  /* It is either fully CNF or not at all. */
2521  assert (!(current_conj->next != NULL
2522  && (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (current_conj, PT_AND)
2523  || PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (current_conj, PT_OR))));
2524  next_conj = current_conj->next;
2525  current_conj->next = NULL;
2526 
2527  for (current_pred = current_conj; current_pred != NULL; current_pred = current_pred->or_next)
2528  {
2529  assert (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (current_pred));
2530  /* It is either fully CNF or not at all. */
2531  assert (!(current_pred->or_next != NULL
2532  && (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (current_pred, PT_AND)
2533  || PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR (current_pred, PT_OR))));
2534  if (pt_is_filtering_expression (parser, current_pred))
2535  {
2536  has_filter_pred = true;
2537  break;
2538  }
2539  }
2540 
2541  if (has_filter_pred)
2542  {
2543  *after_cb_filter = parser_append_node (current_conj, *after_cb_filter);
2544  }
2545  else
2546  {
2547  *join_part = parser_append_node (current_conj, *join_part);
2548  }
2549  }
2550 }
2551

2556  */

2558 pt_node_next (const PT_NODE * node)

2560  if (node)
2561  {
2562  return node->next;
2563  }
2564  return NULL;
2565 }

2613 /*
2614  * pt_record_warning () - creates a new PT_ZZ_ERROR_MSG node appends it
2615  * to parser->warning
2616  * return:
2617  * parser(in): pointer to parser structure
2618  * stmt_no(in): source statement where warning was detected
2619  * line_no(in): source line number where warning was detected
2620  * col_no(in): source column number where warning was detected
2621  * msg(in): a helpful explanation of the warning
2622  */
2623 void
2624 pt_record_warning (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int stmt_no, int line_no, int col_no, const char *msg)
2625 {
2626  PT_NODE *node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_ZZ_ERROR_MSG);
2627  node->info.error_msg.statement_number = stmt_no;
2628  node->line_number = line_no;
2629  node->column_number = col_no;
2630  node->info.error_msg.error_message = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, msg);
2631  parser->warnings = parser_append_node (node, parser->warnings);
2632 }

2649 /*
2650  * pt_reset_error () - resets the errors recorded in a parser to none
2651  * return:
2652  * parser(in/out):
2653  */
2654 void
2655 pt_reset_error (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
2656 {
2657  if (parser)
2658  {
2659  if (pt_has_error (parser))
2660  {
2661  parser_free_tree (parser, parser->error_msgs);
2662  parser->error_msgs = NULL;
2663  }
2664  parser->oid_included = PT_NO_OID_INCLUDED;
2665  }
2666  return;
2667 }
2668 
2669 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
2670 /*
2671  * pt_column_updatable () - takes a subquery expansion of a class, and tests
2672  * it for column aka object-master updatability
2673  * return: true on updatable
2674  * parser(in):
2675  * statement(in):
2676  */
2677 bool
2678 pt_column_updatable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
2679 {
2680  bool updatable = (statement != NULL);
2681 
2682  while (updatable && statement)
2683  {
2684  switch (statement->node_type)
2685  {
2686  case PT_SELECT:
2687  if (statement->info.query.q.select.group_by || statement->info.query.q.select.from->info.spec.derived_table
2688  || statement->info.query.all_distinct == PT_DISTINCT)
2689  {
2690  updatable = false;
2691  }
2692 
2693  if (updatable)
2694  {
2695  updatable = !pt_has_aggregate (parser, statement);
2696  }
2697  break;
2698 
2699  case PT_UNION:
2700  if (statement->info.query.all_distinct == PT_DISTINCT)
2701  {
2702  updatable = false;
2703  }
2704 
2705  if (updatable)
2706  {
2707  updatable = pt_column_updatable (parser, statement->info.query.q.union_.arg1);
2708  }
2709 
2710  if (updatable)
2711  {
2712  updatable = pt_column_updatable (parser, statement->info.query.q.union_.arg2);
2713  }
2714  break;
2715 
2716  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
2717  case PT_INTERSECTION:
2718  default:
2719  updatable = false;
2720  break;
2721  }
2722  statement = statement->next;
2723  }
2724 
2725  return updatable;
2726 }
2727 #endif
2728 
2729 /*
2730  * pt_has_error () - returns true if there are errors recorder for this parser
2731  * return:
2732  * parser(in):
2733  */
2734 int
2735 pt_has_error (const PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
2736 {

2773

2775  || from_spec->node_type != PT_SPEC || !(from_name = from_spec->info.spec.entity_name)

2788  * spec(in): a parsed SELECT query specification
2789  */
2790 const char *
2791 pt_get_select_from_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * spec)
2792 {

2800  {
2801  result = (char *) from_name->info.name.original;
2802  }
2803  else
2804  {
2805  result = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, from_name->info.name.resolved);
2806  result = pt_append_string (parser, result, ".");
2807  result = pt_append_string (parser, result, from_name->info.name.original);
2808  }
2809  }

2841 /*
2842  * pt_has_aggregate () -
2843  * return: true if statement has an aggregate node in its parse tree
2844  * parser(in):
2845  * node(in/out):
2846  *
2847  * Note :
2848  * for aggregate select statement, set agg flag for next re-check
2849  */
2850 bool
2851 pt_has_aggregate (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
2852 {
2853  PT_AGG_FIND_INFO info;
2854  PT_NODE *save_next;
2855  info.select_stack = NULL;
2856  info.base_count = 0;
2857  info.out_of_context_count = 0;
2858  info.stop_on_subquery = false;
2859  info.disable_loose_scan = false;
2860 
2861  if (!node)
2862  {
2863  return false;
2864  }
2865 
2866  if (node->node_type == PT_SELECT)
2867  {
2868  bool found = false;
2869 
2870  /* STEP 1: check agg flag */
2871  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_AGG))
2872  {
2873  /* we've been here before */
2874  return true;
2875  }
2876 
2877  /* STEP 2: check GROUP BY, HAVING */
2878  if (node->info.query.q.select.group_by || node->info.query.q.select.having)
2879  {
2880  found = true;
2881  /* fall trough, we need to check for loose scan */
2882  }
2883 
2884  /* STEP 3: check tree */
2885  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_UPD_DEL_QUERY)
2886  || PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_MERGE_QUERY))
2887  {
2888  /* UPDATE, DELETE and MERGE queries cannot own aggregates from subqueries, so this SELECT can't either */
2889  info.stop_on_subquery = true;
2890  }
2891  save_next = node->next;
2892  node->next = NULL;
2893  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &info, pt_find_aggregate_functions_post,
2894  &info);
2895  node->next = save_next;
2896 
2897  if (info.base_count > 0)
2898  {
2899  found = true;
2900  if (info.disable_loose_scan)
2901  {
2902  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_DISABLE_LOOSE_SCAN);
2903  }
2904  }
2905 
2906  if (found)
2907  {
2908  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_AGG);
2909  return true;
2910  }
2911  }
2912  else if (node->node_type == PT_MERGE)
2913  {
2914  /* for MERGE statement, free aggregates in search condition and in update assignments are not allowed; however,
2915  * those contained in subqueries are, even if they reference high level specs */
2916  info.stop_on_subquery = true;
2917  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.search_cond, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &info,
2918  pt_find_aggregate_functions_post, &info);
2919  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.update.assignment, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &info,
2920  pt_find_aggregate_functions_post, &info);
2921  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &info,
2922  pt_find_aggregate_functions_post, &info);
2923 
2924  if (info.out_of_context_count > 0)
2925  {
2926  return true;
2927  }
2928  }
2929  else
2930  {
2931  info.stop_on_subquery = true;
2932  save_next = node->next;
2933  node->next = NULL;
2934  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_find_aggregate_functions_pre, &info, pt_find_aggregate_functions_post,
2935  &info);
2936  node->next = save_next;
2937 
2938  if (info.out_of_context_count > 0)
2939  {
2940  return true;
2941  }
2942  }
2943 
2944  return false;
2945 }
2946 
2947 /*
2948  * pt_has_analytic () -
2949  * return: true if statement has an analytic function in its parse tree
2950  * parser(in):
2951  * node(in/out):
2952  *
2953  */
2954 bool
2955 pt_has_analytic (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
2956 {
2957  bool has_analytic = false;
2958  bool has_analytic_arg1 = false;
2959  bool has_analytic_arg2 = false;
2960 
2961  if (!node)
2962  {
2963  return false;
2964  }
2965 
2966  switch (node->node_type)
2967  {
2968  case PT_SELECT:
2969  if (PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_ANALYTIC))
2970  {
2971  has_analytic = true;
2972  }
2973  else
2974  {
2975  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list, pt_is_analytic_node, &has_analytic,
2976  pt_is_analytic_node_post, &has_analytic);
2977  if (has_analytic)
2978  {
2979  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_ANALYTIC);
2980  }
2981  }
2982  break;
2983 
2984  case PT_UNION:
2985  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
2986  case PT_INTERSECTION:
2987  has_analytic_arg1 = pt_has_analytic (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg1);
2988  has_analytic_arg2 = pt_has_analytic (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg2);
2989  if (has_analytic_arg1 || has_analytic_arg2)
2990  {
2991  has_analytic = true;
2992  }
2993  break;
2994 
2995  default:
2996  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_is_analytic_node, &has_analytic, pt_is_analytic_node_post,
2997  &has_analytic);
2998  break;
2999  }
3000 
3001  return has_analytic;
3002 }

3022 /*
3023  * pt_insert_host_var () - insert a host_var into a list based on
3024  * its ordinal position
3025  * return: a list of PT_HOST_VAR type nodes
3026  * parser(in): the parser context
3027  * h_var(in): a PT_HOST_VAR type node
3028  * list(in/out): a list of PT_HOST_VAR type nodes
3029  */
3030 static PT_NODE *
3031 pt_insert_host_var (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * h_var, PT_NODE * list)
3032 {
3033  PT_NODE *temp, *tail, *new_node;
3034 
3035  if (!list || list->info.host_var.index > h_var->info.host_var.index)
3036  {
3037  /* the new node goes before the rest of the list */
3038  new_node = parser_copy_tree (parser, h_var);
3039  if (new_node == NULL)
3040  {
3041  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
3042  return NULL;
3043  }
3044 
3045  new_node->next = list;
3046  list = new_node;
3047  }
3048  else
3049  {
3050  tail = temp = list;
3051  while (temp && temp->info.host_var.index <= h_var->info.host_var.index)
3052  {
3053  tail = temp;
3054  temp = temp->next;
3055  }
3056 
3057  if (tail->info.host_var.index < h_var->info.host_var.index)
3058  {
3059  new_node = parser_copy_tree (parser, h_var);
3060  if (new_node == NULL)
3061  {
3062  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
3063  return NULL;
3064  }
3065 
3066  tail->next = new_node;
3067  new_node->next = temp;
3068  }
3069  }
3070 
3071  return list;
3072 }
3073 
3074 /*
3075  * pt_collect_host_info () - collect host_var or cursor info from this node
3076  * return: node
3077  * parser(in): the parser context used in deriving this node
3078  * node(in): a node of the parse tree of an esql statement
3079  * h_var(in/out): a PT_HOST_VARS for depositing host_var or cursor info
3080  * continue_walk(in/out): flag that tells when to stop traversal
3081  *
3082  * Note :
3083  * if node is a host_var then
3084  * append a copy of node into h_var.inputs or h_var.outputs
3085  * or if node is a host descriptor then
3086  * save node into h_var.in_descr or h_var.out_descr
3087  * or if node is an UPDATE or DELETE current of cursor then
3088  * save cursor name into h_var.cursor
3089  */
3090 static PT_NODE *
3091 pt_collect_host_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *h_var, int *continue_walk)
3092 {
3093  PT_HOST_VARS *hvars = (PT_HOST_VARS *) h_var;
3094 
3095  switch (node->node_type)
3096  {
3097  case PT_HOST_VAR:
3098  switch (node->info.host_var.var_type)
3099  {
3100  case PT_HOST_IN: /* an input host variable */
3101  hvars->inputs = pt_insert_host_var (parser, node, hvars->inputs);
3102  break;
3103 
3104  case PT_HOST_OUT: /* an output host variable */
3105  hvars->outputs = pt_insert_host_var (parser, node, hvars->outputs);
3106  break;
3107 
3108  case PT_HOST_OUT_DESCR: /* an output host descriptor */
3109  hvars->out_descr = parser_copy_tree (parser, node);
3110  break;
3111 
3112  default:
3113  break;
3114  }
3115  break;
3116 
3117  case PT_DELETE:
3118  if (node->info.delete_.cursor_name)
3119  {
3120  hvars->cursor = parser_copy_tree (parser, node->info.delete_.cursor_name);
3121  }
3122  break;
3123 
3124  case PT_UPDATE:
3125  if (node->info.update.cursor_name)
3126  {
3127  hvars->cursor = parser_copy_tree (parser, node->info.update.cursor_name);
3128  }
3129  break;
3130 
3131  default:
3132  break;
3133  }
3134 
3135  return node;
3136 }

3141  * return: PT_HOST_VARS

3143  * stmt(in): parse tree of a an esql statement

3361 /*
3362  * pt_chop_trailing_dots () - return copy of string with
3363  * its trailing dots removed
3364  * return: copy of msg with any trailing dots removed if all OK,
3365  * NULL otherwise
3366  * parser(in): the parser context
3367  * msg(in) : a null-terminated character string
3368  */
3369 
3370 char *
3371 pt_chop_trailing_dots (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *msg)
3372 {
3373  char *c, *s = NULL;
3374  int l;
3375 
3376  assert (parser != NULL);
3377 
3378  if (!msg || (l = strlen (msg)) <= 0)
3379  {
3380  return (char *) "NULL message string";
3381  }
3382 
3383  c = pt_append_string (parser, s, msg);
3384  s = &c[l - 1];
3385  while (char_isspace (*s) || *s == '.')
3386  {
3387  s--;
3388  }
3389 
3390  *(s + 1) = '\0';
3391  return c;
3392 }

3394 /*
3395  * pt_get_proxy_spec_name () - return a proxy query_spec's "from" entity name
3396  * return: qspec's from entity name if all OK, NULL otherwise
3397  * qspec(in): a proxy's SELECT query specification
3398  */
3399 
3400 const char *
3401 pt_get_proxy_spec_name (const char *qspec)
3402 {
3403  PT_NODE **qtree;
3404  PARSER_CONTEXT *parser = NULL;
3405  const char *from_name = NULL, *result;
3406  size_t newlen;
3407 
3408  /* the parser and its strings go away upon return, but the caller probably wants the proxy_spec_name to remain, so */
3409  static char tblname[256], *name;
3410  static size_t namelen = 256;
3411 
3412  name = tblname;
3413 
3414  if (qspec && (parser = parser_create_parser ()) && (qtree = parser_parse_string (parser, qspec))
3415  && !pt_has_error (parser) && qtree[0])
3416  {
3417  from_name = pt_get_spec_name (parser, qtree[0]);
3418  }
3419 
3420  if (from_name == NULL)
3421  {
3422  result = NULL; /* no, it failed */
3423  }
3424  else
3425  {
3426  /* copy from_name into tblname but do not overrun it! */
3427  newlen = strlen (from_name) + 1;
3428  if (newlen + 1 > namelen)
3429  {
3430  /* get a bigger name buffer */
3431  if (name != tblname)
3432  {
3433  free_and_init (name);
3434  }
3435  name = (char *) malloc (newlen);
3436  namelen = newlen;
3437  }
3438 
3439 
3440  if (name)
3441  {
3442  strcpy (name, from_name);
3443  }
3444 
3445  result = name;
3446  }
3447 
3448  if (parser != NULL)
3449  {
3450  parser_free_parser (parser);
3451  }
3452 
3453  return result;
3454 }
3455 
3456 /*
3457  * pt_register_orphan () - Accepts PT_NODE and puts it on the parser's
3458  * orphan list for subsequent freeing
3459  * return: none
3460  * parser(in):
3461  * orphan(in):
3462  */
3463 void
3464 pt_register_orphan (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * orphan)
3465 {
3466  PT_NODE *dummy;
3467 
3468  if (orphan)
3469  {
3470  /* this node has already been freed. */
3471  if (orphan->node_type == PT_LAST_NODE_NUMBER)
3472  {
3473  assert_release (false);
3474  return;
3475  }
3476 
3477  dummy = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
3478  dummy->info.expr.op = PT_NOT; /* probably not necessary */
3479  dummy->info.expr.arg1 = (PT_NODE *) orphan;
3480  parser->orphans = parser_append_node (dummy, parser->orphans);
3481  }
3482 }
3483 
3484 /*
3485  * pt_register_orphan_db_value () - Accepts a db_value, wraps a PT_VALUE node
3486  * around it for convenience, and puts it on the parser's orphan
3487  * list for subsequent freeing
3488  * return: none
3489  * parser(in):
3490  * orphan(in):
3491  */
3492 void
3493 pt_register_orphan_db_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const DB_VALUE * orphan)
3494 {
3495  PT_NODE *dummy;
3496 
3497  if (orphan)
3498  {
3499  dummy = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
3500  dummy->info.value.db_value_is_in_workspace = 1;
3501  dummy->info.value.db_value = *orphan; /* structure copy */
3502  parser->orphans = parser_append_node (dummy, parser->orphans);
3503  }
3504 }
3505 
3506 /*
3507  * pt_free_orphans () - Frees all of the registered orphans
3508  * return:
3509  * parser(in):
3510  */
3511 void
3512 pt_free_orphans (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
3513 {
3514  PT_NODE *ptr, *next;
3515 
3516  ptr = parser->orphans;
3517  while (ptr)
3518  {
3519  next = ptr->next;
3520  ptr->next = NULL; /* cut off link */
3521  parser_free_tree (parser, ptr);
3522  ptr = next; /* next to the link */
3523  }
3524 
3525  parser->orphans = NULL;
3526 }
3527 
3528 /*
3529  * pt_sort_spec_cover () -
3530  * return: true or false
3531  * cur_list(in): current PT_SORT_SPEC list pointer
3532  * new_list(in): new PT_SORT_SPEC list pointer
3533  */
3534 
3535 bool
3536 pt_sort_spec_cover (PT_NODE * cur_list, PT_NODE * new_list)
3537 {
3538  PT_NODE *s1, *s2;
3539  QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_POSITION *p1, *p2;
3540 
3541  if (new_list == NULL)
3542  {
3543  return false;
3544  }
3545 
3546  for (s1 = cur_list, s2 = new_list; s1 && s2; s1 = s1->next, s2 = s2->next)
3547  {
3548  p1 = &(s1->info.sort_spec.pos_descr);
3549  p2 = &(s2->info.sort_spec.pos_descr);
3550 
3551  if (p1->pos_no <= 0)
3552  {
3553  s1 = NULL; /* mark as end-of-sort */
3554  }
3555 
3556  if (p2->pos_no <= 0)
3557  {
3558  s2 = NULL; /* mark as end-of-sort */
3559  }
3560 
3561  /* end-of-sort check */
3562  if (s1 == NULL || s2 == NULL)
3563  {
3564  break;
3565  }
3566 
3567  /* equality check */
3568  if (p1->pos_no != p2->pos_no || s1->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc != s2->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc
3569  || (s1->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last != s2->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last))
3570  {
3571  return false;
3572  }
3573  }
3574 
3575  return (s2 == NULL) ? true : false;
3576 }
3577

3655 /*
3656  * regu_strdup () - Duplication function for string.
3657  * return: char *
3658  * srptr(in) : pointer to the source string
3659  * alloc(in) : pointer to an allocation function
3660  */
3661 char *
3662 regu_strdup (const char *srptr, char *(*alloc) (int))
3663 {
3664  int len;
3665  char *dtptr;
3666 
3667  len = strlen (srptr) + 1;
3668  dtptr = alloc (len);
3669  if (dtptr == NULL)
3670  {
3671  return NULL;
3672  }
3673 
3674  /* because alloc may be bound to regu_bytes_alloc (which is a fixed-len buffer allocator), we must guard against
3675  * copying strings longer than DB_MAX_STRING_LENGTH. Otherwise, we get a corrupted heap seg fault. */
3676  len = (len > DB_MAX_STRING_LENGTH ? DB_MAX_STRING_LENGTH : len);
3677  dtptr[0] = '\0';
3678  strncat (dtptr, srptr, len);
3679  dtptr[len - 1] = '\0';
3680  return dtptr;
3681 }
3682 
3683 /*
3684  * regu_strcmp () - String comparison function.
3685  * return: int
3686  * name1(in) : pointer to the first string
3687  * name2(in) : pointer to the second string
3688  * function_strcmp(in): pointer to the function strcmp or ansisql_strcmp
3689  */
3690 int
3691 regu_strcmp (const char *name1, const char *name2, int (*function_strcmp) (const char *, const char *))
3692 {
3693  int i;
3694 
3695  if (name1 == NULL && name2 == NULL)
3696  {
3697  return 0;
3698  }
3699  else if (name1 == NULL)
3700  {
3701  return -2;
3702  }
3703  else if (name2 == NULL)
3704  {
3705  return 2;
3706  }
3707  else if ((i = function_strcmp (name1, name2)) == 0)
3708  {
3709  return 0;
3710  }
3711  else
3712  {
3713  return ((i < 0) ? -1 : 1);
3714  }
3715 }
3716 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

4644 static void
4645 regu_xasl_node_init (XASL_NODE * ptr, PROC_TYPE type)
4646 {
4647  memset ((char *) ptr, 0x00, sizeof (XASL_NODE));
4648 
4649  ptr->type = type;
4650  ptr->option = Q_ALL;
4651  ptr->iscan_oid_order = prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_BT_INDEX_SCAN_OID_ORDER);
4652  ptr->scan_op_type = S_SELECT;
4653 
4654  switch (type)
4655  {
4656  case UNION_PROC:
4657  case DIFFERENCE_PROC:
4658  case INTERSECTION_PROC:
4659  ptr->option = Q_DISTINCT;
4660  break;
4661 
4662  case OBJFETCH_PROC:
4663  break;
4664 
4665  case BUILDLIST_PROC:
4666  break;
4667 
4668  case BUILDVALUE_PROC:
4669  break;
4670 
4671  case MERGELIST_PROC:
4672  break;
4673 
4674  case SCAN_PROC:
4675  break;
4676 
4677  case UPDATE_PROC:
4678  break;
4679 
4680  case DELETE_PROC:
4681  break;
4682 
4683  case INSERT_PROC:
4684  break;
4685 
4686  case CONNECTBY_PROC:
4687  /* allocate CONNECT BY internal list files */
4688  ptr->proc.connect_by.input_list_id = regu_listid_alloc ();
4689  ptr->proc.connect_by.start_with_list_id = regu_listid_alloc ();
4690  break;
4691 
4692  case DO_PROC:
4693  break;
4694 
4695  case MERGE_PROC:
4696  ptr->proc.merge.update_xasl = NULL;
4697  ptr->proc.merge.insert_xasl = NULL;
4698  break;
4699 
4700  case CTE_PROC:
4701  ptr->proc.cte.recursive_part = NULL;
4702  ptr->proc.cte.non_recursive_part = NULL;
4703  break;
4704 
4705  default:
4706  /* BUILD_SCHEMA_PROC */
4707  break;
4708  }
4709 }

5192 /*
5193  * regu_free_domain () -
5194  * return:
5195  * ptr(in) : pointer to a schema manager domain
5196  *
5197  * Note: Free function for SM_DOMAIN using free_and_init.
5198  */
5199 void
5200 regu_free_domain (SM_DOMAIN * ptr)
5201 {
5202  if (ptr != NULL)
5203  {

5205  regu_free_domain (ptr->setdomain);
5206  free_and_init (ptr);
5207  }
5208 }
5209 
5210 
5211 /*
5212  * regu_cp_domain () -
5213  * return: SM_DOMAIN *
5214  * ptr(in) : pointer to a schema manager domain
5215  *
5216  * Note: Copy function for SM_DOMAIN.
5217  */
5218 SM_DOMAIN *
5219 regu_cp_domain (SM_DOMAIN * ptr)
5220 {
5221  SM_DOMAIN *new_ptr;
5222 
5223  if (ptr == NULL)
5224  {
5225  return NULL;
5226  }
5227 
5228  new_ptr = regu_domain_db_alloc ();
5229  if (new_ptr == NULL)
5230  {
5231  return NULL;
5232  }
5233  *new_ptr = *ptr;
5234 
5235  if (ptr->next != NULL)
5236  {
5237  new_ptr->next = regu_cp_domain (ptr->next);
5238  if (new_ptr->next == NULL)
5239  {
5240  free_and_init (new_ptr);
5241  return NULL;
5242  }
5243  }
5244 
5245  if (ptr->setdomain != NULL)
5246  {
5247  new_ptr->setdomain = regu_cp_domain (ptr->setdomain);
5248  if (new_ptr->setdomain == NULL)
5249  {
5250  regu_free_domain (new_ptr->next);
5251  new_ptr->next = NULL;
5252  free_and_init (new_ptr);
5253  return NULL;
5254  }
5255  }
5256 
5257  return new_ptr;
5258 }

5939 /* pt_enter_packing_buf() - mark the beginning of another level of packing
5940  * return: none
5941  */
5942 void
5943 pt_enter_packing_buf (void)
5944 {
5945  ++packing_level;
5946 }
5947 
5948 /* pt_alloc_packing_buf() - allocate space for packing
5949  * return: pointer to the allocated space if all OK, NULL otherwise
5950  * size(in): the amount of space to be allocated
5951  */
5952 char *
5953 pt_alloc_packing_buf (int size)
5954 {
5955  char *res;
5956  HL_HEAPID heap_id;
5957  int i;
5958 
5959  if (size <= 0)
5960  {
5961  return NULL;
5962  }
5963 
5964  if (packing_heap == NULL)
5965  {
5966  packing_heap_num_slot = PACKING_MMGR_BLOCK_SIZE;
5967  packing_heap = (HL_HEAPID *) calloc (packing_heap_num_slot, sizeof (HL_HEAPID));
5968  if (packing_heap == NULL)
5969  {
5970  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5971  PACKING_MMGR_BLOCK_SIZE * sizeof (HL_HEAPID));
5972  return NULL;
5973  }
5974  }
5975  else if (packing_heap_num_slot == packing_level - 1)
5976  {
5977  packing_heap_num_slot += PACKING_MMGR_BLOCK_SIZE;
5978 
5979  packing_heap = (HL_HEAPID *) realloc (packing_heap, packing_heap_num_slot * sizeof (HL_HEAPID));
5980  if (packing_heap == NULL)
5981  {
5982  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
5983  PACKING_MMGR_BLOCK_SIZE * sizeof (HL_HEAPID));
5984  return NULL;
5985  }
5986 
5987  for (i = 0; i < PACKING_MMGR_BLOCK_SIZE; i++)
5988  {
5989  packing_heap[packing_heap_num_slot - i - 1] = 0;
5990  }
5991  }
5992 
5993  heap_id = packing_heap[packing_level - 1];
5994  if (heap_id == 0)
5995  {
5996  heap_id = db_create_ostk_heap (PACKING_MMGR_CHUNK_SIZE);
5997  packing_heap[packing_level - 1] = heap_id;
5998  }
5999 
6000  if (heap_id == 0)
6001  {
6002  /* make sure an error is set, one way or another */
6003  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (size_t) PACKING_MMGR_CHUNK_SIZE);
6004  res = NULL;
6005  }
6006  else
6007  {
6008  res = (char *) db_ostk_alloc (heap_id, size);
6009  }
6010 
6011  if (res == NULL)
6012  {
6013  qp_Packing_er_code = -1;
6014  }
6015 
6016  return res;
6017 }
6018 
6019 /* pt_free_packing_buf() - free packing space
6020  * return: none
6021  * slot(in): index of the packing space
6022  */
6023 static void
6024 pt_free_packing_buf (int slot)
6025 {
6026  if (packing_heap && slot >= 0 && packing_heap[slot])
6027  {
6028  db_destroy_ostk_heap (packing_heap[slot]);
6029  packing_heap[slot] = 0;
6030  }
6031 }
6032 
6033 /* pt_exit_packing_buf() - mark the end of another level of packing
6034  * return: none
6035  */
6036 void
6037 pt_exit_packing_buf (void)
6038 {
6039  --packing_level;
6040  pt_free_packing_buf (packing_level);
6041 }
6042 
6043 /* pt_final_packing_buf() - free all resources for packing
6044  * return: none
6045  */
6046 void
6047 pt_final_packing_buf (void)
6048 {
6049  int i;
6050 
6051  for (i = 0; i < packing_level; i++)
6052  {
6053  pt_free_packing_buf (i);
6054  }
6055 
6056  free_and_init (packing_heap);
6057  packing_level = packing_heap_num_slot = 0;
6058 }
