6113 /*
6114  * pt_limit_to_numbering_expr () -rewrite limit expr to xxx_num() expr
6115  * return: expr node with numbering
6116  * limit(in): limit node
6117  * num_op(in):
6118  * is_gry_num(in):
6119  *
6120  */
6121 PT_NODE *
6122 pt_limit_to_numbering_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * limit, PT_OP_TYPE num_op, bool is_gby_num)
6123 {
6124  PT_NODE *lhs, *sum, *part1, *part2, *node;
6125  DB_VALUE sum_val;
6126 
6127  db_make_null (&sum_val);
6128 
6129  if (limit == NULL)
6130  {
6131  return NULL;
6132  }
6133 
6134  lhs = sum = part1 = part2 = node = NULL;
6135 
6136  if (is_gby_num == true)
6137  {
6138  lhs = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
6139  if (lhs != NULL)
6140  {
6141  lhs->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
6142  lhs->info.function.function_type = PT_GROUPBY_NUM;
6143  lhs->info.function.arg_list = NULL;
6144  lhs->info.function.all_or_distinct = PT_ALL;
6145  }
6146  }
6147  else
6148  {
6149  lhs = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6150  if (lhs != NULL)
6151  {
6152  lhs->info.expr.op = num_op;
6153  }
6154  }
6155 
6156  if (lhs == NULL)
6157  {
6158  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6159  return NULL;
6160  }
6161 
6162  if (limit->next == NULL)
6163  {
6164  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6165  if (node == NULL)
6166  {
6167  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6168  goto error_exit;
6169  }
6170 
6171  if (is_gby_num)
6172  {
6173  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_LIMIT);
6174  }
6175  node->info.expr.op = PT_LE;
6176  node->info.expr.arg1 = lhs;
6177  lhs = NULL;
6178 
6179  node->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, limit);
6180  if (node->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
6181  {
6182  goto error_exit;
6183  }
6184  }
6185  else
6186  {
6187  part1 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6188  if (part1 == NULL)
6189  {
6190  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6191  goto error_exit;
6192  }
6193 
6194  part1->info.expr.op = PT_GT;
6195  part1->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
6196  part1->info.expr.arg1 = lhs;
6197  lhs = NULL;
6198 
6199  part1->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, limit);
6200  if (part1->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
6201  {
6202  goto error_exit;
6203  }
6204 
6205  part2 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6206  if (part2 == NULL)
6207  {
6208  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6209  goto error_exit;
6210  }
6211 
6212  part2->info.expr.op = PT_LE;
6213  part2->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
6214  part2->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, part1->info.expr.arg1);
6215  if (part2->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
6216  {
6217  goto error_exit;
6218  }
6219 
6220  sum = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6221  if (sum == NULL)
6222  {
6223  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6224  goto error_exit;
6225  }
6226 
6227  sum->info.expr.op = PT_PLUS;
6228  sum->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NUMERIC;
6229  sum->data_type = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
6230  if (sum->data_type == NULL)
6231  {
6232  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6233  goto error_exit;
6234  }
6235 
6236  sum->data_type->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NUMERIC;
6237  sum->data_type->info.data_type.precision = 38;
6238  sum->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision = 0;
6239 
6240  sum->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, limit);
6241  sum->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, limit->next);
6242  if (sum->info.expr.arg1 == NULL || sum->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
6243  {
6244  goto error_exit;
6245  }
6246 
6247  if (limit->node_type == PT_VALUE && limit->next->node_type == PT_VALUE)
6248  {
6249  pt_evaluate_tree (parser, sum, &sum_val, 1);
6250  part2->info.expr.arg2 = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &sum_val);
6251  if (part2->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
6252  {
6253  goto error_exit;
6254  }
6255 
6256  parser_free_tree (parser, sum);
6257  }
6258  else
6259  {
6260  part2->info.expr.arg2 = sum;
6261  }
6262  sum = NULL;
6263 
6264  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
6265  if (node == NULL)
6266  {
6267  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6268  goto error_exit;
6269  }
6270 
6271  if (is_gby_num)
6272  {
6273  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (part1, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_LIMIT);
6274  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (part2, PT_EXPR_INFO_GROUPBYNUM_LIMIT);
6275  }
6276  node->info.expr.op = PT_AND;
6277  node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
6278  node->info.expr.arg1 = part1;
6279  node->info.expr.arg2 = part2;
6280  }
6281 
6282  return node;
6283 
6284 error_exit:
6285  if (lhs)
6286  {
6287  parser_free_tree (parser, lhs);
6288  }
6289  if (sum)
6290  {
6291  parser_free_tree (parser, sum);
6292  }
6293  if (part1)
6294  {
6295  parser_free_tree (parser, part1);
6296  }
6297  if (part2)
6298  {
6299  parser_free_tree (parser, part2);
6300  }
6301  if (node)
6302  {
6303  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
6304  }
6305 
6306  return NULL;
6307 }
6308 
6309 /*
6310  * pt_create_param_for_value () - Creates a PT_NODE to be used as a host
6311  * variable that replaces an existing value
6312  * return: the node or NULL on error
6313  * parser(in):
6314  * value(in): the value to be replaced
6315  * host_var_index(in): the index of the host variable that replaces the value
6316  */
6317 static PT_NODE *
6318 pt_create_param_for_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * value, int host_var_index)
6319 {
6320  PT_NODE *host_var = parser_new_node (parser, PT_HOST_VAR);
6321  if (host_var == NULL)
6322  {
6323  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
6324  return NULL;
6325  }
6326 
6327  host_var->type_enum = value->type_enum;
6328  host_var->expected_domain = value->expected_domain;
6329  host_var->data_type = parser_copy_tree (parser, value->data_type);
6330  host_var->info.host_var.var_type = PT_HOST_IN;
6331  host_var->info.host_var.str = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "?");
6332  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (value) && value->info.value.host_var_index != -1)
6333  {
6334  /* this value come from a host_var, we just need restore host_var. */
6335  host_var->info.host_var.index = value->info.value.host_var_index;
6336  assert (host_var->info.host_var.index < parser->host_var_count);
6337  }
6338  else
6339  {
6340  host_var->info.host_var.index = host_var_index;
6341  }
6342 
6343  return host_var;
6344 }
6345 
6346 /*
6347  * pt_rewrite_to_auto_param () - Rewrites a value to a host variable and fills
6348  * in the value of the new host variable in the
6349  * auto parameters values array
6350  * return: the new node or NULL on error
6351  * parser(in):
6352  * value(in): the value to be replaced by a host variable parameter
6353  */
6354 PT_NODE *
6355 pt_rewrite_to_auto_param (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * value)
6356 {
6357  PT_NODE *host_var = NULL;
6358  DB_VALUE *host_var_val = NULL;
6359  DB_VALUE *val = NULL;
6360  int count_to_realloc = 0;
6361  DB_VALUE *larger_host_variables = NULL;
6362 
6363  assert (pt_is_const_not_hostvar (value));
6364 
6365  /* The index number of auto-parameterized host variables starts after the last one of the user-specified host
6366  * variables. */
6367  host_var = pt_create_param_for_value (parser, value, parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count);
6368  if (host_var == NULL)
6369  {
6370  goto error_exit;
6371  }
6372 
6373  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (host_var, value);
6374 
6375  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (value) && value->info.value.host_var_index != -1)
6376  {
6377  /* this value come from a host_var, realloc is not needed. */
6378  assert (host_var->info.host_var.index < parser->host_var_count);
6379  }
6380  else
6381  {
6382  /* Expand parser->host_variables by realloc */
6383  count_to_realloc = parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count + 1;
6384  /* We actually allocate around twice more than needed so that we don't do useless copies too often. */
6385  count_to_realloc = (count_to_realloc / 2) * 4;
6386  if (count_to_realloc == 0)
6387  {
6388  count_to_realloc = 1;
6389  }
6390  larger_host_variables = (DB_VALUE *) realloc (parser->host_variables, count_to_realloc * sizeof (DB_VALUE));
6391  if (larger_host_variables == NULL)
6392  {
6393  PT_ERRORm (parser, value, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
6394  goto error_exit;
6395  }
6396  parser->host_variables = larger_host_variables;
6397  ++parser->auto_param_count;
6398  larger_host_variables = NULL;
6399 
6400  /* Copy the DB_VALUE to parser->host_variables */
6401  host_var_val = parser->host_variables + host_var->info.host_var.index;
6402  val = pt_value_to_db (parser, value);
6403  /* TODO Is it ok to ignore errors here? */
6404  if (val != NULL)
6405  {
6406  (void) pr_clone_value (val, host_var_val);
6407  }
6408  else
6409  {
6410  db_make_null (host_var_val);
6411  }
6412  }
6413  parser_free_tree (parser, value);
6414 
6415  return host_var;
6416 
6417 error_exit:
6418  if (host_var != NULL)
6419  {
6420  parser_free_tree (parser, host_var);
6421  host_var = NULL;
6422  }
6423  return NULL;
6424 }
6425 
6426 /*
6427  * pt_copy_statement_flags () - Copies the special flags relevant for statement
6428  * execution from one node to another. This is
6429  * useful for executing statements that are
6430  * generated by rewriting existing statements
6431  * (see CREATE ... AS SELECT for an example).
6432  * source(in): the statement to copy the flags from
6433  * destination(in/out): the statement to copy the flags to
6434  *
6435  * Note: Not all the PT_NODE flags are copied, only the ones needed for correct
6436  * execution of a statement are copied.
6437  */
6438 void
6439 pt_copy_statement_flags (PT_NODE * source, PT_NODE * destination)
6440 {
6441  destination->recompile = source->recompile;
6442  destination->cannot_prepare = source->cannot_prepare;
6443  destination->si_datetime = source->si_datetime;
6444  destination->si_tran_id = source->si_tran_id;
6445 }
6446 
6447 /*
6448  * pt_get_dup_key_oid_var_index () - Gets the index of the auto-parameterized
6449  * host variable in the INSERT ON DUPLICATE
6450  * KEY UPDATE statement
6451  * return: the index or -1 on error
6452  * parser(in):
6453  * update_statement(in):
6454  *
6455  * Note: The host variable will be replaced at runtime with the value of the
6456  * OID of an existing duplicate key that will be updated. See
6457  * pt_dup_key_update_stmt () to have a better understanding of what will
6458  * be executed.
6459  */
6460 int
6461 pt_get_dup_key_oid_var_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * update_statement)
6462 {
6463  PT_NODE *search_cond = NULL;
6464  PT_NODE *oid_node = NULL;
6465  int index = -1;
6466 
6467  if (update_statement == NULL || update_statement->node_type != PT_UPDATE)
6468  {
6469  return -1;
6470  }
6471  search_cond = update_statement->info.update.search_cond;
6472  if (search_cond == NULL || search_cond->node_type != PT_EXPR)
6473  {
6474  return -1;
6475  }
6476  oid_node = search_cond->info.expr.arg2;
6477  if (oid_node == NULL || oid_node->node_type != PT_HOST_VAR)
6478  {
6479  return -1;
6480  }
6481  index = oid_node->info.host_var.index;
6482  if (oid_node->info.host_var.var_type != PT_HOST_IN)
6483  {
6484  return -1;
6485  }
6486  if (index < 0 || index >= (parser->host_var_count + parser->auto_param_count))
6487  {
6488  return -1;
6489  }
6490  return index;
6491 }
6492 
6493 /*
6494  * pt_dup_key_update_stmt () - Builds a special UPDATE statement to be used
6495  * for INSERT ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE statement
6496  * processing
6497  * return: the UPDATE statement or NULL on error
6498  * parser(in):
6499  * spec(in):
6500  * assignment(in):
6501  *
6502  * Note: For the following INSERT statement:
6503  * INSERT INTO tbl VALUES (1) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE id = 4
6504  * the following UPDATE statement will be generated:
6505  * UPDATE tbl SET id = 4 WHERE tbl = OID_OF_DUPLICATE_KEY (tbl)
6506  * After type checking, constant folding and auto-parameterization, the
6507  * OID_OF_DUPLICATE_KEY (tbl) node will be replaced by a host variable.
6508  * At runtime, the variable will be assigned the OID of a duplicate key
6509  * and the UPDATE XASL will be executed.
6510  */
6511 PT_NODE *
6512 pt_dup_key_update_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * assignment)
6513 {
6514  PT_NODE *node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_UPDATE);
6515  PT_NODE *name_node = NULL;
6516  PT_NODE *name_arg_node = NULL;
6517  PT_NODE *func_node = NULL;
6518 
6519  if (node == NULL)
6520  {
6521  goto error_exit;
6522  }
6523 
6524  if (spec->node_type != PT_SPEC || spec->info.spec.entity_name == NULL)
6525  {
6526  goto error_exit;
6527  }
6528  name_node = parser_copy_tree (parser, spec->info.spec.entity_name);
6529  if (name_node == NULL || name_node->node_type != PT_NAME)
6530  {
6531  goto error_exit;
6532  }
6533  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (name_node, PT_NAME_INFO_GENERATED_OID);
6534 
6535  name_arg_node = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_node);
6536  if (name_arg_node == NULL)
6537  {
6538  goto error_exit;
6539  }
6540 
6541  node->info.update.spec = parser_copy_tree (parser, spec);
6542  if (node->info.update.spec == NULL)
6543  {
6544  goto error_exit;
6545  }
6546 
6547  /* This will be replaced by a OID PT_VALUE node in constant folding, see pt_fold_const_expr () */
6548  func_node = pt_expression_1 (parser, PT_OID_OF_DUPLICATE_KEY, name_arg_node);
6549  if (func_node == NULL)
6550  {
6551  goto error_exit;
6552  }
6553  name_arg_node = NULL;
6554 
6555  node->info.update.search_cond = pt_expression_2 (parser, PT_EQ, name_node, func_node);
6556  if (node->info.update.search_cond == NULL)
6557  {
6558  goto error_exit;
6559  }
6560 
6561  /* We need the OID PT_VALUE to become a host variable, see qo_optimize_queries () */
6562  node->info.update.search_cond->force_auto_parameterize = 1;
6563 
6564  /* We don't want constant folding on the WHERE clause because it might result in the host variable being removed from
6565  * the tree. */
6566  node->info.update.search_cond->do_not_fold = 1;
6567 
6568  func_node = NULL;
6569  name_node = NULL;
6570 
6571  node->info.update.assignment = assignment;
6572 
6573  return node;
6574 
6575 error_exit:
6576 
6577  if (func_node != NULL)
6578  {
6579  parser_free_tree (parser, func_node);
6580  func_node = NULL;
6581  }
6582  if (name_arg_node != NULL)
6583  {
6584  parser_free_tree (parser, name_arg_node);
6585  name_arg_node = NULL;
6586  }
6587  if (name_node != NULL)
6588  {
6589  parser_free_tree (parser, name_node);
6590  name_node = NULL;
6591  }
6592  if (node != NULL)
6593  {
6594  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
6595  node = NULL;
6596  }
6597  return NULL;
6598 }
6599 
6600 /*
6601  * pt_fixup_column_type() - Fixes the type of a SELECT column so that it can
6602  * be used for view creation and for CREATE AS SELECT
6603  * statements
6604  * col(in/out): the SELECT statement column
6605  *
6606  * Note: modifies TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE precision for char/bit constants
6607  * This code is mostly a hack needed because string literals do not have
6608  * the proper precision set. A better fix is to modify
6609  * pt_db_value_initialize () so that the precision information is set.
6610  */
6611 void
6612 pt_fixup_column_type (PT_NODE * col)
6613 {
6614  int fixed_precision = 0;
6615 
6616  if (col->node_type == PT_VALUE)
6617  {
6618  switch (col->type_enum)
6619  {
6620  /* for NCHAR(3) type column, we reserve only 3bytes. precision and length for NCHAR(n) type is n */
6621  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
6622  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
6623  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
6624  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
6625  if (col->info.value.data_value.str != NULL)
6626  {
6627  fixed_precision = col->info.value.data_value.str->length;
6628  if (fixed_precision == 0)
6629  {
6630  fixed_precision = 1;
6631  }
6632  }
6633  break;
6634 
6635  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
6636  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
6637  switch (col->info.value.string_type)
6638  {
6639  case 'B':
6640  if (col->info.value.data_value.str != NULL)
6641  {
6642  fixed_precision = col->info.value.data_value.str->length;
6643  if (fixed_precision == 0)
6644  {
6645  fixed_precision = 1;
6646  }
6647  }
6648  break;
6649 
6650  case 'X':
6651  if (col->info.value.data_value.str != NULL)
6652  {
6653  fixed_precision = col->info.value.data_value.str->length;
6654  if (fixed_precision == 0)
6655  {
6656  fixed_precision = 1;
6657  }
6658  }
6659  break;
6660 
6661  default:
6662  break;
6663  }
6664  break;
6665 
6666  default:
6667  break;
6668  }
6669  }
6670 
6671  /* Convert char(max) to varchar(max), nchar(max) to varnchar(max), bit(max) to varbit(max) */
6672  if ((col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_CHAR || col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NCHAR || col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_BIT)
6673  && col->data_type != NULL && (col->data_type->info.data_type.precision == TP_FLOATING_PRECISION_VALUE))
6674  {
6675  if (col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_CHAR)
6676  {
6677  col->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARCHAR;
6678  col->data_type->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARCHAR;
6679  }
6680  else if (col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NCHAR)
6681  {
6682  col->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR;
6683  col->data_type->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR;
6684  }
6685  else
6686  {
6687  col->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARBIT;
6688  col->data_type->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARBIT;
6689  }
6690 
6691  if (fixed_precision != 0)
6692  {
6693  col->data_type->info.data_type.precision = fixed_precision;
6694  }
6695  }
6696 }
6697 
6698 /*
6699  * pt_get_select_query_columns() - Retrieves the columns of a SELECT query
6700  * result
6701  * return: NO_ERROR on success, non-zero for ERROR
6702  * parser(in): Parser context
6703  * create_select(in): the select statement parse tree
6704  * query_columns(out): the columns of the select statement
6705  *
6706  * Note: The code is very similar to the one in db_compile_statement_local ()
6707  */
6708 int
6709 pt_get_select_query_columns (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * create_select, DB_QUERY_TYPE ** query_columns)
6710 {
6711  PT_NODE *temp_copy = NULL;
6712  DB_QUERY_TYPE *qtype = NULL;
6713  int error = NO_ERROR;
6714 
6715  assert (query_columns != NULL);
6716 
6717  if (pt_node_to_cmd_type (create_select) != CUBRID_STMT_SELECT)
6718  {
6719  ERROR1 (error, ER_UNEXPECTED, "Expecting a select statement.");
6720  goto error_exit;
6721  }
6722 
6723  temp_copy = parser_copy_tree (parser, create_select);
6724  if (temp_copy == NULL)
6725  {
6726  error = ER_FAILED;
6727  goto error_exit;
6728  }
6729 
6730  qtype = pt_get_titles (parser, create_select);
6731  if (qtype == NULL)
6732  {
6733  /* We ignore this for now and we try again later. */
6734  }
6735 
6736  /* Semantic check for the statement */
6737  temp_copy = pt_compile (parser, temp_copy);
6738  if (temp_copy == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
6739  {
6740 #if 0
6741  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6742 #endif
6743  error = er_errid ();
6744  pt_report_to_ersys_with_statement (parser, PT_SEMANTIC, temp_copy);
6745  if (error == NO_ERROR)
6746  {
6747  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6748  error = er_errid ();
6749  }
6750  goto error_exit;
6751  }
6752 
6753  if (qtype == NULL)
6754  {
6755  qtype = pt_get_titles (parser, temp_copy);
6756  }
6757 
6758  if (qtype == NULL)
6759  {
6760  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6761  error = er_errid ();
6762  goto error_exit;
6763  }
6764 
6765  qtype = pt_fillin_type_size (parser, temp_copy, qtype, DB_NO_OIDS, true, true);
6766  if (qtype == NULL)
6767  {
6768  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6769  error = er_errid ();
6770  goto error_exit;
6771  }
6772 
6773  /* qtype will be freed later */
6774  *query_columns = qtype;
6775 
6776  parser_free_tree (parser, temp_copy);
6777  temp_copy = NULL;
6778 
6779  return error;
6780 
6781 error_exit:
6782  if (qtype != NULL)
6783  {
6784  db_free_query_format (qtype);
6785  qtype = NULL;
6786  }
6787  if (temp_copy != NULL)
6788  {
6789  parser_free_tree (parser, temp_copy);
6790  temp_copy = NULL;
6791  }
6792  return error;
6793 }
6794 
6795 /*
6796  * pt_node_list_to_array() - returns an array of nodes(PT_NODE) from a
6797  * PT_NODE list. Used mainly to convert a list of
6798  * argument nodes to an array of argument nodes
6799  * return: NO_ERROR on success, ER_GENERIC_ERROR on failure
6800  * parser(in): Parser context
6801  * arg_list(in): List of nodes (arguments) chained on next
6802  * arg_array(out): array of nodes (arguments)
6803  * array_size(in): the (allocated) size of array
6804  * num_args(out): the number of nodes found in list
6805  *
6806  * Note: the arg_array must be allocated and sized to 'array_size'
6807  */
6808 int
6809 pt_node_list_to_array (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * arg_list, PT_NODE * arg_array[], const int array_size,
6810  int *num_args)
6811 {
6812  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
6813  int error = NO_ERROR, len = 0;
6814 
6815  assert (array_size > 0);
6816  assert (arg_array != NULL);
6817  assert (arg_list != NULL);
6818  assert (num_args != NULL);
6819 
6820  *num_args = 0;
6821 
6822  for (arg = arg_list; arg != NULL; arg = arg->next)
6823  {
6824  if (len >= array_size)
6825  {
6826  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
6827  }
6828  arg_array[len] = arg;
6829  *num_args = ++len;
6830  }
6831  return error;
6832 }
6833 
6834 /*
6835  * pt_make_dotted_identifier() - returns an identifier node (type PT_NAME) or
6836  * a PT_DOT node tree
6837  *
6838  * return: node with constructed identifier, NULL if construction fails
6839  * parser(in): Parser context
6840  * identifier_str(in): string containing full identifier name. Dots ('.')
6841  * are used to delimit class names and column
6842  * names; for this reason, column and class names should
6843  * not contain dots.
6844  */
6845 static PT_NODE *
6846 pt_make_dotted_identifier (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *identifier_str)
6847 {
6848  return pt_make_dotted_identifier_internal (parser, identifier_str, 0);
6849 }
6850 
6851 /*
6852  * pt_make_dotted_identifier_internal() - builds an identifier node
6853  * (type PT_NAME) or tree (type PT_DOT)
6854  *
6855  * return: node with constructed identifier, NULL if construction fails
6856  * parser(in): Parser context
6857  * identifier_str(in): string containing full identifier name (with dots);
6858  * length must be smaller than maximum allowed
6859  * identifier length
6860  * depth(in): depth of current constructed node relative to PT_DOT subtree
6861  *
6862  * Note : the depth argument is used to flag the PT_NAME node corresponding
6863  * to the first scoping name as 'meta_class = PT_NORMAL'.
6864  * This applies only to dotted identifier names.
6865  */
6866 static PT_NODE *
6867 pt_make_dotted_identifier_internal (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *identifier_str, int depth)
6868 {
6869  PT_NODE *identifier = NULL;
6870  char *p_dot = NULL;
6871 
6872  assert (depth >= 0);
6873  if (strlen (identifier_str) >= SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH)
6874  {
6875  assert (false);
6876  return NULL;
6877  }
6878 
6879  p_dot = (char *) strrchr (identifier_str, '.');
6880 
6881  if (p_dot != NULL)
6882  {
6883  char string_name1[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH] = { 0 };
6884  char string_name2[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH] = { 0 };
6885  PT_NODE *name1 = NULL;
6886  PT_NODE *name2 = NULL;
6887  int position = CAST_BUFLEN (p_dot - identifier_str);
6888  int remaining = strlen (identifier_str) - position - 1;
6889 
6890  assert ((remaining > 0) && (remaining < strlen (identifier_str) - 1));
6891  assert ((position > 0) && (position < strlen (identifier_str) - 1));
6892 
6893  strncpy (string_name1, identifier_str, position);
6894  string_name1[position] = '\0';
6895  strncpy (string_name2, p_dot + 1, remaining);
6896  string_name2[remaining] = '\0';
6897 
6898  /* create PT_DOT_ - must be left - balanced */
6899  name1 = pt_make_dotted_identifier_internal (parser, string_name1, depth + 1);
6900  name2 = pt_name (parser, string_name2);
6901  if (name1 == NULL || name2 == NULL)
6902  {
6903  return NULL;
6904  }
6905 
6906  identifier = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DOT_);
6907  if (identifier == NULL)
6908  {
6909  return NULL;
6910  }
6911 
6912  identifier->info.dot.arg1 = name1;
6913  identifier->info.dot.arg2 = name2;
6914  }
6915  else
6916  {
6917  identifier = pt_name (parser, identifier_str);
6918  if (identifier == NULL)
6919  {
6920  return NULL;
6921  }
6922 
6923  /* it is a dotted identifier, make the first name PT_NORMAL */
6924  if (depth != 0)
6925  {
6926  identifier->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
6927  }
6928  }
6929 
6930  assert (identifier != NULL);
6931 
6932  return identifier;
6933 }
6934 
6935 /*
6936  * pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list() - builds a corresponding node for a table
6937  * column and adds it to the end of the select
6938  * list of a SELECT node
6939  *
6940  * return: error code
6941  * parser(in): Parser context
6942  * select(in): SELECT node
6943  * identifier_str(in): string identifying the column (may contain dots)
6944  * col_alias(in): alias of the new select item
6945  */
6946 static int
6947 pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * select, const char *identifier_str,
6948  const char *col_alias)
6949 {
6950  PT_NODE *sel_item = NULL;
6951

6953  assert (identifier_str != NULL);
6954 
6955  sel_item = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, identifier_str);
6956  if (sel_item == NULL)
6957  {
6958  return ER_FAILED;
6959  }
6960  sel_item->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, col_alias);
6961 
6962  select->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (sel_item, select->info.query.q.select.list);
6963  return NO_ERROR;
6964 }

6996 /*
6997  * pt_add_table_name_to_from_list() - builds a corresponding node for a table
6998  * 'spec' and adds it to the end of the FROM list
6999  * of a SELECT node
7000  *
7001  * return: newly build PT_NODE, NULL if construction fails
7002  * parser(in): Parser context
7003  * select(in): SELECT node
7004  * table_name(in): table name (should not contain dots), may be NULL if spec
7005  * is a subquery (instead of a table)
7006  * table_alias(in): alias of the table
7007  * auth_bypass(in): bit mask of privileges flags that will bypass
7008  * authorizations
7009  */
7010 PT_NODE *
7011 pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * select, const char *table_name,
7012  const char *table_alias, const DB_AUTH auth_bypass)
7013 {
7014  PT_NODE *spec = NULL;
7015  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7016  PT_NODE *range_var = NULL;
7017 
7018  if (table_name != NULL)
7019  {
7020  from_item = pt_name (parser, table_name);
7021  if (from_item == NULL)
7022  {
7023  return NULL;
7024  }
7025  }
7026  if (table_alias != NULL)
7027  {
7028  range_var = pt_name (parser, table_alias);
7029  if (range_var == NULL)
7030  {
7031  return NULL;
7032  }
7033  }
7034 
7035  spec = pt_entity (parser, from_item, range_var, NULL);
7036  if (spec == NULL)
7037  {
7038  return NULL;
7039  }
7040 
7041  spec->info.spec.only_all = PT_ONLY;
7042  spec->info.spec.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
7043  select->info.query.q.select.from = parser_append_node (spec, select->info.query.q.select.from);
7044  spec->info.spec.auth_bypass_mask = auth_bypass;
7045 
7046  return spec;
7047 }
7048 
7049 /*
7050  * pt_make_pred_name_int_val() - builds a predicate node (PT_EXPR) using a
7051  * column identifier on LHS and a integer value on
7052  * RHS
7053  *
7054  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7055  * parser(in): Parser context
7056  * op_type(in): operator type; should be a binary operator that makes sense
7057  * for the passed arguments (such as PT_EQ, PT_GT, ...)
7058  * col_name(in): column name (may contain dots)
7059  * int_value(in): integer to assign to PT_VALUE RHS node
7060  */
7061 static PT_NODE *
7062 pt_make_pred_name_int_val (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_OP_TYPE op_type, const char *col_name, const int int_value)
7063 {
7064  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
7065  PT_NODE *pred_lhs = NULL;
7066  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
7067 
7068  /* create PT_VALUE for rhs */
7069  pred_rhs = pt_make_integer_value (parser, int_value);
7070  /* create PT_NAME for lhs */
7071  pred_lhs = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, col_name);
7072 
7073  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, op_type, pred_lhs, pred_rhs, NULL);
7074  return pred;
7075 }

7077 /*
7078  * pt_make_pred_name_string_val() - builds a predicate node (PT_EXPR) using an
7079  * identifier on LHS and a string value on
7080  * RHS
7081  *
7082  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7083  * parser(in): Parser context
7084  * op_type(in): operator type; should be a binary operator that makes sense
7085  * for the passed arguments (such as PT_EQ, PT_GT, ...)
7086  * identifier_str(in): column name (may contain dots)
7087  * str_value(in): string to assign to PT_VALUE RHS node
7088  */
7089 static PT_NODE *
7090 pt_make_pred_name_string_val (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_OP_TYPE op_type, const char *identifier_str,
7091  const char *str_value)
7092 {
7093  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
7094  PT_NODE *pred_lhs = NULL;
7095  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
7096 
7097  /* create PT_VALUE for rhs */
7098  pred_rhs = pt_make_string_value (parser, str_value);
7099  /* create PT_NAME for lhs */
7100  pred_lhs = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, identifier_str);
7101 
7102  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, op_type, pred_lhs, pred_rhs, NULL);
7103 
7104  return pred;
7105 }

7107 /*
7108  * pt_make_pred_with_identifiers() - builds a predicate node (PT_EXPR) using
7109  * an identifier on LHS and another identifier on
7110  * RHS
7111  *
7112  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7113  * parser(in): Parser context
7114  * op_type(in): operator type; should be a binary operator that makes sense
7115  * for the passed arguments (such as PT_EQ, PT_GT, ...)
7116  * lhs_identifier(in): LHS column name (may contain dots)
7117  * rhs_identifier(in): RHS column name (may contain dots)
7118  */
7119 static PT_NODE *
7120 pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_OP_TYPE op_type, const char *lhs_identifier,
7121  const char *rhs_identifier)
7122 {
7123  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
7124  PT_NODE *pred_lhs = NULL;
7125  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
7126 
7127  /* create PT_DOT_ for lhs */
7128  pred_lhs = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, lhs_identifier);
7129  /* create PT_DOT_ for rhs */
7130  pred_rhs = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, rhs_identifier);
7131 
7132  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, op_type, pred_lhs, pred_rhs, NULL);
7133 
7134  return pred;
7135 }

7137 /*
7138  * pt_make_if_with_expressions() - builds an IF (pred, expr_true, expr_false)
7139  * operator node (PT_EXPR) given two expression
7140  * nodes for true/false values
7141  *
7142  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7143  * parser(in): Parser context
7144  * pred(in): a node for expression used as predicate
7145  * expr1(in): expression node for true value of predicate
7146  * expr2(in): expression node for false value of predicate
7147  * alias(in): alias for this new node
7148  */
7149 static PT_NODE *
7150 pt_make_if_with_expressions (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * pred, PT_NODE * expr1, PT_NODE * expr2,
7151  const char *alias)
7152 {
7153  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
7154 
7155  if_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, pred, expr1, expr2);
7156 
7157  if (alias != NULL)
7158  {
7159  if_node->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, alias);
7160  }
7161  return if_node;
7162 }
7163 
7164 /*
7165  * pt_make_if_with_strings() - builds an IF (pred, expr_true, expr_false)
7166  * operator node (PT_EXPR) using two strings as
7167  * true/false values
7168  *
7169  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7170  * parser(in): Parser context
7171  * pred(in): a node for expression used as predicate
7172  * string1(in): string used to build a value node for true value of predicate
7173  * string2(in): string used to build a value node for false value of predicate
7174  * alias(in): alias for this new node
7175  */
7176 static PT_NODE *
7177 pt_make_if_with_strings (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * pred, const char *string1, const char *string2,
7178  const char *alias)
7179 {
7180  PT_NODE *val1_node = NULL;
7181  PT_NODE *val2_node = NULL;
7182  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
7183 
7184  val1_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, string1);
7185  val2_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, string2);
7186 
7187  if_node = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, val1_node, val2_node, alias);
7188  return if_node;
7189 }

7191 /*
7192  * pt_make_like_col_expr() - builds a LIKE operator node (PT_EXPR) using
7193  * an identifier on LHS an expression node on RHS
7194  * '<col_name> LIKE <rhs_expr>'
7195  *
7196  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7197  * parser(in): Parser context
7198  * rhs_expr(in): expression node
7199  * col_name(in): LHS column name (may contain dots)
7200  */
7201 static PT_NODE *
7202 pt_make_like_col_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * rhs_expr, const char *col_name)
7203 {

7205  PT_NODE *like_node = NULL;
7206 
7207  like_lhs = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, col_name);
7208  like_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_LIKE, like_lhs, rhs_expr, NULL);
7209 
7210  return like_node;
7211 }
7212 
7213 /*
7214  * pt_make_outer_select_for_show_stmt() - builds a SELECT node and wrap the
7215  * inner supplied SELECT node
7216  * 'SELECT * FROM (<inner_select>) <select_alias>'
7217  *
7218  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
7219  * parser(in): Parser context
7220  * inner_select(in): PT_SELECT node
7221  * select_alias(in): alias for the 'FROM specs'
7222  */
7223 static PT_NODE *
7224 pt_make_outer_select_for_show_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * inner_select, const char *select_alias)
7225 {
7226  /* SELECT * from ( SELECT .... ) <select_alias>; */
7227  PT_NODE *val_node = NULL;
7228  PT_NODE *outer_node = NULL;
7229  PT_NODE *alias_subquery = NULL;
7230  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7231 
7232  assert (inner_select != NULL);
7233  assert (inner_select->node_type == PT_SELECT);
7234 
7235  val_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
7236  if (val_node)
7237  {
7238  val_node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_STAR;
7239  }
7240  else
7241  {
7242  return NULL;
7243  }
7244 
7245  outer_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7246  if (outer_node == NULL)
7247  {
7248  return NULL;
7249  }
7250 
7251  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (outer_node, PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY);
7252 
7253  outer_node->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (val_node, outer_node->info.query.q.select.list);
7254  inner_select->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
7255 
7256  alias_subquery = pt_name (parser, select_alias);
7257  /* add to FROM an empty entity, the entity will be populated later */
7258  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, outer_node, NULL, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
7259 
7260  if (from_item == NULL)
7261  {
7262  return NULL;
7263 
7264  }
7265 
7266  from_item->info.spec.derived_table = inner_select;
7267  from_item->info.spec.meta_class = PT_MISC_NONE;
7268  from_item->info.spec.range_var = alias_subquery;
7269  from_item->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
7270  from_item->info.spec.join_type = PT_JOIN_NONE;
7271 
7272  return outer_node;
7273 }
7274 
7275 /*
7276  * pt_make_outer_select_for_show_columns() - builds a SELECT node and wrap the
7277  * inner supplied SELECT node
7278  * 'SELECT * FROM (<inner_select>) <select_alias>'
7279  *
7280  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
7281  * parser(in): Parser context
7282  * inner_select(in): PT_SELECT node
7283  * select_alias(in): alias for the 'FROM specs'
7284  * query_names(in): query column names
7285  * query_aliases(in): query column aliasses
7286  * names_length(in): the length of query_names array
7287  * is_show_full(in): non zero if show full columns
7288  * outer_node(out): the result query
7289  */
7290 static int
7291 pt_make_outer_select_for_show_columns (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * inner_select, const char *select_alias,
7292  const char **query_names, const char **query_aliases, int names_length,
7293  int is_show_full, PT_NODE ** outer_node)
7294 {
7295  /* SELECT * from ( SELECT .... ) <select_alias>; */
7296  PT_NODE *alias_subquery = NULL;
7297  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7298  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
7299  int i, error = NO_ERROR;
7300 
7301  assert (inner_select != NULL);
7302  assert (inner_select->node_type == PT_SELECT);
7303  assert (outer_node != NULL);
7304 
7305  *outer_node = NULL;
7306 
7307  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7308  if (query == NULL)
7309  {
7310  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
7311  }
7312 
7313  if (is_show_full)
7314  {
7315  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (query, PT_SELECT_FULL_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA);
7316  }
7317  else
7318  {
7319  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (query, PT_SELECT_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA);
7320  }
7321 
7322  for (i = 0; i < names_length; i++)
7323  {
7324  error = pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, query, query_names[i], query_aliases ? query_aliases[i] : NULL);
7325  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7326  {
7327  goto error_exit;
7328  }
7329  }
7330 
7331  /* add to FROM an empty entity, the entity will be populated later */
7332  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, NULL, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
7333 
7334  if (from_item == NULL)
7335  {
7336  error = ER_FAILED;
7337  goto error_exit;
7338  }
7339 
7340  inner_select->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
7341  alias_subquery = pt_name (parser, select_alias);
7342  from_item->info.spec.derived_table = inner_select;
7343  from_item->info.spec.meta_class = PT_MISC_NONE;
7344  from_item->info.spec.range_var = alias_subquery;
7345  from_item->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
7346  from_item->info.spec.join_type = PT_JOIN_NONE;
7347 
7348  *outer_node = query;
7349  return NO_ERROR;
7350 
7351 error_exit:
7352 
7353  if (query)
7354  {
7355  parser_free_tree (parser, query);
7356  }
7357  return error;
7358 }
7359 
7360 /*
7361  * pt_make_select_count_star() - builds a 'SELECT COUNT(*)' node
7362  *
7363  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
7364  * parser(in): Parser context
7365  *
7366  * Note : The created node is not complete : FROM and WHERE should be filled
7367  * after using this function
7368  */
7369 static PT_NODE *
7370 pt_make_select_count_star (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
7371 {
7372  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
7373  PT_NODE *sel_item = NULL;
7374 
7375  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7376 
7377  sel_item = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
7378 
7379  if (sel_item == NULL || query == NULL)
7380  {
7381  return NULL;
7382  }
7383  sel_item->info.function.arg_list = NULL;
7384  sel_item->info.function.function_type = PT_COUNT_STAR;
7385  query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (sel_item, query->info.query.q.select.list);
7386 
7387  return query;
7388 }
7389 
7390 
7391 /*
7392  * pt_make_field_type_expr_node() - builds the node required to print the type
7393  * of column in SHOW COLUMNS
7394  *
7395  * CONCAT(type_name, IF (prec > 0
7396  * AND (type_id=27 OR
7397  * type_id=26 OR
7398  * type_id=25 OR
7399  * type_id=24 OR
7400  * type_id=23 OR
7401  * type_id=4 OR
7402  * type_id=22),
7403  * CONCAT( '(',
7404  * prec ,
7405  * IF (type_id=22,
7406  * CONCAT( ',',
7407  * scale,
7408  * ')' )
7409  * ,')')
7410  * ) ,
7411  * IF ( type_id = 6 OR
7412  * type_id = 7 OR
7413  * type_id=8 ,
7414  * CONCAT( ' OF ',
7415  * Types_t.Composed_types),
7416  * IF (type_id = 35,
7417  * CONCAT('(',
7418  * SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(CONCAT('''', EV.a, '''') SEPARATOR ', ')
7419  * FROM TABLE(D.enumeration) as EV(a), ')'), ''))
7420  * )
7421  * ) AS Type
7422  *
7423  * - type_id values are defined in dbtype.h in DB_TYPE
7424  *
7425  *
7426  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7427  * parser(in): Parser context
7428  */
7429 static PT_NODE *
7430 pt_make_field_type_expr_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
7431 {
7432  PT_NODE *concat_node = NULL;
7433  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
7434  PT_NODE *if_node_types = NULL;
7435  PT_NODE *if_node_enum = NULL;
7436 
7437  /* CONCAT(',',scale,')') */
7438  {
7439  PT_NODE *concat_arg_list = NULL;
7440  PT_NODE *concat_arg = NULL;
7441 
7442  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, ",");
7443  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7444 
7445  concat_arg = pt_name (parser, "scale");
7446  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7447 
7448  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, ")");
7449  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7450 
7451  concat_node = parser_keyword_func ("concat", concat_arg_list);
7452  if (concat_node == NULL)
7453  {
7454  return NULL;
7455  }
7456  }
7457 
7458  /* IF( type_id=22 , CONCAT(',',scale,')') , ')' ) */
7459  {
7460  PT_NODE *pred_for_if = NULL;
7461  PT_NODE *val1_node = NULL;
7462  PT_NODE *val2_node = NULL;
7463 
7464  pred_for_if = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 22);
7465  assert (concat_node != NULL);
7466  val1_node = concat_node;
7467  val2_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, ")");
7468 
7469  if_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, pred_for_if, val1_node, val2_node);
7470  if (if_node == NULL)
7471  {
7472  return NULL;
7473  }
7474  concat_node = NULL;
7475  }
7476 
7477  /* CONCAT( '(' , prec , IF(..) ) */
7478  {
7479  PT_NODE *concat_arg_list = NULL;
7480  PT_NODE *concat_arg = NULL;
7481 
7482  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, "(");
7483  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7484 
7485  concat_arg = pt_name (parser, "prec");
7486  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7487 
7488  assert (if_node != NULL);
7489  concat_arg = if_node;
7490  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7491 
7492  concat_node = parser_keyword_func ("concat", concat_arg_list);
7493  if (concat_node == NULL)
7494  {
7495  return NULL;
7496  }
7497 
7498  if_node = NULL;
7499  }
7500 
7501  /* IF (prec > 0 AND (type_id=27 OR type_id=26 OR type_id=25 OR type_id=24 OR type_id=23 OR type_id=4 or type_id=22),
7502  * CONCAT(...) , '' ) */
7503  {
7504  PT_NODE *cond_item1 = NULL;
7505  PT_NODE *cond_item2 = NULL;
7506  PT_NODE *val1_node = NULL;
7507  PT_NODE *val2_node = NULL;
7508  PT_NODE *pred_for_if = NULL;
7509 
7510  /* VARNCHAR and CHAR */
7511  cond_item1 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 27);
7512  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 26);
7513  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7514  /* CHAR */
7515  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 25);
7516  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7517  /* VARBIT */
7518  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 24);
7519  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7520  /* BIT */
7521  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 23);
7522  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7523  /* VARCHAR */
7524  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 4);
7525  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7526  /* NUMERIC */
7527  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 22);
7528  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7529  cond_item1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
7530 
7531  /* prec */
7532  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_GT, "prec", 0);
7533  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, cond_item2, cond_item1, NULL);
7534 
7535  pred_for_if = cond_item1;
7536  assert (concat_node != NULL);
7537  val1_node = concat_node;
7538  val2_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "");
7539 
7540  if_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, pred_for_if, val1_node, val2_node);
7541  if (if_node == NULL)
7542  {
7543  return NULL;
7544  }
7545 
7546  concat_node = NULL;
7547  }
7548 
7549  /* CONCAT(' OF ',Types_t.Composed_types) */
7550  {
7551  PT_NODE *concat_arg_list = NULL;
7552  PT_NODE *concat_arg = NULL;
7553 
7554  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, " OF ");
7555  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7556 
7557  concat_arg = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "Types_t.Composed_types");
7558  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7559 
7560  concat_node = parser_keyword_func ("concat", concat_arg_list);
7561  if (concat_node == NULL)
7562  {
7563  return NULL;
7564  }
7565  }
7566 
7567  /* IF (type_id = 35, CONCAT('(', SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(CONCAT('''', EV.a, '''') SEPARATOR ', ') FROM TABLE
7568  * (D.enumeration) as EV(a), ')' ), '') */
7569  {
7570  PT_NODE *node1 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
7571  PT_NODE *node2 = NULL;
7572  PT_NODE *node3 = NULL;
7573 
7574  if (node1 == NULL)
7575  {
7576  return NULL;
7577  }
7578 
7579  /* CONCAT('''', EV.a, '''') */
7580  node2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, "'");
7581  node3 = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "EV.a");
7582  node2 = parser_append_node (node3, node2);
7583  node3 = pt_make_string_value (parser, "'");
7584  node2 = parser_append_node (node3, node2);
7585  node2 = parser_keyword_func ("concat", node2);
7586 
7587  /* GROUP_CONCAT(EV.a SEPARATOR ', ') */
7588  node1->info.function.function_type = PT_GROUP_CONCAT;
7589  node1->info.function.all_or_distinct = PT_ALL;
7590 
7591  node3 = pt_make_string_value (parser, ", ");
7592  node1->info.function.arg_list = parser_append_node (node3, node2);
7593  node1->info.function.order_by = NULL;
7594 
7595  /* TABLE(D.enumeration) as EV(a) */
7596  node2 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SPEC);
7597  if (node2 == NULL)
7598  {
7599  return NULL;
7600  }
7601  node2->info.spec.derived_table = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "D.enumeration");
7602  node2->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SET_EXPR;
7603  node2->info.spec.range_var = pt_name (parser, "EV");
7604  node2->info.spec.as_attr_list = pt_name (parser, "a");
7605 
7606  /* SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(EV.a SEPARATOR ', ') FROM TABLE(D.enumeration) as EV(a) */
7607  node3 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7608  if (node3 == NULL)
7609  {
7610  return NULL;
7611  }
7612  node3->info.query.q.select.list = node1;
7613  node3->info.query.q.select.from = node2;
7614 
7615  /* CONCAT('(', SELECT ..., ')') */
7616  node1 = pt_make_string_value (parser, "(");
7617  node1 = parser_append_node (node3, node1);
7618  node1 = parser_append_node (pt_make_string_value (parser, ")"), node1);
7619  node2 = parser_keyword_func ("concat", node1);
7620 
7621  /* IF (type_id = 35, CONCAT('(', SELECT ..., ')'), '') */
7622  node1 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 35);
7623  node3 = pt_make_string_value (parser, "");
7624  if_node_enum = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, node1, node2, node3);
7625  if (if_node_enum == NULL)
7626  {
7627  return NULL;
7628  }
7629  }
7630 
7631  /* IF ( type_id = 6 OR type_id = 7 OR type_id=8 , CONCAT( .. ),'') */
7632  {
7633  PT_NODE *cond_item1 = NULL;
7634  PT_NODE *cond_item2 = NULL;
7635  PT_NODE *val1_node = NULL;
7636  PT_NODE *val2_node = NULL;
7637  PT_NODE *pred_for_if = NULL;
7638 
7639  /* SET and MULTISET */
7640  cond_item1 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 6);
7641  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 7);
7642  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7643  /* SEQUENCE */
7644  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 8);
7645  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7646 
7647  pred_for_if = cond_item1;
7648  assert (concat_node != NULL);
7649  val1_node = concat_node;
7650  val2_node = if_node_enum;
7651 
7652  assert (pred_for_if != NULL && val1_node != NULL && val2_node != NULL);
7653 
7654  if_node_types = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, pred_for_if, val1_node, val2_node);
7655  if (if_node_types == NULL)
7656  {
7657  return NULL;
7658  }
7659  }
7660 
7661  /* CONCAT( type_name, IF(...) , IF (...) ) */
7662  {
7663  PT_NODE *concat_arg_list = NULL;
7664  PT_NODE *concat_arg = NULL;
7665 
7666  concat_arg = pt_name (parser, "type_name");
7667  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7668 
7669  assert (if_node != NULL);
7670  concat_arg = if_node;
7671  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7672 
7673  assert (if_node_types != NULL);
7674  concat_arg = if_node_types;
7675  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
7676 
7677  concat_node = parser_keyword_func ("concat", concat_arg_list);
7678  if (concat_node == NULL)
7679  {
7680  return NULL;
7681  }
7682  }
7683 
7684  concat_node->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "Type");
7685 
7686  return concat_node;
7687 }
7688 
7689 
7690 /*
7691  * pt_make_collation_expr_node() - builds the node required to print the
7692  * collation of column in SHOW COLUMNS
7693  *
7694  * (IF (type_id=27 OR type_id=26 OR type_id=25 OR type_id=4,
7695  * CL.coll_name, NULL)) AS Collation
7696  *
7697  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE)
7698  * parser(in): Parser context
7699  */
7700 static PT_NODE *
7701 pt_make_collation_expr_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
7702 {
7703  PT_NODE *collation_name = NULL;
7704  PT_NODE *null_expr = NULL;
7705  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
7706 
7707  collation_name = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "CL.coll_name");
7708 
7709  null_expr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
7710  if (null_expr)
7711  {
7712  null_expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
7713  }
7714 
7715  /* IF (type_id=27 OR type_id=26 OR type_id=25 OR type_id=4, CL.name , NULL ) */
7716  {
7717  PT_NODE *cond_item1 = NULL;
7718  PT_NODE *cond_item2 = NULL;
7719  PT_NODE *pred_for_if = NULL;
7720 
7721  /* VARNCHAR and CHAR */
7722  cond_item1 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 27);
7723  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 26);
7724  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7725  /* CHAR */
7726  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 25);
7727  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7728  /* STRING */
7729  cond_item2 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "type_id", 4);
7730  cond_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, cond_item1, cond_item2, NULL);
7731 
7732  pred_for_if = cond_item1;
7733 
7734  if_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IF, pred_for_if, collation_name, null_expr);
7735 
7736  if (if_node != NULL)
7737  {
7738  if_node->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "Collation");
7739  }
7740  }
7741 
7742  return if_node;
7743 }
7744 
7745 /*
7746  * pt_make_field_extra_expr_node() - builds the 'Extra' field for the
7747  * SHOW COLUMNS statment
7748  *
7749  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
7750  * parser(in): Parser context
7751  *
7752  * IF( (SELECT count(*)
7753  * FROM db_serial S
7754  * WHERE S.att_name = A.attr_name AND
7755  * S.class_name = C.class_name
7756  * ) >= 1 ,
7757  * 'auto_increment',
7758  * '' )
7759  * AS Extra
7760  *
7761  * Note : Currently, only 'auto_increment' is diplayed in the Extra field
7762  */
7763 static PT_NODE *
7764 pt_make_field_extra_expr_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
7765 {
7766  PT_NODE *where_item1 = NULL;
7767  PT_NODE *where_item2 = NULL;
7768  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7769  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
7770  PT_NODE *extra_node = NULL;
7771  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
7772  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
7773 
7774  /* SELECT .. FROM .. WHERE */
7775  query = pt_make_select_count_star (parser);
7776  if (query == NULL)
7777  {
7778  return NULL;
7779  }
7780 
7781  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, "db_serial", "S", DB_AUTH_NONE);
7782 
7783  /* S.att_name = A.attr_name */
7784  where_item1 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "S.att_name", "A.attr_name");
7785  /* S.class_name = C.class_name */
7786  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "S.class_name", "C.class_name");
7787 
7788  /* item1 = item2 AND item2 */
7789  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
7790  query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item1, query->info.query.q.select.where);
7791 
7792  /* IF ( SELECT (..) >=1 , 'auto_increment' , '' ) */
7793  pred_rhs = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 1);
7794 
7795  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_GE, query, pred_rhs, NULL);
7796 
7797  extra_node = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "auto_increment", "", "Extra");
7798 
7799  return extra_node;
7800 }
7801 
7802 /*
7803  * pt_make_field_key_type_expr_node() - builds the 'Key' field for the
7804  * SHOW COLUMNS statment
7805  *
7806  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
7807  * parser(in): Parser context
7808  *
7809  * IF ( pri_key_count > 0,
7810  * 'PRI' ,
7811  * IF (uni_key_count > 0 ,
7812  * 'UNI',
7813  * IF (mul_count > 0 ,
7814  * 'MUL',
7815  * '')
7816  * )
7817  * )
7818  *
7819  *
7820  * Note : PRI : when the column is part of an index with primary key
7821  * UNI : when the column is part of an index with unique key
7822  * MUL : when the column is the first column in a non-unique index
7823  * if more than one applies to a column, only the one is displayed,
7824  * in the order PRI,UNI,MUL
7825  * '' : no index on the column
7826  */
7827 static PT_NODE *
7828 pt_make_field_key_type_expr_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
7829 {
7830  PT_NODE *pri_key_query = NULL;
7831  PT_NODE *uni_key_query = NULL;
7832  PT_NODE *mul_query = NULL;
7833  PT_NODE *key_node = NULL;
7834 
7835  {
7836  /* pri_key_count : (SELECT count (*) FROM (SELECT IK.key_attr_name ATTR, I.is_primary_key PRI_KEY FROM
7837  * _db_index_key IK , _db_index I WHERE IK IN I.key_attrs AND IK.key_attr_name = A.attr_name AND I.class_of =
7838  * A.class_of AND A.class_of.class_name=C.class_name) constraints_pri_key WHERE PRI_KEY=1) */
7839  PT_NODE *sub_query = NULL;
7840  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7841  PT_NODE *where_item1 = NULL;
7842  PT_NODE *where_item2 = NULL;
7843  PT_NODE *alias_subquery = NULL;
7844 
7845  /* SELECT IK.key_attr_name ATTR, I.is_primary_key PRI_KEY FROM _db_index_key IK , _db_index I WHERE IK IN
7846  * I.key_attrs AND IK.key_attr_name = A.attr_name AND I.class_of = A.class_of AND A.class_of.class_name =
7847  * C.class_name */
7848  sub_query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7849  if (sub_query == NULL)
7850  {
7851  return NULL;
7852  }
7853 
7854  /* SELECT list : */
7855  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, sub_query, "IK.key_attr_name", "ATTR");
7856  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, sub_query, "I.is_primary_key", "PRI_KEY");
7857  /* .. FROM : */
7858  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, sub_query, "_db_index_key", "IK", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
7859  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, sub_query, "_db_index", "I", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
7860 
7861  /* .. WHERE : */
7862  where_item1 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_IS_IN, "IK", "I.key_attrs");
7863  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "IK.key_attr_name", "A.attr_name");
7864  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
7865 
7866  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "I.class_of", "A.class_of");
7867  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
7868 
7869  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "A.class_of.class_name", "C.class_name");
7870  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
7871 
7872  /* WHERE clause should be empty */
7873  assert (sub_query->info.query.q.select.where == NULL);
7874  sub_query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item1, sub_query->info.query.q.select.where);
7875 
7876  /* outer query : SELECT count (*) FROM (..) WHERE PRI_KEY=1 */
7877  pri_key_query = pt_make_select_count_star (parser);
7878  if (pri_key_query == NULL)
7879  {
7880  return NULL;
7881  }
7882 
7883  /* add to FROM and empy entity, the entity will be populated later */
7884  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, pri_key_query, NULL, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
7885  if (from_item == NULL)
7886  {
7887  return NULL;
7888  }
7889  alias_subquery = pt_name (parser, "constraints_pri_key");
7890 
7891  from_item->info.spec.derived_table = sub_query;
7892  from_item->info.spec.meta_class = PT_MISC_NONE;
7893  from_item->info.spec.range_var = alias_subquery;
7894  from_item->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
7895  from_item->info.spec.join_type = PT_JOIN_NONE;
7896  where_item1 = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "PRI_KEY", 1);
7897  pri_key_query->info.query.q.select.where =
7898  parser_append_node (where_item1, pri_key_query->info.query.q.select.where);
7899  /* pri_key_count query is done */
7900  }
7901 
7902  {
7903  /* uni_key_count : (SELECT count (*) FROM (SELECT IK.key_attr_name ATTR, I.is_unique UNI_KEY FROM _db_index_key IK
7904  * , _db_index I WHERE IK IN I.key_attrs AND IK.key_attr_name = A.attr_name AND I.class_of = A.class_of AND
7905  * A.class_of.class_name = C.class_name) constraints_pri_key WHERE UNI_KEY=1) */
7906  PT_NODE *sub_query = NULL;
7907  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
7908  PT_NODE *where_item1 = NULL;
7909  PT_NODE *where_item2 = NULL;
7910  PT_NODE *alias_subquery = NULL;

7913  * AND IK.key_attr_name = A.attr_name AND I.class_of = A.class_of AND A.class_of.class_name = C.class_name */
7914  sub_query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
7915  if (sub_query == NULL)
7916  {
7917  return NULL;
7918  }

7940  sub_query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item1, sub_query->info.query.q.select.where);
7941

7980  * A.attr_name AND I.class_of = A.class_of AND A.class_of.class_name = C.class_name AND IK.key_order = 0 */
