8030 
8031  /* IF ( pri_key_count > 0, 'PRI' , IF (uni_key_count > 0 , 'UNI', IF (mul_count > 0 , 'MUL', '') ) ) */
8032  {
8033  PT_NODE *if_node1 = NULL;
8034  PT_NODE *if_node2 = NULL;
8035  PT_NODE *if_node3 = NULL;
8036 
8037  {
8038  /* IF (mul_count > 0 , 'MUL', '' */
8039  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
8040  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
8041 
8042  pred_rhs = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 0);
8043 
8044  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_GT, mul_query, pred_rhs, NULL);
8045 
8046  if_node3 = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "MUL", "", NULL);
8047  }
8048 
8049  {
8050  /* IF (uni_key_count > 0 , 'UNI', (..IF..) */
8051  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
8052  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
8053  PT_NODE *string1_node = NULL;
8054 
8055  pred_rhs = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 0);
8056 
8057  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_GT, uni_key_query, pred_rhs, NULL);
8058 
8059  string1_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "UNI");
8060 
8061  if_node2 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string1_node, if_node3, NULL);
8062  }
8063 
8064  {
8065  /* pri_key_count > 0, 'PRI', (..IF..) */
8066  PT_NODE *pred_rhs = NULL;
8067  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
8068  PT_NODE *string1_node = NULL;
8069 
8070  pred_rhs = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 0);
8071 
8072  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_GT, pri_key_query, pred_rhs, NULL);
8073 
8074  string1_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "PRI");
8075 
8076  if_node1 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string1_node, if_node2, "Key");
8077  }
8078  key_node = if_node1;
8079  }
8080  return key_node;
8081 }
8082 
8083 /*
8084  * pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier() - builds a SORT_SPEC for GROUP BY or
8085  * ORDER BY using a column indentifier
8086  *
8087  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
8088  * parser(in): Parser context
8089  * identifier(in): full name of identifier
8090  * sort_mode(in): sorting ascendint or descending; if this parameter is not
8091  * PT_ASC or PT_DESC, the function will return NULL
8092  */
8093 static PT_NODE *
8094 pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *identifier, PT_MISC_TYPE sort_mode)
8095 {
8096  PT_NODE *group_by_node = NULL;
8097  PT_NODE *group_by_col = NULL;
8098 
8099  if (sort_mode != PT_ASC && sort_mode != PT_DESC)
8100  {
8101  assert (false);
8102  return NULL;
8103  }
8104  group_by_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SORT_SPEC);
8105  if (group_by_node == NULL)
8106  {
8107  return NULL;
8108  }
8109 
8110  group_by_col = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, identifier);
8111  group_by_node->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc = sort_mode;
8112  group_by_node->info.sort_spec.expr = group_by_col;
8113 
8114  return group_by_node;
8115 }
8116 
8117 /*
8118  * pt_make_sort_spec_with_number() - builds a SORT_SPEC for ORDER BY using
8119  * a numeric indentifier
8120  * used in : < ORDER BY <x> <ASC|DESC> >
8121  *
8122  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
8123  * parser(in): Parser context
8124  * number_pos(in): position number for ORDER BY
8125  * sort_mode(in): sorting ascendint or descending; if this parameter is not
8126  * PT_ASC or PT_DESC, the function will return NULL
8127  */
8128 static PT_NODE *
8129 pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const int number_pos, PT_MISC_TYPE sort_mode)
8130 {
8131  PT_NODE *sort_spec_node = NULL;
8132  PT_NODE *sort_spec_num = NULL;
8133 
8134  if (sort_mode != PT_ASC && sort_mode != PT_DESC)
8135  {
8136  assert (false);
8137  return NULL;
8138  }
8139  sort_spec_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SORT_SPEC);
8140  if (sort_spec_node == NULL)
8141  {
8142  return NULL;
8143  }
8144 
8145  sort_spec_num = pt_make_integer_value (parser, number_pos);
8146  sort_spec_node->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc = sort_mode;
8147  sort_spec_node->info.sort_spec.expr = sort_spec_num;
8148 
8149  return sort_spec_node;
8150 }
8151 
8152 /*
8153  * pt_make_collection_type_subquery_node() - builds a SELECT subquery used
8154  * construct the string to display
8155  * the list of sub-types for a collection
8156  * type (SET , SEQUENCE, MULTISET);
8157  * used to build SHOW COLUMNS statement
8158  *
8159  *
8160  * SELECT AA.attr_name ATTR,
8161  * GROUP_CONCAT( TT.type_name ORDER BY 1 SEPARATOR ',')
8162  * Composed_types
8163  * FROM _db_attribute AA, _db_domain DD , _db_data_type TT
8164  * WHERE AA.class_of.class_name = '<table_name>' AND
8165  * DD.data_type = TT.type_id AND
8166  * DD.object_of IN AA.domains
8167  * GROUP BY AA.attr_name)
8168  *
8169  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
8170  * parser(in): Parser context
8171  * table_name(in): name of table to filter by ; only the columns from this
8172  * table are checked for their type
8173  *
8174  */
8175 static PT_NODE *
8176 pt_make_collection_type_subquery_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *table_name)
8177 {
8178  PT_NODE *where_item1 = NULL;
8179  PT_NODE *where_item2 = NULL;
8180  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
8181  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
8182 
8183  assert (table_name != NULL);
8184 
8185  /* SELECT .. FROM .. WHERE */
8186  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
8187  if (query == NULL)
8188  {
8189  return NULL;
8190  }
8191 
8192  query->info.query.is_subquery = PT_IS_SUBQUERY;
8193 
8194  /* SELECT list : */
8195  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, query, "AA.attr_name", "ATTR");
8196 
8197  {
8198  /* add GROUP_CONCAT (...) */
8199  PT_NODE *sel_item = NULL;
8200  PT_NODE *group_concat_field = NULL;
8201  PT_NODE *group_concat_sep = NULL;
8202  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
8203 
8204  sel_item = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
8205  if (sel_item == NULL)
8206  {
8207  return NULL;
8208  }
8209 
8210  sel_item->info.function.function_type = PT_GROUP_CONCAT;
8211  sel_item->info.function.all_or_distinct = PT_ALL;
8212 
8213  group_concat_field = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "TT.type_name");
8214  group_concat_sep = pt_make_string_value (parser, ",");
8215  sel_item->info.function.arg_list = parser_append_node (group_concat_sep, group_concat_field);
8216 
8217  /* add ORDER BY */
8218  assert (sel_item->info.function.order_by == NULL);
8219 
8220  /* By 1 */
8221  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 1, PT_ASC);
8222  sel_item->info.function.order_by = order_by_item;
8223 
8224  sel_item->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "Composed_types");
8225  query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (sel_item, query->info.query.q.select.list);
8226  }
8227 
8228  /* FROM : */
8229  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, "_db_attribute", "AA", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
8230  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, "_db_domain", "DD", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
8231  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, "_db_data_type", "TT", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
8232 
8233  /* WHERE : */
8234  /* AA.class_of.class_name = '<table_name>' */
8235  where_item1 = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "AA.class_of.class_name", table_name);
8236  /* DD.data_type = TT.type_id */
8237  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "DD.data_type", "TT.type_id");
8238  /* item1 = item2 AND item2 */
8239  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
8240 
8241  /* DD.object_of IN AA.domains */
8242  where_item2 = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_IS_IN, "DD.object_of", "AA.domains");
8243  where_item1 = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_item1, where_item2, NULL);
8244 
8245  query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item1, query->info.query.q.select.where);
8246 
8247  /* GROUP BY : */
8248  {
8249  PT_NODE *group_by_node = NULL;
8250 
8251  group_by_node = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "AA.attr_name", PT_ASC);
8252  if (group_by_node == NULL)
8253  {
8254  return NULL;
8255  }
8256  query->info.query.q.select.group_by = group_by_node;
8257  }
8258 
8259  return query;
8260 }
8261 
8262 /*
8263  * pt_make_dummy_query_check_table() - builds a SELECT subquery used check
8264  * if the table exists; when attached to
8265  * the SHOW statement, it should cause an
8266  * execution error, instead of displaying
8267  * 'no results';
8268  * used to build SHOW COLUMNS statement
8269  *
8270  * SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <table_name> LIMIT 1;
8271  *
8272  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
8273  * parser(in): Parser context
8274  * table_name(in): name of table
8275  *
8276  */
8277 static PT_NODE *
8278 pt_make_dummy_query_check_table (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *table_name)
8279 {
8280  PT_NODE *limit_item = NULL;
8281  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
8282  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
8283 
8284  assert (table_name != NULL);
8285 
8286  /* This query should cause an execution errors when performing SHOW COLUMNS on a non-existing table or when the user
8287  * doesn't have SELECT privilege on that table; A simpler query like: SELECT 1 FROM <table_name> WHERE FALSE; is
8288  * removed during parse tree optimizations, and no error is printed when user has insuficient privileges. We need a
8289  * query which will not be removed on translation (in order to be kept up to the authentication stage, but also with
8290  * low impact on performance. */
8291  /* We use : SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <table_name> LIMIT 1; TODO: this will impact performance so we might find a better
8292  * solution */
8293  query = pt_make_select_count_star (parser);
8294  if (query == NULL)
8295  {
8296  return NULL;
8297  }
8298  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, table_name, "DUMMY", DB_AUTH_NONE);
8299 
8300  limit_item = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 1);
8301  query->info.query.limit = limit_item;
8302 
8303  return query;
8304 }
8305 
8306 /*
8307  * pt_make_query_show_table() - builds the query used for SHOW TABLES
8308  *
8309  * SELECT * FROM (SELECT C.class_name AS tables_in_<dbname>,
8310  * IF(class_type='CLASS','VIEW','BASE TABLE')
8311  * AS table_type
8312  * FROM db_class C
8313  * WHERE is_system_class='NO') show_tables
8314  * ORDER BY 1;
8315  *
8316  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
8317  * parser(in): Parser context
8318  * is_full_syntax(in): true, if the SHOW statement contains the 'FULL' token
8319  * like_where_syntax(in): indicator of presence for LIKE or WHERE clauses in
8320  * SHOW statement. Values : 0 = none of LIKE or WHERE,
8321  * 1 = contains LIKE, 2 = contains WHERE
8322  * like_or_where_expr(in): node expression supplied as condition (in WHERE)
8323  * or RHS for LIKE
8324  *
8325  */
8326 PT_NODE *
8327 pt_make_query_show_table (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, bool is_full_syntax, int like_where_syntax,
8328  PT_NODE * like_or_where_expr)
8329 {
8330  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
8331  PT_NODE *sub_query = NULL;
8332  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
8333  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
8334  char tables_col_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH] = { 0 };
8335 
8336  {
8337  char *db_name = db_get_database_name ();
8338  const char *const col_header = "Tables_in_";
8339 
8340  if (db_name == NULL)
8341  {
8342  return NULL;
8343  }
8344 
8345  strcpy (tables_col_name, col_header);
8346  strncat (tables_col_name, db_name, SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH - strlen (col_header) - 1);
8347  tables_col_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH - 1] = '\0';
8348  db_string_free (db_name);
8349  db_name = NULL;
8350  }
8351 
8352  sub_query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
8353  if (sub_query == NULL)
8354  {
8355  return NULL;
8356  }
8357 
8358  /* ------ SELECT list ------- */
8359  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, sub_query, "C.class_name", tables_col_name);
8360 
8361  /* ------ SELECT ... FROM ------- */
8362  /* db_class is a view on the _db_class table; we are selecting from the view, to avoid checking the authorization as
8363  * this check is already performed by the view */
8364  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, sub_query, "db_class", "C", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
8365 
8366  /* ------ SELECT ... WHERE ------- */
8367  /* create item for "WHERE is_system_class = 'NO'" */
8368  where_item = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "is_system_class", "NO");
8369  sub_query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, sub_query->info.query.q.select.where);
8370 
8371  if (is_full_syntax)
8372  {
8373  /* SHOW FULL : add second column : 'BASE TABLE' or 'VIEW' */
8374  PT_NODE *eq_node = NULL;
8375  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
8376 
8377  /* create IF ( class_type = 'CLASS', 'BASE TABLE', 'VIEW') */
8378  eq_node = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "class_type", "CLASS");
8379  if_node = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, eq_node, "BASE TABLE", "VIEW", "Table_type");
8380 
8381  /* add IF to SELECT list, list should not be empty at this point */
8382  assert (sub_query->info.query.q.select.list != NULL);
8383 
8384  sub_query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (if_node, sub_query->info.query.q.select.list);
8385  }
8386 
8387  /* done with subquery, create the enclosing query : SELECT * from ( SELECT .... ) show_tables; */
8388 
8389  node = pt_make_outer_select_for_show_stmt (parser, sub_query, "show_tables");
8390  if (node == NULL)
8391  {
8392  return NULL;
8393  }
8394 
8395  {
8396  /* add ORDER BY */
8397  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
8398 
8399  assert (node->info.query.order_by == NULL);
8400  /* By Tables_in_<db_name> */
8401  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 1, PT_ASC);
8402  node->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, node->info.query.order_by);
8403  }
8404 
8405  if (like_or_where_expr != NULL)
8406  {
8407  if (like_where_syntax == 1)
8408  {
8409  /* make LIKE */
8410  where_item = pt_make_like_col_expr (parser, like_or_where_expr, tables_col_name);
8411  }
8412  else
8413  {
8414  /* WHERE */
8415  assert (like_where_syntax == 2);
8416  where_item = like_or_where_expr;
8417  }
8418 
8419  node->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, node->info.query.q.select.where);
8420  }
8421  else
8422  {
8423  assert (like_where_syntax == 0);
8424  }
8425 
8426  return node;
8427 }
8428 
8429 /*
8430  * check_arg_valid() - check argument type and set error code if not valid
8431  *
8432  * return: true - valid, false - not valid, semantic check error will set when return false.
8433  * parser(in):
8434  * arg_meta(in): argument validation rule
8435  * arg_num(in): argument sequence
8436  * val(in): argument value node
8437  */
8438 static bool
8439 check_arg_valid (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const SHOWSTMT_NAMED_ARG * arg_meta, int arg_num, PT_NODE * val)
8440 {
8441  bool valid = false;
8442 
8443  switch (arg_meta->type)
8444  {
8445  case AVT_INTEGER:
8446  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (val) && val->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
8447  {
8448  valid = true;
8449  }
8450  else if (arg_meta->optional && PT_IS_NULL_NODE (val))
8451  {
8452  valid = true;
8453  }
8454 
8455  if (!valid)
8456  {
8457  /* expect unsigned integer value in here */
8458  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNEXPECTED_NTH_ARGUMENT,
8459  "positive integer value", arg_num);
8460  }
8461  break;
8462 
8463  case AVT_STRING:
8464  if (PT_IS_VALUE_NODE (val) && val->type_enum == PT_TYPE_CHAR)
8465  {
8466  valid = true;
8467  }
8468  else if (arg_meta->optional && PT_IS_NULL_NODE (val))
8469  {
8470  valid = true;
8471  }
8472 
8473  if (!valid)
8474  {
8475  /* expect string value in here */
8476  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNEXPECTED_NTH_ARGUMENT, "string value",
8477  arg_num);
8478  }
8479  break;
8480 
8481  case AVT_IDENTIFIER:
8482  if (PT_IS_NAME_NODE (val))
8483  {
8484  valid = true;
8485  }
8486  else if (arg_meta->optional && PT_IS_NULL_NODE (val))
8487  {
8488  valid = true;
8489  }
8490 
8491  if (!valid)
8492  {
8493  /* expect identifier in here */
8494  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNEXPECTED_NTH_ARGUMENT, "identifier",
8495  arg_num);
8496  }
8497  break;
8498 
8499  default:
8500  assert (0);
8501  }
8502 
8503  return valid;
8504 }
8505 
8506 /*
8507  * pt_resolve_showstmt_args_unnamed() -
8508  * do semantic check for unnamed arguments by specified meta data
8509  * from SHOWSTMT_NAMED_ARG.
8510  *
8511  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE) for arguments
8512  * parser(in): Parser context
8513  * arg_infos(in): array for meta data of argument
8514  * arg_info_count(in): array count of arg_infos
8515  * arg_infos(in): argument node to be processed
8516  */
8517 static PT_NODE *
8518 pt_resolve_showstmt_args_unnamed (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const SHOWSTMT_NAMED_ARG * arg_infos, int arg_info_count,
8519  PT_NODE * args)
8520 {
8521  int i;
8522  PT_NODE *arg, *id_string;
8523  PT_NODE *prev = NULL, *head = NULL;
8524 
8525  if (arg_info_count == 0)
8526  {
8527  return args;
8528  }
8529 
8530  /* process each argument by meta information */
8531  i = 0;
8532  arg = args;
8533 
8534  for (; i < arg_info_count && arg != NULL; i++, arg = arg->next)
8535  {
8536  if (!check_arg_valid (parser, &arg_infos[i], i + 1, arg))
8537  {
8538  goto error;
8539  }
8540 
8541  if (arg_infos[i].type == AVT_IDENTIFIER)
8542  {
8543  /* replace identifier node with string value node */
8544  id_string = pt_make_string_value (parser, arg->info.name.original);
8545  if (id_string == NULL)
8546  {
8547  goto error;
8548  }
8549 
8550  id_string->next = arg->next;
8551  arg = id_string;
8552  }
8553 
8554  if (prev == NULL)
8555  {
8556  head = arg;
8557  }
8558  else
8559  {
8560  prev->next = arg;
8561  }
8562 
8563  prev = arg;
8564  }
8565 
8566  if (arg != NULL)
8567  {
8568  /* too many arguments, n-th argument is not needed */
8569  PT_ERRORm (parser, arg, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENT);
8570  goto error;
8571  }
8572 
8573  if (i < arg_info_count)
8574  {
8575  /* too few arguments */
8576  PT_ERRORmf (parser, head, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_TOO_FEW_ARGUMENT, arg_info_count);
8577  goto error;
8578  }
8579 
8580  return head;
8581 
8582 error:
8583  return NULL;
8584 }
8585 
8586 /*
8587  * pt_resolve_showstmt_args_named() -
8588  * do semantic check for named arguments by specified meta data
8589  * from SHOWSTMT_NAMED_ARG.
8590  *
8591  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE) for arguments
8592  * parser(in): Parser context
8593  * arg_infos(in): array for meta data of argument
8594  * arg_info_count(in): array count of arg_infos
8595  * arg_infos(in): argument node to be processed
8596  */
8597 static PT_NODE *
8598 pt_resolve_showstmt_args_named (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const SHOWSTMT_NAMED_ARG * arg_infos, int arg_info_count,
8599  PT_NODE * args)
8600 {
8601  int i;
8602  bool found = false;
8603  PT_NODE *name_node, *value_node;
8604  PT_NODE *prev = NULL, *res = NULL;
8605  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
8606 
8607  if (arg_info_count == 0)
8608  {
8609  return args;
8610  }
8611 
8612  for (i = 0; i < arg_info_count; i++)
8613  {
8614  found = false;
8615  prev = NULL;
8616 
8617  for (arg = args; arg != NULL; arg = arg->next)
8618  {
8619  assert (arg->node_type == PT_NAMED_ARG);
8620 
8621  name_node = arg->info.named_arg.name;
8622  value_node = arg->info.named_arg.value;
8623 
8624  if (strcasecmp (name_node->info.name.original, arg_infos[i].name) == 0)
8625  {
8626  if (!check_arg_valid (parser, &arg_infos[i], i + 1, value_node))
8627  {
8628  goto error;
8629  }
8630 
8631  if (arg_infos[i].type == AVT_IDENTIFIER)
8632  {
8633  /* replace identifier node with string value node */
8634  value_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, value_node->info.name.original);
8635  }
8636 
8637  res = parser_append_node (value_node, res);
8638  arg->info.named_arg.value = NULL;
8639 
8640  /* remove processed arg */
8641  if (prev)
8642  {
8643  prev->next = arg->next;
8644  }
8645  else
8646  {
8647  args = arg->next;
8648  }
8649  found = true;
8650  break;
8651  }
8652 
8653  prev = arg;
8654  }
8655 
8656  if (!found)
8657  {
8658  /* missing argument */
8659  PT_ERRORmf (parser, args, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MISSING_ARGUMENT, arg_infos[i].name);
8660  goto error;
8661  }
8662  }
8663 
8664  /* all argument should be processed and nothing left */
8665  if (args != NULL)
8666  {
8667  /* unknown argument */
8668  PT_ERRORmf (parser, args, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNKNOWN_ARGUMENT,
8669  arg->info.named_arg.name->info.name.original);
8670  goto error;
8671  }
8672 
8673  return res;
8674 
8675 error:
8676  return NULL;
8677 }
8678 
8679 /*
8680  * pt_make_query_showstmt () - builds the query for SHOW statement
8681  *
8682  * return: newly built node (PT_NODE), NULL if construction fails
8683  * parser(in): Parser context
8684  * type (int): show statement type
8685  * arg (in): show statement arguments
8686  *
8687  * Notes: make query as:
8688  *
8689  * SELECT *
8690  * FROM (pt_showstmt_info(type, args))
8691  * [WHERE expr]
8692  * [ORDER BY sort_col asc_or_desc]
8693  *
8694  */
8695 PT_NODE *
8696 pt_make_query_showstmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, unsigned int type, PT_NODE * args, int like_where_syntax,
8697  PT_NODE * like_or_where_expr)
8698 {
8699  const SHOWSTMT_METADATA *meta = NULL;
8700  const SHOWSTMT_COLUMN_ORDERBY *orderby = NULL;
8701  int num_orderby;
8702  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
8703  PT_NODE *value, *from_item, *showstmt_info;
8704  PT_NODE *order_by_item;
8705  int i;
8706 
8707  /* get show column info */
8708  meta = showstmt_get_metadata ((SHOWSTMT_TYPE) type);
8709 
8710  if (meta->only_for_dba)
8711  {
8712  if (!au_is_dba_group_member (Au_user))
8713  {
8714  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_AU_DBA_ONLY, 1, meta->alias_print);
8715  return NULL;
8716  }
8717  }
8718 
8719  orderby = meta->orderby;
8720  num_orderby = meta->num_orderby;
8721 
8722  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
8723  if (query == NULL)
8724  {
8725  return NULL;
8726  }
8727 
8728  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (query, PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY);
8729 
8730  value = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
8731  if (value == NULL)
8732  {
8733  goto error;
8734  }
8735  value->type_enum = PT_TYPE_STAR;
8736  query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (value, query->info.query.q.select.list);
8737 
8738  showstmt_info = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SHOWSTMT);
8739  if (showstmt_info == NULL)
8740  {
8741  goto error;
8742  }
8743  showstmt_info->info.showstmt.show_type = (SHOWSTMT_TYPE) type;
8744 
8745  if (meta->args != NULL)
8746  {
8747  if (meta->args[0].name == NULL)
8748  {
8749  showstmt_info->info.showstmt.show_args =
8750  pt_resolve_showstmt_args_unnamed (parser, meta->args, meta->arg_size, args);
8751  }
8752  else
8753  {
8754  showstmt_info->info.showstmt.show_args =
8755  pt_resolve_showstmt_args_named (parser, meta->args, meta->arg_size, args);
8756  }
8757  if (showstmt_info->info.showstmt.show_args == NULL)
8758  {
8759  goto error;
8760  }
8761  }
8762 
8763  /* add to FROM an empty entity, the entity will be populated later */
8764  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, NULL, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
8765  if (from_item == NULL)
8766  {
8767  goto error;
8768  }
8769  from_item->info.spec.derived_table = showstmt_info;
8770  from_item->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SHOWSTMT;
8771  from_item->info.spec.meta_class = PT_MISC_NONE;
8772  from_item->info.spec.join_type = PT_JOIN_NONE;
8773 
8774  if (like_or_where_expr != NULL)
8775  {
8776  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
8777 
8778  if (like_where_syntax == 1)
8779  {
8780  /* there would be least one column */
8781  assert (meta->num_cols > 0);
8782  where_item = pt_make_like_col_expr (parser, like_or_where_expr, meta->cols[0].name);
8783  }
8784  else
8785  {
8786  assert (like_where_syntax == 2);
8787  where_item = like_or_where_expr;
8788  }
8789 
8790  query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, query->info.query.q.select.where);
8791  }
8792  else
8793  {
8794  assert (like_where_syntax == 0);
8795  }
8796 
8797  for (i = 0; i < num_orderby; i++)
8798  {
8799  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, orderby[i].pos, orderby[i].asc ? PT_ASC : PT_DESC);
8800  if (order_by_item == NULL)
8801  {
8802  goto error;
8803  }
8804  query->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, query->info.query.order_by);
8805  }
8806  return query;
8807 
8808 error:
8809  if (query != NULL)
8810  {
8811  parser_free_tree (parser, query);
8812  }
8813 
8814  return NULL;
8815 }
8816 
8817 /*
8818  * pt_make_query_show_columns() - builds the query for SHOW COLUMNS
8819  *
8820  * return: newly built node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
8821  * parser(in): Parser context
8822  * original_cls_id(in): node (PT_NAME) containing name of class
8823  *
8824  * SELECT Field AS Field,
8825  * Type AS Type
8826  * [Collation AS Collation]
8827  * Null AS Null
8828  * Key AS Key
8829  * Default AS Default
8830  * Extra AS Extra
8831  * [Comment AS Comment]
8832  * FROM
8833  * (SELECT 0 AS Attr_Type,
8834  * 0 AS Def_Order
8835  * "" AS Field,
8836  * 0 AS Type,
8837  * ["" AS Collation]
8838  * "" AS Null,
8839  * 0 AS Key,
8840  * "" AS Default,
8841  * "" AS Extra,
8842  * ["" AS Comment]
8843  * FROM <table> ORDER BY 3, 5)
8844  * [LIKE 'pattern' | WHERE expr];
8845  *
8846  * like_where_syntax(in): indicator of presence for LIKE or WHERE clauses in
8847  * SHOW statement. Values : 0 = none of LIKE or WHERE,
8848  * 1 = contains LIKE, 2 = contains WHERE
8849  * like_or_where_expr(in): node expression supplied as condition (in WHERE)
8850  * or RHS for LIKE
8851  *
8852  * Note : Order is defined by: attr_type (shared attributes first, then
8853  * class attributes, then normal attributes), order of definition in
8854  * table
8855  * [ ] -> optional fields controlled by 'is_show_full' argument
8856  * Note : At execution, all empty fields from inner query will be replaced by
8857  * values that will be read from class schema
8858  */
8859 PT_NODE *
8860 pt_make_query_show_columns (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * original_cls_id, int like_where_syntax,
8861  PT_NODE * like_or_where_expr, int is_show_full)
8862 {
8863  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
8864  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
8865  PT_NODE *sub_query = NULL;
8866  PT_NODE *outer_query = NULL;
8867  char lower_table_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
8868  PT_NODE *value = NULL, *value_list = NULL;
8869  DB_VALUE db_valuep[10];
8870  const char **psubquery_aliases = NULL, **pquery_names = NULL, **pquery_aliases = NULL;
8871  int subquery_list_size = is_show_full ? 10 : 8;
8872  int query_list_size = subquery_list_size - 2;
8873 
8874  const char *subquery_aliases[] = { "Attr_Type", "Def_Order", "Field", "Type", "Null", "Key", "Default",
8875  "Extra"
8876  };
8877  const char *subquery_full_aliases[] = { "Attr_Type", "Def_Order", "Field", "Type", "Collation", "Null",
8878  "Key", "Default", "Extra", "Comment"
8879  };
8880 
8881  const char *query_names[] = { "Field", "Type", "Null", "Key", "Default", "Extra" };
8882 
8883  const char *query_aliases[] = { "Field", "Type", "Null", "Key", "Default", "Extra" };
8884 
8885  const char *query_full_names[] = { "Field", "Type", "Collation", "Null", "Key", "Default", "Extra",
8886  "Comment"
8887  };
8888 
8889  const char *query_full_aliases[] = { "Field", "Type", "Collation", "Null", "Key", "Default", "Extra",
8890  "Comment"
8891  };
8892 
8893  int i = 0;
8894 
8895  assert (original_cls_id != NULL);
8896  assert (original_cls_id->node_type == PT_NAME);
8897 
8898  sub_query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
8899  if (sub_query == NULL)
8900  {
8901  return NULL;
8902  }
8903 
8904  if (is_show_full)
8905  {
8906  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (sub_query, PT_SELECT_FULL_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA);
8907  }
8908  else
8909  {
8910  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (sub_query, PT_SELECT_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA);
8911  }
8912 
8913  intl_identifier_lower (original_cls_id->info.name.original, lower_table_name);
8914 
8915  db_make_int (db_valuep + 0, 0);
8916  db_make_int (db_valuep + 1, 0);
8917  for (i = 2; i < subquery_list_size; i++)
8918  {
8919  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + i, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
8920  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
8921  }
8922 
8923  psubquery_aliases = is_show_full ? subquery_full_aliases : subquery_aliases;
8924  pquery_names = is_show_full ? query_full_names : query_names;
8925  pquery_aliases = is_show_full ? query_full_aliases : query_aliases;
8926 
8927  for (i = 0; i < subquery_list_size; i++)
8928  {
8929  value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, db_valuep + i);
8930  if (value == NULL)
8931  {
8932  goto error;
8933  }
8934  value->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, psubquery_aliases[i]);
8935  value_list = parser_append_node (value, value_list);
8936  }
8937 
8938  sub_query->info.query.q.select.list = value_list;
8939  value_list = NULL;
8940 
8941  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, sub_query, lower_table_name, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
8942  if (from_item == NULL)
8943  {
8944  goto error;
8945  }
8946 
8947  if (pt_make_outer_select_for_show_columns (parser, sub_query, NULL, pquery_names, pquery_aliases, query_list_size,
8948  is_show_full, &outer_query) != NO_ERROR)
8949  {
8950  goto error;
8951  }
8952 
8953  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "Attr_Type", PT_DESC);
8954  if (order_by_item == NULL)
8955  {
8956  goto error;
8957  }
8958  outer_query->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, outer_query->info.query.order_by);
8959 
8960  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "Def_Order", PT_ASC);
8961  if (order_by_item == NULL)
8962  {
8963  goto error;
8964  }
8965  outer_query->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, outer_query->info.query.order_by);
8966 
8967  /* no ORDER BY to outer SELECT */
8968  /* add LIKE or WHERE from SHOW , if present */
8969  if (like_or_where_expr != NULL)
8970  {
8971  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
8972 
8973  if (like_where_syntax == 1)
8974  {
8975  /* LIKE token */
8976  where_item = pt_make_like_col_expr (parser, like_or_where_expr, "Field");
8977  }
8978  else
8979  {
8980  /* WHERE token */
8981  assert (like_where_syntax == 2);
8982  where_item = like_or_where_expr;
8983  }
8984 
8985  outer_query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, outer_query->info.query.q.select.where);
8986  }
8987  else
8988  {
8989  assert (like_where_syntax == 0);
8990  }
8991 
8992  return outer_query;
8993 
8994 error:
8995  if (outer_query)
8996  {
8997  parser_free_tree (parser, outer_query);
8998  }
8999  else if (sub_query)
9000  {
9001  parser_free_tree (parser, sub_query);
9002  }
9003 
9004  if (value_list)
9005  {
9006  parser_free_tree (parser, value_list);
9007  }
9008 
9009  return NULL;
9010 }
9011 
9012 /*
9013  * pt_help_show_create_table() help to generate create table string.
9014  * parser(in) : Parser context
9015  * table_name(in): table name node
9016  * strbuf(out) : string of create table.
9017  */
9018 static void
9019 pt_help_show_create_table (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * table_name, string_buffer & strbuf)
9020 {
9021  DB_OBJECT *class_op;
9022  int is_class = 0;
9023 
9024  /* look up class in all schema's */
9025  class_op = sm_find_class (table_name->info.name.original);
9026  if (class_op == NULL)
9027  {
9028  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
9029  {
9030  PT_ERRORc (parser, table_name, er_msg ());
9031  }
9032  return;
9033  }
9034 
9035  is_class = db_is_class (class_op);
9036  if (is_class < 0)
9037  {
9038  if (er_errid () != NO_ERROR)
9039  {
9040  PT_ERRORc (parser, table_name, er_msg ());
9041  }
9042  return;
9043  }
9044  else if (!is_class)
9045  {
9046  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, table_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A,
9047  table_name->info.name.original, pt_show_misc_type (PT_CLASS));
9048  }
9049 
9050  object_printer obj_print (strbuf);
9051  obj_print.describe_class (class_op);
9052 
9053  if (strbuf.len () == 0)
9054  {
9055  int error = er_errid ();
9056 
9057  assert (error != NO_ERROR);
9058 
9059  if (error == ER_AU_SELECT_FAILURE)
9060  {
9061  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, table_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_IS_NOT_AUTHORIZED_ON, "select",
9062  db_get_class_name (class_op));
9063  }
9064  else
9065  {
9066  PT_ERRORc (parser, table_name, er_msg ());
9067  }
9068  }
9069 }
9070 
9071 /*
9072  * pt_make_query_show_create_table() builds the query used for SHOW CREATE
9073  * TABLE
9074  *
9075  * SELECT 'table_name' as TABLE, 'create table ...' as CREATE TABLE
9076  * FROM db_root
9077  *
9078  * return string of create table.
9079  * parser(in) : Parser context
9080  * table_name(in): table name node
9081  */
9082 PT_NODE *
9083 pt_make_query_show_create_table (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * table_name)
9084 {
9085  PT_NODE *select;
9086 
9087  assert (table_name != NULL);
9088  assert (table_name->node_type == PT_NAME);
9089 
9090  /* *INDENT-OFF* */
9091  string_buffer strbuf {
9092  [&parser] (mem::block &block, size_t len)
9093  {
9094  size_t dim = block.dim ? block.dim : 1;
9095 
9096  for (; dim < block.dim + len; dim *= 2) // calc next power of 2 >= b.dim+len
9097  ;
9098 
9099  mem::block b{ dim, (char *) parser_alloc (parser, dim) };
9100  memcpy (b.ptr, block.ptr, block.dim); // copy old content
9101  block = std::move (b);
9102  },
9103  [](mem::block &block) //no need to deallocate for parser_context
9104  {
9105  }
9106  };
9107  /* *INDENT-ON* */
9108 
9109  pt_help_show_create_table (parser, table_name, strbuf);
9110  if (strbuf.len () == 0)
9111  {
9112  return NULL;
9113  }
9114 
9115  select = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
9116  if (select == NULL)
9117  {
9118  return NULL;
9119  }
9120 
9121  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (select, PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY);
9122 
9123  /*
9124  * SELECT 'table_name' as TABLE, 'create table ...' as CREATE TABLE
9125  * FROM db_root
9126  */
9127  pt_add_string_col_to_sel_list (parser, select, table_name->info.name.original, "TABLE");
9128  pt_add_string_col_to_sel_list (parser, select, strbuf.get_buffer (), "CREATE TABLE");
9129  pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, select, "db_root", NULL, DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9130  return select;
9131 }
9132 
9133 /*
9134  * pt_make_query_show_create_view() - builds the query used for SHOW CREATE
9135  * VIEW
9136  *
9137  * SELECT * FROM
9138  * (SELECT IF( VC.vclass_name = '',
9139  * (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <view_name> LIMIT 1),
9140  * VC.vclass_name )
9141  * AS View_,
9142  * IF( VC.comment IS NULL or VC.comment = '',
9143  * VC.vclass_def,
9144  * VC.vclass_def + ' COMMENT=''' + VC.comment + '''' )
9145  * AS Create_View
9146  * FROM db_vclass VC
9147  * WHERE VC.vclass_name=<view_name>)
9148  * show_create_view;
9149  *
9150  * Note : The first column in query (name of view = VC.vclass_name) is wrapped
9151  * with IF, in order to accomodate a dummy query, which has the role to
9152  * trigger the apropiate error if the view doesn't exist or the user
9153  * doesn't have the privilege to SELECT it; the condition in IF
9154  * expression (VC.vclass_name = '') is supposed to always evaluate to
9155  * false (class name cannot be empty), in order for the query to always
9156  * print what it is supposed to (view name); second purpose of the
9157  * condition is to avoid optimisation (otherwise the IF will evalute to
9158  * <VC.vclass_name>)
9159  *
9160  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
9161  * parser(in): Parser context
9162  * view_identifier(in): node identifier for view
9163  */
9164 PT_NODE *
9165 pt_make_query_show_create_view (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * view_identifier)
9166 {
9167  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
9168  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
9169  char lower_view_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
9170 
9171  assert (view_identifier != NULL);
9172  assert (view_identifier->node_type == PT_NAME);
9173 
9174  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
9175  if (node == NULL)
9176  {
9177  return NULL;
9178  }
9179 
9180  intl_identifier_lower (view_identifier->info.name.original, lower_view_name);
9181 
9182  /* ------ SELECT list ------- */
9183  {
9184  /* View name : IF( VC.vclass_name = '', (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <view_name> LIMIT 1), VC.vclass_name ) AS View */
9185  PT_NODE *if_true_node = NULL;
9186  PT_NODE *if_false_node = NULL;
9187  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
9188  PT_NODE *view_field = NULL;
9189 
9190  if_true_node = pt_make_dummy_query_check_table (parser, lower_view_name);
9191  if_false_node = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "VC.vclass_name");
9192  pred = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "VC.vclass_name", "");
9193 
9194  view_field = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, if_true_node, if_false_node, "View");
9195  node->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (view_field, node->info.query.q.select.list);
9196  }
9197 
9198  {
9199  /* Create View: IF( VC.comment IS NULL or VC.comment = '', VC.vclass_def, VC.vclass_def + ' COMMENT=''' +
9200  * VC.comment + '''' ) AS Create_View */
9201  PT_NODE *if_true_node = NULL;
9202  PT_NODE *if_false_node = NULL;
9203  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
9204  PT_NODE *comment_node = NULL;
9205  PT_NODE *create_view_field = NULL;
9206  PT_NODE *lhs = NULL, *rhs = NULL;
9207 
9208  if_true_node = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "VC.vclass_def");
9209 
9210  lhs = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_CONCAT, "VC.vclass_def", " comment='");
9211  rhs = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_CONCAT, "VC.comment", "'");
9212  if_false_node = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_CONCAT, lhs, rhs, NULL);
9213 
9214  comment_node = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "VC.comment");
9215  lhs = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_IS_NULL, comment_node, NULL, NULL);
9216  rhs = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "VC.comment", "");
9217  pred = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, lhs, rhs, NULL);
9218 
9219  create_view_field = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, if_true_node, if_false_node, "Create View");
9220 
9221  node->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (create_view_field, node->info.query.q.select.list);
9222  }
9223 
9224  /* ------ SELECT ... FROM ------- */
9225  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, node, "db_vclass", "VC", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9226 
9227  /* ------ SELECT ... WHERE ------- */
9228  {
9229  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
9230  where_item = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "VC.vclass_name", lower_view_name);
9231 
9232  /* WHERE list should be empty */
9233  assert (node->info.query.q.select.where == NULL);
9234  node->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, node->info.query.q.select.where);
9235  }
9236 
9237  return node;
9238 }
9239 
9240 PT_NODE *
9241 pt_make_query_show_exec_stats (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
9242 {
9243  PT_NODE **node = NULL;
9244  PT_NODE *show_node;
9245  const char *query =
9246  "(SELECT 'data_page_fetches' as [variable] , exec_stats('Num_data_page_fetches') as [value])"
9247  "UNION ALL (SELECT 'data_page_dirties' as [variable] , exec_stats('Num_data_page_dirties') as [value])"

9356 /*
9357  * pt_make_query_user_groups() - builds the query to return the SET of DB
9358  * groups to which a DB user belongs to.
9359  *
9360  * SELECT SUM(SET{t.g.name})
9361  * FROM db_user U, TABLE(groups) AS t(g)
9362  * WHERE U.name=<user_name>
9363  *
9364  *
9365  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
9366  * parser(in): Parser context
9367  * user_name(in): DB user name
9368  */
9369 static PT_NODE *
9370 pt_make_query_user_groups (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *user_name)
9371 {
9372  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
9373  PT_NODE *sel_item = NULL;
9374  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
9375 
9376  assert (user_name != NULL);
9377 
9378  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
9379  if (query == NULL)
9380  {
9381  return NULL;
9382  }
9383 
9384  /* SELECT list : */
9385  /* SUM(SET{t.g.name}) */
9386  {
9387  PT_NODE *group_name_identifier = NULL;
9388  PT_NODE *set_of_group_name = NULL;
9389 
9390  group_name_identifier = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "t.g.name");
9391  set_of_group_name = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
9392  if (set_of_group_name == NULL)
9393  {
9394  return NULL;
9395  }
9396  set_of_group_name->info.value.data_value.set = group_name_identifier;
9397  set_of_group_name->type_enum = PT_TYPE_SET;
9398 
9399  sel_item = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
9400  if (sel_item == NULL)
9401  {
9402  return NULL;
9403  }
9404 
9405  sel_item->info.function.function_type = PT_SUM;
9406  sel_item->info.function.all_or_distinct = PT_ALL;
9407  sel_item->info.function.arg_list = parser_append_node (set_of_group_name, sel_item->info.function.arg_list);
9408  }
9409  query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (sel_item, query->info.query.q.select.list);
9410 
9411  /* FROM : */
9412  /* db_user U */
9413  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, "db_user", "U", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9414 
9415 
9416  {
9417  /* TABLE(groups) AS t(g) */
9418  PT_NODE *table_col = NULL;
9419  PT_NODE *alias_table = NULL;
9420  PT_NODE *alias_col = NULL;
9421 
9422  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, NULL, NULL, DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9423 
9424  if (from_item == NULL)
9425  {
9426  return NULL;
9427  }
9428  table_col = pt_name (parser, "groups");
9429  alias_table = pt_name (parser, "t");
9430  alias_col = pt_name (parser, "g");
9431  if (table_col == NULL || alias_table == NULL || alias_col == NULL)
9432  {
9433  return NULL;
9434  }
9435  table_col->info.name.meta_class = PT_NORMAL;
9436 
9437  from_item->info.spec.derived_table = table_col;
9438  from_item->info.spec.meta_class = PT_MISC_NONE;
9439  from_item->info.spec.range_var = alias_table;
9440  from_item->info.spec.as_attr_list = alias_col;
9441  from_item->info.spec.derived_table_type = PT_IS_SET_EXPR;
9442  from_item->info.spec.join_type = PT_JOIN_NONE;
9443  }
9444  /* WHERE : */
9445  {
9446  /* U.name = <user_name> */
9447  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
9448 
9449  where_item = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "U.name", user_name);
9450  /* WHERE list should be empty */
9451  assert (query->info.query.q.select.where == NULL);
9452  query->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, query->info.query.q.select.where);
9453  }
9454 
9455  return query;
9456 }
