9458 /*
9459  * pt_make_query_show_grants_curr_usr() - builds the query used for
9460  * SHOW GRANTS for current user
9461  *
9462  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
9463  * parser(in): Parser context
9464  */
9465 PT_NODE *
9466 pt_make_query_show_grants_curr_usr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser)
9467 {
9468  const char *user_name = NULL;
9469  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
9470 
9471  user_name = au_user_name ();
9472  if (user_name == NULL)
9473  {
9474  return NULL;
9475  }
9476 
9477  node = pt_make_query_show_grants (parser, user_name);
9478 
9479  if (user_name != NULL)
9480  {
9481  db_string_free ((char *) user_name);
9482  }
9483  return node;
9484 }
9485 
9486 /*
9487  * pt_make_query_show_grants() - builds the query used for SHOW GRANTS for a
9488  * given user
9489  *
9490  * SELECT CONCAT ( 'GRANT ',
9491  * GROUP_CONCAT(AU.auth_type ORDER BY 1 SEPARATOR ', '),
9492  * ' ON ' ,
9493  * AU.class_of.class_name,
9494  * ' TO ',
9495  * AU.grantee.name ,
9496  * IF (AU.is_grantable=1,
9497  * ' WITH GRANT OPTION',
9498  * '')
9499  * ) AS GRANTS
9500  * FROM db_class C, _db_auth AU
9501  * WHERE AU.class_of.class_name = C.class_name AND
9502  * C.is_system_class='NO' AND
9503  * ( AU.grantee.name=<user_name> OR
9504  * SET{ AU.grantee.name} SUBSETEQ (
9505  * SELECT SUM(SET{t.g.name})
9506  * FROM db_user U, TABLE(groups) AS t(g)
9507  * WHERE U.name=<user_name>)
9508  * )
9509  * GROUP BY AU.grantee, AU.class_of, AU.is_grantable
9510  * ORDER BY 1;
9511  *
9512  * Note : The purpose of GROUP BY is to group all the privilege by user,
9513  * table and the presence of 'WITH GRANT OPTION' flag. We output the
9514  * privileges for the user but also for all groups to which the user
9515  * belongs to : these privileges are shown in separate lines. Multiple
9516  * privileges for the same table are displayed on the same line,
9517  * except when 'WITH GRANT OPTION' is present, case when these
9518  * privileges are displayed on another line.
9519  *
9520  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
9521  * parser(in): Parser context
9522  * user_name(in): DB user name
9523  */
9524 PT_NODE *
9525 pt_make_query_show_grants (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *original_user_name)
9526 {
9527  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
9528  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
9529  PT_NODE *where_expr = NULL;
9530  PT_NODE *concat_node = NULL;
9531  PT_NODE *group_by_item = NULL;
9532  char user_name[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
9533 
9534  assert (original_user_name != NULL);
9535  assert (strlen (original_user_name) < SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH);
9536 
9537  /* conversion to uppercase can cause <original_user_name> to double size, if internationalization is used : size
9538  * <user_name> accordingly */
9539  intl_identifier_upper (original_user_name, user_name);
9540 
9541  node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
9542  if (node == NULL)
9543  {
9544  return NULL;
9545  }
9546 
9547  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY);
9548 
9549  /* ------ SELECT list ------- */
9550  /*
9551  * CONCAT ( 'GRANT ',
9552  * GROUP_CONCAT(AU.auth_type ORDER BY 1 SEPARATOR ', '),
9553  * ' ON ' ,
9554  * AU.class_of.class_name,
9555  * ' TO ',
9556  * AU.grantee.name ,
9557  * IF (AU.is_grantable=1,
9558  * ' WITH GRANT OPTION',
9559  * '')
9560  * ) AS GRANTS
9561  */
9562  {
9563  PT_NODE *concat_arg_list = NULL;
9564  PT_NODE *concat_arg = NULL;
9565 
9566  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, "GRANT ");
9567  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9568 
9569  {
9570  /* GROUP_CONCAT(AU.auth_type ORDER BY 1 SEPARATOR ', ') */
9571  PT_NODE *group_concat_field = NULL;
9572  PT_NODE *group_concat_sep = NULL;
9573  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
9574 
9575  concat_arg = parser_new_node (parser, PT_FUNCTION);
9576  if (concat_arg == NULL)
9577  {
9578  return NULL;
9579  }
9580 
9581  concat_arg->info.function.function_type = PT_GROUP_CONCAT;
9582  concat_arg->info.function.all_or_distinct = PT_ALL;
9583 
9584  group_concat_field = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "AU.auth_type");
9585  group_concat_sep = pt_make_string_value (parser, ", ");
9586  concat_arg->info.function.arg_list = parser_append_node (group_concat_sep, group_concat_field);
9587 
9588  /* add ORDER BY */
9589  assert (concat_arg->info.function.order_by == NULL);
9590 
9591  /* By 1 */
9592  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 1, PT_ASC);
9593  concat_arg->info.function.order_by = order_by_item;
9594  }
9595  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9596 
9597  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, " ON ");
9598  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9599 
9600  concat_arg = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "AU.class_of.class_name");
9601  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9602 
9603  concat_arg = pt_make_string_value (parser, " TO ");
9604  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9605 
9606  concat_arg = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "AU.grantee.name");
9607  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9608 
9609  /* IF (AU.is_grantable=1, ' WITH GRANT OPTION','') */
9610  {
9611  PT_NODE *pred_for_if = NULL;
9612 
9613  pred_for_if = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "AU.is_grantable", 1);
9614  concat_arg = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred_for_if, " WITH GRANT OPTION", "", NULL);
9615  }
9616  concat_arg_list = parser_append_node (concat_arg, concat_arg_list);
9617 
9618  concat_node = parser_keyword_func ("concat", concat_arg_list);
9619  if (concat_node == NULL)
9620  {
9621  return NULL;
9622  }
9623 
9624  {
9625  char col_alias[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH] = { 0 };
9626  const char *const col_header = "Grants for ";
9627 
9628  strcpy (col_alias, col_header);
9629  strncat (col_alias, user_name, SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH - strlen (col_header) - 1);
9630  col_alias[SM_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH - 1] = '\0';
9631  concat_node->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, col_alias);
9632  }
9633  }
9634  node->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (concat_node, node->info.query.q.select.list);
9635 
9636  /* ------ SELECT ... FROM ------- */
9637  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, node, "db_class", "C", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9638 
9639  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, node, "_db_auth", "AU", DB_AUTH_SELECT);
9640 
9641  /* ------ SELECT ... WHERE ------- */
9642  /*
9643  * WHERE AU.class_of.class_name = C.class_name AND
9644  * C.is_system_class='NO' AND
9645  * ( AU.grantee.name=<user_name> OR
9646  * SET{ AU.grantee.name} SUBSETEQ ( <query_user_groups> )
9647  * )
9648  */
9649  {
9650  /* AU.class_of.class_name = C.class_name */
9651  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
9652 
9653  where_item = pt_make_pred_with_identifiers (parser, PT_EQ, "AU.class_of.class_name", "C.class_name");
9654  where_expr = where_item;
9655  }
9656  {
9657  /* C.is_system_class = 'NO' */
9658  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
9659 
9660  where_item = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "C.is_system_class", "NO");
9661  /* <where_expr> = <where_expr> AND <where_item> */
9662  where_expr = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_expr, where_item, NULL);
9663  }
9664  {
9665  PT_NODE *user_cond = NULL;
9666  PT_NODE *group_cond = NULL;
9667  /* AU.grantee.name = <user_name> */
9668  user_cond = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "AU.grantee.name", user_name);
9669 
9670  /* SET{ AU.grantee.name} SUBSETEQ ( <query_user_groups> */
9671  {
9672  /* query to get a SET of user's groups */
9673  PT_NODE *query_user_groups = NULL;
9674  PT_NODE *set_of_grantee_name = NULL;
9675 
9676  {
9677  /* SET{ AU.grantee.name} */
9678  PT_NODE *grantee_name_identifier = NULL;
9679 
9680  grantee_name_identifier = pt_make_dotted_identifier (parser, "AU.grantee.name");
9681  set_of_grantee_name = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
9682  if (set_of_grantee_name == NULL)
9683  {
9684  return NULL;
9685  }
9686  set_of_grantee_name->info.value.data_value.set = grantee_name_identifier;
9687  set_of_grantee_name->type_enum = PT_TYPE_SET;
9688  }
9689 
9690  query_user_groups = pt_make_query_user_groups (parser, user_name);
9691 
9692  group_cond = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_SUBSETEQ, set_of_grantee_name, query_user_groups, NULL);
9693  }
9694  user_cond = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_OR, user_cond, group_cond, NULL);
9695 
9696  where_expr = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_AND, where_expr, user_cond, NULL);
9697  }
9698 
9699 
9700 
9701  /* WHERE list should be empty */
9702  assert (node->info.query.q.select.where == NULL);
9703  node->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_expr, node->info.query.q.select.where);
9704 
9705  /* GROUP BY : AU.grantee, AU.class_of, AU.is_grantable */
9706  assert (node->info.query.q.select.group_by == NULL);
9707  group_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "AU.grantee", PT_ASC);
9708  node->info.query.q.select.group_by = parser_append_node (group_by_item, node->info.query.q.select.group_by);
9709 
9710  group_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "AU.class_of", PT_ASC);
9711  node->info.query.q.select.group_by = parser_append_node (group_by_item, node->info.query.q.select.group_by);
9712 
9713  group_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_identifier (parser, "AU.is_grantable", PT_ASC);
9714  node->info.query.q.select.group_by = parser_append_node (group_by_item, node->info.query.q.select.group_by);
9715  group_by_item = NULL;
9716 
9717  {
9718  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
9719 
9720  assert (node->info.query.order_by == NULL);
9721 
9722  /* By GROUPS */
9723  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 1, PT_ASC);
9724  node->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, node->info.query.order_by);
9725  }
9726  return node;
9727 }
9728 
9729 /*
9730  * pt_is_spec_referenced() - check if the current node references the spec id
9731  * passed as parameter
9732  * return: the current node
9733  * parser(in): Parser context
9734  * node(in):
9735  * void_arg(in): must contain an address to the id of the spec. If the spec id
9736  * is referenced then reference of this parameter is modified to
9737  * 0.
9738  * continue_walk(in):
9739  *
9740  */
9741 static PT_NODE *
9742 pt_is_spec_referenced (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *void_arg, int *continue_walk)
9743 {
9744  UINTPTR spec_id = *(UINTPTR *) void_arg;
9745 
9746  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
9747 
9748  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME && node->info.name.spec_id == spec_id && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_METHOD
9749  && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_INDEX_NAME)
9750  {
9751  *(UINTPTR *) void_arg = 0;
9752  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
9753  return node;
9754  }
9755 
9756  if (node->node_type == PT_SPEC)
9757  {
9758  /* The only part of a spec node that could contain references to the given spec_id are derived tables,
9759  * path_entities, path_conjuncts, and on_cond. All the rest of the name nodes for the spec are not references,
9760  * but range variables, class names, etc. We don't want to mess with these. We'll handle the ones that we want by
9761  * hand. */
9762  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.derived_table, pt_is_spec_referenced, void_arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
9763  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.path_entities, pt_is_spec_referenced, void_arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
9764  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.path_conjuncts, pt_is_spec_referenced, void_arg, pt_continue_walk,
9765  NULL);
9766  parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.spec.on_cond, pt_is_spec_referenced, void_arg, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
9767  /* don't visit any other leaf nodes */
9768  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9769  return node;
9770  }
9771 
9772  /* Data type nodes can not contain any valid references. They do contain class names and other things we don't want.
9773  */
9774  if (node->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE)
9775  {
9776  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9777  }
9778 
9779  return node;
9780 }
9781 
9782 /*
9783  * pt_create_delete_stmt() - create a new simple delete statement
9784  * return: the PT_DELETE node on success or NULL otherwise
9785  * parser(in/out): Parser context
9786  * spec(in): the spec for which the DELETE statement is created
9787  * target_class(in): the PT_NAME node that will appear in the target_classes
9788  * list.
9789  *
9790  * Note: The 'spec' and 'target_class' parameters are assigned to the new
9791  * statement.
9792  */
9793 static PT_NODE *
9794 pt_create_delete_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * target_class)
9795 {
9796  PT_NODE *delete_stmt = NULL;
9797 
9798  assert (spec != NULL && spec->node_type == PT_SPEC);
9799 
9800  delete_stmt = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DELETE);
9801  if (delete_stmt == NULL)
9802  {
9803  PT_ERRORm (parser, spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
9804  return NULL;
9805  }
9806 
9807  delete_stmt->info.delete_.spec = spec;
9808  delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes = target_class;
9809 
9810  return delete_stmt;
9811 }
9812 
9813 /*
9814  * pt_split_delete_stmt() - split DELETE statement into independent DELETE
9815  * statements
9816  * return: NO_ERROR or error code;
9817  * parser(in/out): Parser context
9818  * delete_stmt(in): the source DELETE statement
9819  *
9820  * Note: The function checks each spec if it is referenced. If the spec was
9821  * specified in the target_classes list (for deletion) and is not
9822  * referenced then it removes it from the current statement and a new
9823  * DELETE statement is generated only for this spec. The newly generated
9824  * statements are stored in del_stmt_list member of the current
9825  * PT_DELETE_INFO node.
9826  */
9827 int
9828 pt_split_delete_stmt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * delete_stmt)
9829 {
9830  PT_NODE *spec = NULL, *prev_spec = NULL, *rem_spec = NULL, *to_delete = NULL;
9831  PT_NODE *prev_name = NULL, *new_del_stmts = NULL, *last_new_del_stmt = NULL;
9832  PT_NODE *rem_name = NULL;
9833  UINTPTR spec_id = 0;
9834 
9835  if (delete_stmt == NULL || delete_stmt->node_type != PT_DELETE)
9836  {
9837  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Invalid argument");
9838  return ER_FAILED;
9839  }
9840 
9841  /* if we have hints that refers globally to the join statement then we skip the split */
9842  if ((delete_stmt->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_ORDERED && delete_stmt->info.delete_.ordered_hint == NULL)
9843  || ((delete_stmt->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_USE_NL) && delete_stmt->info.delete_.use_nl_hint == NULL)
9844  || ((delete_stmt->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_USE_IDX) && delete_stmt->info.delete_.use_idx_hint == NULL)
9845  || ((delete_stmt->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_USE_MERGE) && delete_stmt->info.delete_.use_merge_hint == NULL))
9846  {
9847  return NO_ERROR;
9848  }
9849 
9850  spec = delete_stmt->info.delete_.spec;
9851  /* if the delete statement has only one spec then we do not split anything */
9852  if (spec->next == NULL)
9853  {
9854  return NO_ERROR;
9855  }
9856 
9857  /* iterate through specs and put in separate delete statements the specs that aren't referenced */
9858  while (spec != NULL && delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes->next != NULL)
9859  {
9860  /* skip the derived tables and tables that will not be deleted */
9861  if (spec->info.spec.derived_table != NULL || !(spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE))
9862  {
9863  prev_spec = spec;
9864  spec = spec->next;
9865  continue;
9866  }
9867 
9868  spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
9869  to_delete = delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes;
9870  /* remove temporarily all target_classes from statement because these references must not be counted, then check
9871  * if the current spec is referenced */
9872  delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes = NULL;
9873  parser_walk_tree (parser, delete_stmt, pt_is_spec_referenced, &spec_id, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
9874  delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes = to_delete;
9875 
9876  /* if the spec is not referenced and if it is not the only remaining spec from the original command that will be
9877  * deleted then remove it */
9878  if (spec_id)
9879  {
9880  /* move the iterator (spec) to the next spec and remove the current spec from the original list of specs */
9881  rem_spec = spec;
9882  spec = spec->next;
9883  rem_spec->next = NULL;
9884  if (prev_spec != NULL)
9885  {
9886  prev_spec->next = spec;
9887  }
9888  else
9889  {
9890  delete_stmt->info.delete_.spec = spec;
9891  }
9892 
9893  /* remove PT_NAMEs from target_classes list */
9894  rem_name = prev_name = NULL;
9895  while (to_delete != NULL)
9896  {
9897  /* if the target class name references the removed spec then remove it from target_classes list */
9898  if (to_delete->info.name.spec_id == spec_id)
9899  {
9900  /* free the previous removed PT_NAME */
9901  if (rem_name != NULL)
9902  {
9903  parser_free_tree (parser, rem_name);
9904  }
9905  /* remove the current PT_NAME from target_classes and keep it for a new DELETE statement */
9906  rem_name = to_delete;
9907  to_delete = to_delete->next;
9908  rem_name->next = NULL;
9909  if (prev_name != NULL)
9910  {
9911  prev_name->next = to_delete;
9912  }
9913  else
9914  {
9915  delete_stmt->info.delete_.target_classes = to_delete;
9916  }
9917  }
9918  else
9919  {
9920  prev_name = to_delete;
9921  to_delete = to_delete->next;
9922  }
9923  }
9924 
9925  /* because the spec is referenced in the target_classes list, we need to generate a new DELETE statement */
9926  if (new_del_stmts == NULL)
9927  {
9928  last_new_del_stmt = new_del_stmts = pt_create_delete_stmt (parser, rem_spec, rem_name);
9929  }
9930  else
9931  {
9932  last_new_del_stmt->next = pt_create_delete_stmt (parser, rem_spec, rem_name);
9933  last_new_del_stmt = last_new_del_stmt->next;
9934  }
9935 
9936  if (last_new_del_stmt == NULL)
9937  {
9938  goto exit_on_error;
9939  }
9940 
9941  /* handle hints */
9942  if (last_new_del_stmt != NULL)
9943  {
9944  last_new_del_stmt->info.delete_.hint = delete_stmt->info.delete_.hint;
9945  last_new_del_stmt->recompile = delete_stmt->recompile;
9946  if ((last_new_del_stmt->info.delete_.hint & PT_HINT_LK_TIMEOUT)
9947  && delete_stmt->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint != NULL)
9948  {
9949  last_new_del_stmt->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint =
9950  parser_copy_tree (parser, delete_stmt->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint);
9951  if (last_new_del_stmt->info.delete_.waitsecs_hint == NULL)
9952  {
9953  goto exit_on_error;
9954  }
9955  }
9956  }
9957  }
9958  else
9959  {
9960  prev_spec = spec;
9961  spec = spec->next;
9962  }
9963  }
9964 
9965  delete_stmt->info.delete_.del_stmt_list = new_del_stmts;
9966 
9967  return NO_ERROR;
9968 
9969 exit_on_error:
9970  if (new_del_stmts != NULL)
9971  {
9972  parser_free_tree (parser, new_del_stmts);
9973  }
9974 
9975  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
9976  {
9977  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
9978  }
9979 
9980  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
9981 }
9982 
9983 /*
9984  * pt_make_query_describe_w_identifier() - builds the query used for DESCRIBE
9985  * with a column name
9986  *
9987  * DESCRIBE <table_name> <column_name>
9988  *
9989  * return: newly build node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
9990  * parser(in): Parser context
9991  * original_cls_id(in): node identifier for table (PT_NAME)
9992  * att_id(in): node identifier for attribute (PT_NAME)
9993  */
9994 PT_NODE *
9995 pt_make_query_describe_w_identifier (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * original_cls_id, PT_NODE * att_id)
9996 {
9997  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
9998  PT_NODE *where_node = NULL;
9999 
10000  assert (original_cls_id != NULL);
10001  assert (original_cls_id->node_type == PT_NAME);
10002  assert (att_id != NULL);
10003 
10004  if (att_id != NULL)
10005  {
10006  assert (att_id->node_type == PT_NAME);
10007  if (att_id->node_type == PT_NAME)
10008  {
10009  char lower_att_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
10010  /* build WHERE */
10011  intl_identifier_lower (att_id->info.name.original, lower_att_name);
10012  where_node = pt_make_pred_name_string_val (parser, PT_EQ, "Field", lower_att_name);
10013  }
10014  }
10015 
10016  node = pt_make_query_show_columns (parser, original_cls_id, (where_node == NULL) ? 0 : 2, where_node, 0);
10017 
10018  return node;
10019 }
10020 
10021 /*
10022  * pt_make_query_show_index() - builds the query used for
10023  * SHOW INDEX IN <table>
10024  *
10025  * return: newly built node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
10026  * parser(in): Parser context
10027  * original_cls_id(in): node (PT_NAME) containing name of class
10028  *
10029  * SELECT "" AS Table,
10030  * 0 AS Non_unique,
10031  * "" AS Key_name,
10032  * 0 AS Seq_in_index,
10033  * "" AS Column_name,
10034  * "" AS Collation,
10035  * 0 AS Cardinality,
10036  * 0 AS Sub_part,
10037  * NULL AS Packed,
10038  * "" AS [Null],
10039  * 'BTREE' AS Index_type
10040  * "" AS Func,
10041  * "" AS Comment,
10042  * "" AS Visible
10043  * FROM <table> ORDER BY 3, 5;
10044  *
10045  * Note: At execution, all empty fields will be replaced by values
10046  * that will be read from class schema
10047  */
10048 PT_NODE *
10049 pt_make_query_show_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * original_cls_id)
10050 {
10051  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
10052  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
10053  PT_NODE *query = NULL;
10054  char lower_table_name[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH];
10055  PT_NODE *value = NULL, *value_list = NULL;
10056  DB_VALUE db_valuep[14];
10057  const char *aliases[] = {
10058  "Table", "Non_unique", "Key_name", "Seq_in_index", "Column_name",
10059  "Collation", "Cardinality", "Sub_part", "Packed", "Null", "Index_type",
10060  "Func", "Comment", "Visible"
10061  };
10062  unsigned int i = 0;
10063 
10064  assert (original_cls_id != NULL);
10065  assert (original_cls_id->node_type == PT_NAME);
10066 
10067  query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
10068  if (query == NULL)
10069  {
10070  return NULL;
10071  }
10072 
10073  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (query, PT_SELECT_INFO_IDX_SCHEMA);
10074  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (query, PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY);
10075 
10076  intl_identifier_lower (original_cls_id->info.name.original, lower_table_name);
10077 
10078  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 0, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10079  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10080  db_make_int (db_valuep + 1, 0);
10081  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 2, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10082  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10083  db_make_int (db_valuep + 3, 0);
10084  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 4, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10085  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10086  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 5, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10087  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10088  db_make_int (db_valuep + 6, 0);
10089  db_make_int (db_valuep + 7, 0);
10090  db_make_null (db_valuep + 8);
10091  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 9, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10092  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10093  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 10, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10094  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10095  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 11, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10096  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10097  db_make_varchar (db_valuep + 12, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, (const DB_C_CHAR) "", 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET, LANG_SYS_COLLATION);
10098  db_value_domain_default (db_valuep + 13, DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, 0, LANG_SYS_CODESET,
10099  LANG_SYS_COLLATION, NULL);
10100 
10101  for (i = 0; i < sizeof (db_valuep) / sizeof (db_valuep[0]); i++)
10102  {
10103  value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, db_valuep + i);
10104  if (value == NULL)
10105  {
10106  goto error;
10107  }
10108  value->alias_print = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, aliases[i]);
10109  value_list = parser_append_node (value, value_list);
10110  }
10111 
10112  query->info.query.q.select.list = value_list;
10113  value_list = NULL;
10114 
10115  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, query, lower_table_name, NULL, DB_AUTH_NONE);
10116  if (from_item == NULL)
10117  {
10118  goto error;
10119  }
10120 
10121  /* By Key_name */
10122  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 3, PT_ASC);
10123  if (order_by_item == NULL)
10124  {
10125  goto error;
10126  }
10127  query->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, query->info.query.order_by);
10128 
10129  /* By Seq_in_index */
10130  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 4, PT_ASC);
10131  if (order_by_item == NULL)
10132  {
10133  goto error;
10134  }
10135  query->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, query->info.query.order_by);
10136 
10137  return query;
10138 
10139 error:
10140  if (query)
10141  {
10142  parser_free_tree (parser, query);
10143  }
10144 
10145  if (value_list)
10146  {
10147  parser_free_tree (parser, value_list);
10148  }
10149 
10150  return NULL;
10151 }
10152 
10153 /*
10154  * pt_convert_to_logical_expr () - if necessary, creates a logically correct
10155  * expression from the given node
10156  *
10157  * return: - the same node if conversion was not necessary, OR
10158  * - a new PT_EXPR: (node <> 0), OR
10159  * - NULL on failures
10160  * parser (in): Parser context
10161  * node (in): the node to be checked and wrapped
10162  * use_parens (in): set to true if parantheses are needed around the original node
10163  *
10164  * Note: we see if the given node is of type PT_TYPE_LOGICAL, and if not,
10165  * we create an expression of the form "(node <> 0)" - with parens
10166  */
10167 PT_NODE *
10168 pt_convert_to_logical_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, bool use_parens_inside, bool use_parens_outside)
10169 {
10170  PT_NODE *expr = NULL;
10171  PT_NODE *zero = NULL;
10172 
10173  (void) use_parens_inside;
10174  (void) use_parens_outside;
10175 
10176  /* If there's nothing to be done, go away */
10177  if (node == NULL || node->type_enum == PT_TYPE_LOGICAL)
10178  {
10179  return node;
10180  }
10181 
10182  /* allocate a new node for the zero value */
10183  zero = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
10184  if (NULL == zero)
10185  {
10186  return NULL;
10187  }
10188 
10189  zero->info.value.data_value.i = 0;
10190  zero->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
10191 
10192  /* make a new expression comparing the node to zero */
10193  expr = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_NE, node, zero, NULL);
10194  if (expr != NULL)
10195  {
10196  expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
10197  }
10198 
10199  return expr;
10200 }
10201 
10202 /*
10203  * pt_is_operator_logical() - returns TRUE if the operator has a logical
10204  * return type (i.e. <, >, AND etc.) and FALSE
10205  * otherwise.
10206  *
10207  * return: boolean
10208  * op(in): the operator
10209  */
10210 bool
10211 pt_is_operator_logical (PT_OP_TYPE op)
10212 {
10213  switch (op)
10214  {
10215  case PT_OR:
10216  case PT_XOR:
10217  case PT_AND:
10218  case PT_IS_NOT:
10219  case PT_IS:
10220  case PT_NOT:
10221  case PT_EXISTS:
10222  case PT_LIKE_ESCAPE:
10223  case PT_LIKE:
10224  case PT_NOT_LIKE:
10225  case PT_RLIKE:
10226  case PT_NOT_RLIKE:
10227  case PT_RLIKE_BINARY:
10228  case PT_NOT_RLIKE_BINARY:
10229  case PT_EQ:
10230  case PT_EQ_ALL:
10231  case PT_EQ_SOME:
10232  case PT_NE:
10233  case PT_NE_ALL:
10234  case PT_NE_SOME:
10235  case PT_GT:
10236  case PT_GT_ALL:
10237  case PT_GT_SOME:
10238  case PT_GE:
10239  case PT_GE_ALL:
10240  case PT_GE_SOME:
10241  case PT_LT:
10242  case PT_LT_ALL:
10243  case PT_LT_SOME:
10244  case PT_LE:
10245  case PT_LE_ALL:
10246  case PT_LE_SOME:
10247  case PT_NULLSAFE_EQ:
10248  case PT_IS_NOT_NULL:
10249  case PT_IS_NULL:
10250  case PT_NOT_BETWEEN:
10251  case PT_BETWEEN:
10252  case PT_IS_IN:
10253  case PT_IS_NOT_IN:
10254  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LE:
10255  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LE:
10256  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LT:
10257  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LT:
10258  case PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA:
10259  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_INF:
10260  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_INF:
10261  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LE:
10262  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LT:
10263  case PT_SETEQ:
10264  case PT_SETNEQ:
10265  case PT_SUBSET:
10266  case PT_SUBSETEQ:
10267  case PT_SUPERSETEQ:
10268  case PT_SUPERSET:
10269  case PT_RANGE:
10270  return true;
10271  default:
10272  return false;
10273  }
10274 }
10275 
10276 /*
10277  * pt_list_has_logical_nodes () - returns TRUE if the node list contains
10278  * top level PT_TYPE_LOGICAL nodes.
10279  *
10280  * return: boolean
10281  * list(in): the node list
10282  *
10283  * Note: this function is important because there are cases (such as arg lists)
10284  * when we want to forbid logical expressions, because of ambiguity over
10285  * the ->next node: is it in a list context, or a CNF context?
10286  */
10287 bool
10288 pt_list_has_logical_nodes (PT_NODE * list)
10289 {
10290  for (; list; list = list->next)
10291  {
10292  if (list->type_enum == PT_TYPE_LOGICAL)
10293  {
10294  return true;
10295  }
10296  }
10297  return false;
10298 }
10299 
10300 /*
10301  * pt_sort_spec_cover_groupby () -
10302  * return: true if group list is covered by sort list
10303  * sort_list(in):
10304  * group_list(in):
10305  */
10306 bool
10307 pt_sort_spec_cover_groupby (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * sort_list, PT_NODE * group_list, PT_NODE * tree)
10308 {
10309  PT_NODE *s1, *s2, *save_node, *col;
10310  QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_POSITION pos_descr;
10311  int i;
10312 
10313  if (group_list == NULL)
10314  {
10315  return false;
10316  }
10317 
10318  s1 = sort_list;
10319  s2 = group_list;
10320 
10321  while (s1 && s2)
10322  {
10323  pt_to_pos_descr (parser, &pos_descr, s2->info.sort_spec.expr, tree, NULL);
10324  if (pos_descr.pos_no > 0)
10325  {
10326  col = tree->info.query.q.select.list;
10327  for (i = 1; i < pos_descr.pos_no && col; i++)
10328  {
10329  col = col->next;
10330  }
10331  if (col != NULL)
10332  {
10333  col = pt_get_end_path_node (col);
10334 
10335  if (col->node_type == PT_NAME && PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (col, PT_NAME_INFO_CONSTANT))
10336  {
10337  s2 = s2->next;
10338  continue; /* skip out constant order */
10339  }
10340  }
10341  }
10342 
10343  save_node = s1->info.sort_spec.expr;
10344  CAST_POINTER_TO_NODE (s1->info.sort_spec.expr);
10345 
10346  if (!pt_name_equal (parser, s1->info.sort_spec.expr, s2->info.sort_spec.expr)
10347  || (s1->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc != s2->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc)
10348  || (s1->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last != s2->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last))
10349  {
10350  s1->info.sort_spec.expr = save_node;
10351  return false;
10352  }
10353 
10354  s1->info.sort_spec.expr = save_node;
10355 
10356  s1 = s1->next;
10357  s2 = s2->next;
10358  }
10359 
10360  return (s2 == NULL) ? true : false;
10361 }
10362 
10363 /*
10364  * pt_rewrite_derived_for_upd_del () - adds ROWOID to select list of
10365  * query so it can be later pulled
10366  * when building the SELECT
10367  * statement for UPDATEs and DELETEs
10368  * returns: rewritten subquery or NULL on error
10369  * parser(in): parser context
10370  * spec(in): spec whose derived table will be rewritten
10371  *
10372  * NOTE: query must be a SELECT statement
10373  */
10374 static PT_NODE *
10375 pt_rewrite_derived_for_upd_del (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_SPEC_FLAG what_for, bool add_as_attr)
10376 {
10377  PT_NODE *derived_table, *as_attr, *col, *upd_del_spec, *spec_list;
10378  PT_NODE *save_spec, *save_next, *flat_copy;
10379  const char *spec_name = NULL;
10380  int upd_del_count = 0;
10381 
10382  derived_table = spec->info.spec.derived_table;
10383  spec_list = derived_table->info.query.q.select.from;
10384  if ((what_for == PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE) && (spec_list == NULL || spec_list->next != NULL))
10385  {
10386  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "only one spec expected for delete");
10387  return NULL;
10388  }
10389 
10390  while (spec_list != NULL)
10391  {
10392  if (spec_list->info.spec.flag & what_for)
10393  {
10394  if (upd_del_count == 0)
10395  {
10396  upd_del_spec = spec_list;
10397  }
10398  upd_del_count++;
10399  }
10400 
10401  spec_list = spec_list->next;
10402  }
10403 
10404  if (upd_del_spec == NULL)
10405  {
10406  /* no specs; error */
10407  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "no target spec for update/delete");
10408  return NULL;
10409  }
10410 
10411  if (upd_del_count > 1)
10412  {
10413  PT_ERRORm (parser, spec_list, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ONLY_ONE_UPDATE_SPEC_ALLOWED);
10414  return NULL;
10415  }
10416 
10417  /* dual update/delete checks have been made - check if oids were already added */
10418  if (spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_CONTAINS_OID)
10419  {
10420  return spec;
10421  }
10422 
10423  /* retrieve spec's name, which will be appended to OID attribute names */
10424  if (spec->info.spec.range_var && spec->info.spec.range_var->node_type == PT_NAME)
10425  {
10426  spec_name = spec->info.spec.range_var->info.name.original;
10427  }
10428 
10429  /* add rowoid to select list of derived table and as_attr_list of spec; it will be pulled later on when building the
10430  * select statement for OID retrieval */
10431  save_spec = derived_table->info.query.q.select.from;
10432  derived_table->info.query.q.select.from = upd_del_spec;
10433  save_next = upd_del_spec->next;
10434  upd_del_spec->next = NULL;
10435 
10436  derived_table = pt_add_row_oid_name (parser, derived_table);
10437 
10438  derived_table->info.query.q.select.from = save_spec;
10439  upd_del_spec->next = save_next;
10440 
10441  col = derived_table->info.query.q.select.list;
10442  if (col->data_type && col->data_type->info.data_type.virt_object)
10443  {
10444  /* no longer comes from a vobj */
10445  col->data_type->info.data_type.virt_object = NULL;
10446  col->data_type->info.data_type.virt_type_enum = PT_TYPE_NONE;
10447  }
10448 
10449  if (add_as_attr)
10450  {
10451  /* add reference for column in select list */
10452  as_attr = pt_name (parser, "rowoid_");
10453  as_attr->info.name.original =
10454  (const char *) pt_append_string (parser, (char *) as_attr->info.name.original, spec_name);
10455  as_attr->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
10456  as_attr->info.name.meta_class = PT_OID_ATTR;
10457  as_attr->type_enum = col->type_enum;
10458  as_attr->data_type = parser_copy_tree (parser, col->data_type);
10459 
10460  as_attr->next = spec->info.spec.as_attr_list;
10461  spec->info.spec.as_attr_list = as_attr;
10462  }
10463 
10464  /* copy flat_entity_list of derived table's spec to parent spec so it will be correctly handled further on */
10465  flat_copy = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, upd_del_spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
10466  spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list = parser_append_node (flat_copy, spec->info.spec.flat_entity_list);
10467 
10468  while (flat_copy)
10469  {
10470  if (flat_copy->node_type == PT_NAME)
10471  {
10472  flat_copy->info.name.spec_id = spec->info.spec.id;
10473  }
10474  flat_copy = flat_copy->next;
10475  }
10476 
10477  /* all ok */
10478  return spec;
10479 }
10480 
10481 /*
10482  * pt_process_spec_for_delete () - recurses trough specs, sets DELETE flag
10483  * and adds OIDs where necessary
10484  * returns: same spec or NULL on error
10485  * parser(in): parser context
10486  * spec(in): spec
10487  */
10488 static PT_NODE *
10489 pt_process_spec_for_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec)
10490 {
10491  PT_NODE *derived_table, *from, *ret;
10492 
10493  if (parser == NULL || spec == NULL || spec->node_type != PT_SPEC)
10494  {
10495  /* should not get here */
10496  assert (false);
10497  return NULL;
10498  }
10499 
10500  /* mark spec */
10501  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE);
10502 
10503  /* fetch derived table of spec */
10504  derived_table = spec->info.spec.derived_table;
10505  if (derived_table == NULL)
10506  {
10507  /* no derived table means nothing to do further */
10508  return spec;
10509  }
10510 
10511  /* derived table - walk it's spec */
10512  if (derived_table->node_type != PT_SELECT)
10513  {
10514  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid derived spec");
10515  return NULL;
10516  }
10517 
10518  from = derived_table->info.query.q.select.from;
10519  if (pt_process_spec_for_delete (parser, from) == NULL)
10520  {
10521  /* error must have been set */
10522  return NULL;
10523  }
10524 
10525  /* add oids */
10526  ret = pt_rewrite_derived_for_upd_del (parser, spec, PT_SPEC_FLAG_DELETE, true);
10527  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_CONTAINS_OID);
10528 
10529  return ret;
10530 }
10531 
10532 /*
10533  * pt_process_spec_for_update () - recurses trough specs, sets UPDATE flag,
10534  * adds OIDs where necessary and resolves name
10535  * returns: resolved name or NULL on error
10536  * parser(in): parser context
10537  * spec(in): spec
10538  * name(in): lhs assignment node
10539  */
10540 static PT_NODE *
10541 pt_process_spec_for_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * name)
10542 {
10543  PT_NODE *as_attr_list = NULL, *attr_list = NULL;
10544  PT_NODE *dt_arg1, *dt_arg2, *derived_table;
10545  PT_NODE *spec_list, *subspec;
10546  PT_NODE *temp_name, *save_dt;
10547  int attr_idx, i;
10548 
10549  if (parser == NULL || spec == NULL || name == NULL || spec->node_type != PT_SPEC || name->node_type != PT_NAME)
10550  {
10551  /* should not get here */
10552  assert (false);
10553  return NULL;
10554  }
10555 
10556  /* mark spec */
10557  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE);
10558 
10559  /* fetch derived table of spec */
10560  dt_arg1 = save_dt = spec->info.spec.derived_table;
10561  if (dt_arg1 == NULL)
10562  {
10563  /* no derived table means nothing to do further */
10564  return name;
10565  }
10566 
10567  /* check derived table */
10568  if (!(spec->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_FROM_VCLASS))
10569  {
10570  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "derived table not allowed");
10571  return NULL;
10572  }
10573 
10574  if (dt_arg1->node_type == PT_UNION)
10575  {
10576  /* union derived table (e.g. UPDATE (view1, view2) SET ...) */
10577  dt_arg2 = dt_arg1->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
10578  dt_arg1 = dt_arg1->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
10579  }
10580  else
10581  {
10582  /* simple derived table */
10583  dt_arg2 = NULL;
10584  }
10585 
10586  if (dt_arg1->node_type != PT_SELECT || (dt_arg2 != NULL && dt_arg2->node_type != PT_SELECT))
10587  {
10588  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid derived spec");
10589  return NULL;
10590  }
10591 
10592  /* find name in as_attr_list */
10593  attr_idx = 0;
10594  as_attr_list = spec->info.spec.as_attr_list;
10595  while (as_attr_list != NULL)
10596  {
10597  if (pt_name_equal (parser, name, as_attr_list))
10598  {
10599  break;
10600  }
10601  as_attr_list = as_attr_list->next;
10602  attr_idx++;
10603  }
10604 
10605  if (as_attr_list == NULL)
10606  {
10607  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "name not found in as_attr_list");
10608  return NULL;
10609  }
10610 
10611  derived_table = dt_arg1;
10612  while (derived_table != NULL)
10613  {
10614  /* resolve name to real name in select list */
10615  attr_list = derived_table->info.query.q.select.list;
10616  for (i = 0; i < attr_idx && attr_list != NULL; i++)
10617  {
10618  attr_list = attr_list->next;
10619  }
10620  if (attr_list == NULL)
10621  {
10622  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "name not found in list");
10623  return NULL;
10624  }
10625 
10626  /* we have a derived table we know came from a view; resolve name further down */
10627  spec_list = derived_table->info.query.q.select.from;
10628  subspec = pt_find_spec (parser, spec_list, attr_list);
10629  if (subspec == NULL)
10630  {
10631  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "spec not found for name");
10632  return NULL;
10633  }
10634 
10635  /* don't allow other subspecs to be updated; this error will be hit when two passes of the function, called for
10636  * different assignments, will try to flag two different specs */
10637  while (spec_list != NULL)
10638  {
10639  if ((spec_list != subspec) && (spec_list->info.spec.flag & PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE))
10640  {
10641  PT_ERRORm (parser, spec_list, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ONLY_ONE_UPDATE_SPEC_ALLOWED);
10642  return NULL;
10643  }
10644 
10645  spec_list = spec_list->next;
10646  }
10647 
10648  /* recurse */
10649  temp_name = pt_process_spec_for_update (parser, subspec, attr_list);
10650  if (temp_name == NULL)
10651  {
10652  /* error should have been set lower down */
10653  return NULL;
10654  }
10655  if (derived_table == dt_arg1)
10656  {
10657  /* skip second resolved name */
10658  name = temp_name;
10659  }
10660 
10661  /* we now have the derived table subtree populated with oids; we can add oids to this derived table's select list
10662  * as well */
10663  spec->info.spec.derived_table = derived_table;
10664  spec = pt_rewrite_derived_for_upd_del (parser, spec, PT_SPEC_FLAG_UPDATE, (derived_table == dt_arg1));
10665  spec->info.spec.derived_table = save_dt;
10666 
10667  if (spec == NULL)
10668  {
10669  /* error should have been set lower down */
10670  return NULL;
10671  }
10672 
10673  /* next derived table of union */
10674  derived_table = (derived_table == dt_arg1 ? dt_arg2 : NULL);
10675  }
10676 
10677  /* spec has OIDs added */
10678  spec->info.spec.flag = (PT_SPEC_FLAG) (spec->info.spec.flag | PT_SPEC_FLAG_CONTAINS_OID);
10679 
10680  /* all ok */
10681  return name;
10682 }
10683 
10684 /*
10685  * pt_mark_spec_list_for_delete () - mark delete targets
10686  * return: none
10687  * parser(in): the parser context
10688  * delete_statement(in): a delete statement
10689  */
10690 void
10691 pt_mark_spec_list_for_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10692 {
10693  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *from;
10694 
10695  if (statement->node_type == PT_DELETE)
10696  {
10697  node = statement->info.delete_.target_classes;
10698  }
10699  else if (statement->node_type == PT_MERGE)
10700  {
10701  node = statement->info.merge.into;
10702  }
10703 
10704  while (node != NULL)
10705  {
10706  if (statement->node_type == PT_DELETE)
10707  {
10708  from = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, statement, node);
10709  if (from == NULL)
10710  {
10711  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid spec id");
10712  return;
10713  }
10714  }
10715  else
10716  {
10717  from = node;
10718  }
10719 
10720  from = pt_process_spec_for_delete (parser, from);
10721  if (from == NULL)
10722  {
10723  /* error must have been set */
10724  return;
10725  }
10726 
10727  node = node->next;
10728  }
10729 }
10730 
10731 /*
10732  * pt_mark_spec_list_for_update () - mark update targets
10733  * return: none
10734  * parser(in): the parser context
10735  * statement(in): an update/merge statement
10736  */
10737 void
10738 pt_mark_spec_list_for_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
10739 {
10740  PT_NODE *lhs, *node_tmp, *node, *resolved;
10741  PT_NODE *assignments = NULL, *spec_list = NULL;
10742 
10743  if (statement->node_type == PT_UPDATE)
10744  {
10745  assignments = statement->info.update.assignment;
10746  spec_list = statement->info.update.spec;
10747  }
10748  else if (statement->node_type == PT_MERGE)
10749  {
10750  assignments = statement->info.merge.update.assignment;
10751  spec_list = statement->info.merge.into;
10752  }
10753 
10754  /* set flags for updatable specs */
10755  node = assignments;
10756  while (node != NULL)
10757  {
10758  lhs = node->info.expr.arg1;
10759 
10760  while (lhs != NULL && lhs->node_type != PT_NAME)
10761  {
10762  if (lhs->node_type == PT_EXPR)
10763  {
10764  /* path expression */
10765  lhs = lhs->info.expr.arg1;
10766  }
10767  else if (lhs->node_type == PT_DOT_)
10768  {
10769  /* dot expression */
10770  lhs = lhs->info.dot.arg2;
10771  }
10772  else
10773  {
10774  lhs = NULL;
10775  }
10776  }
10777 
10778  if (lhs == NULL)
10779  {
10780  /* should not get here */
10781  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "malformed assignment");
10782  return;
10783  }
10784 
10785  while (lhs != NULL)
10786  {
10787  /* resolve to spec */
10788  node_tmp = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, statement, lhs);
10789  if (node_tmp == NULL)
10790  {
10791  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid spec id");
10792  return;
10793  }
10794 
10795  /* resolve name and add rowoid attributes where needed */
10796  resolved = pt_process_spec_for_update (parser, node_tmp, lhs);
10797  if (resolved == NULL || resolved->node_type != PT_NAME)
10798  {
10799  /* error should have been set */
10800  break;
10801  }
10802 
10803  /* flat_entity_list will be propagated trough derived tables of updatable views, so the assignment name
10804  * should be able to be resolved to them */
10805  lhs->info.name.original = resolved->info.name.original;
10806 
10807  /* advance to next name in set (if exists) */
10808  lhs = lhs->next;
10809  }
10810 
10811  /* next assignment */
10812  node = node->next;
10813  }
10814 }
10815 
10816 /*
10817  * pt_check_grammar_charset_collation () - validates a pair of charset and
10818  * collation nodes and return the associated identifiers
10819  * return: error status
10820  * parser(in): the parser context
10821  * charset_node(in): node containing charset string (PT_VALUE)
10822  * coll_node(in): node containing collation string (PT_VALUE)
10823  * charset(in): validated value for charset (INTL_CHARSET)
10824  * coll_id(in): validated value for collation
10825  */
10826 int
10827 pt_check_grammar_charset_collation (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * charset_node, PT_NODE * coll_node, int *charset,
10828  int *coll_id)
10829 {
10830  bool has_user_charset = false;
10831 
10832  assert (charset != NULL);
10833  assert (coll_id != NULL);
10834 
10835  *charset = LANG_SYS_CODESET;
10836  *coll_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION;
10837 
10838  if (charset_node != NULL)
10839  {
10840  const char *cs_name;
10841  assert (charset_node->node_type == PT_VALUE);
10842 
10843  assert (charset_node->info.value.data_value.str != NULL);
10844 
10845  cs_name = (char *) charset_node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes;
10846 
10847  *charset = lang_charset_cubrid_name_to_id (cs_name);
10848  if (*charset == INTL_CODESET_NONE)
10849  {
10850  PT_ERRORm (parser, charset_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_CHARSET);
10851 
10852  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10853  }
10854 
10855  has_user_charset = true;
10856  }
10857 
10858  if (coll_node != NULL)
10859  {
10860  LANG_COLLATION *lang_coll;
10861 
10862  assert (coll_node->node_type == PT_VALUE);
10863 
10864  assert (coll_node->info.value.data_value.str != NULL);
10865  lang_coll = lang_get_collation_by_name ((const char *) coll_node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes);
10866 
10867  if (lang_coll != NULL)
10868  {
10869  int coll_charset;
10870 
10871  *coll_id = lang_coll->coll.coll_id;
10872  coll_charset = (int) lang_coll->codeset;
10873 
10874  if (has_user_charset && coll_charset != *charset)
10875  {
10876  /* error incompatible charset and collation */
10877  PT_ERRORm (parser, coll_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INCOMPATIBLE_CS_COLL);
10878  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10879  }
10880 
10881  /* default charset for this collation */
10882  *charset = coll_charset;
10883  }
10884  else
10885  {
10886  PT_ERRORmf (parser, coll_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNKNOWN_COLL,
10887  coll_node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes);
10888  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
10889  }
10890  }
10891  else
10892  {
10893  assert (coll_node == NULL);
10894  /* set a default collation for a charset */
10895 
10896  switch (*charset)
10897  {
10898  case INTL_CODESET_ISO88591:
10899  *coll_id = LANG_COLL_ISO_BINARY;
10900  break;
10901  case INTL_CODESET_KSC5601_EUC:
10902  *coll_id = LANG_COLL_EUCKR_BINARY;
10903  break;
10904  case INTL_CODESET_UTF8:
10905  *coll_id = LANG_COLL_UTF8_BINARY;
10906  break;
10907  default:
10908  assert (*charset == INTL_CODESET_BINARY);
10909  *coll_id = LANG_COLL_BINARY;
10910  break;
10911  }
10912  }
10913 
10914  return NO_ERROR;
10915 }
10916 
10917 /*
10918  * pt_make_tuple_value_reference () - create a PT_TUPLE_VALUE node for a
10919  * SELECT list of a SELECT statement
10920  * return : new node or NULL
10921  * parser (in) : parser context
10922  * name (in) : name node
10923  * select_list (in) : select list of a query
10924  * cursor_p (in) : cursor for the query
10925  */
10926 PT_NODE *
10927 pt_make_tuple_value_reference (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * name, PT_NODE * select_list, CURSOR_ID * cursor_p)
10928 {
10929  int index = 0;
10930  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *new_col = NULL, *last_node = NULL, *next = NULL;
10931 
10932  assert_release (select_list != NULL);
10933 
10934  for (node = select_list, index = 0; node != NULL; node = node->next, index++)
10935  {
10936  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, node, name) == 0)
10937  {
10938  /* found it, just make a tuple_value reference to it */
10939  next = name->next;
10940  name->next = NULL;
10941  name = pt_tuple_value (parser, name, cursor_p, index);
10942  name->next = next;
10943  return name;
10944  }
10945  last_node = node;
10946  }
10947 
10948  next = name->next;
10949  name->next = NULL;
10950 
10951  /* add it to the end of the select_list */
10952  new_col = parser_copy_tree (parser, name);
10953  if (new_col == NULL)
10954  {
10955  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
10956  return NULL;
10957  }
10958  last_node->next = new_col;
10959 
10960  /* change name to tuple value */
10961  name = pt_tuple_value (parser, name, cursor_p, index);
10962  if (name == NULL)
10963  {
10964  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
10965  return NULL;
10966  }
10967  name->next = next;
10968 
10969  return name;
10970 }

10972 /*
10973  * pt_make_query_show_collation() - builds the query for SHOW COLLATION
10974  *
10975  * SELECT * FROM
10976  * (SELECT coll_name AS [Collation],
10977  * IF (charset_id = 3, 'iso88591',
10978  * IF (charset_id = 5, 'utf8',
10979  * IF (charset_id = 2, 'binary',
10980  * IF (charset_id = 4, 'euckr', 'other')))) AS Charset,
10981  * coll_id AS Id,
10982  * IF (built_in = 0, 'No', 'Yes') AS Built_in,
10983  * IF (expansions = 0, 'No', 'Yes') AS Expansions,
10984  * IF (uca_strength = 1,'Primary',
10985  * IF (uca_strength = 2,'Secondary',
10986  * IF (uca_strength = 3, 'Tertiary',
10987  * IF (uca_strength = 4,'Quaternary',
10988  * IF (uca_strength = 5, 'Identity',
10989  * 'Not applicable'))))) AS Strength
10990  * FROM _db_collation) show_colllation
10991  * ORDER BY 1;
10992  *
10993  * return: newly built node (PT_NODE), NULL if construnction fails
10994  * parser(in): Parser context
10995  * like_where_syntax(in): indicator of presence for LIKE or WHERE clauses in
10996  * SHOW statement. Values : 0 = none of LIKE or WHERE,
10997  * 1 = contains LIKE, 2 = contains WHERE
10998  * like_or_where_expr(in): node expression supplied as condition (in WHERE)
10999  * or RHS for LIKE
11000  *
11001  * Note : Order is defined by: coll_name
11002  */
11003 PT_NODE *
11004 pt_make_query_show_collation (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, int like_where_syntax, PT_NODE * like_or_where_expr)
11005 {
11006  PT_NODE *sub_query = NULL;
11007  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
11008  PT_NODE *from_item = NULL;
11009 
11010  sub_query = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SELECT);
11011  if (sub_query == NULL)
11012  {
11013  return NULL;
11014  }
11015 
11016  /* ------ SELECT list ------- */
11017  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, sub_query, "coll_name", "Collation");
11018 
11019  /* Charset */
11020  {
11021  PT_NODE *if_node1 = NULL;
11022  PT_NODE *if_node2 = NULL;
11023  PT_NODE *if_node3 = NULL;
11024  PT_NODE *if_node4 = NULL;
11025 
11026  {
11027  /* IF (charset_id = 4, 'euckr', 'other') */
11028  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11029 
11030  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "charset_id", 4);
11031  if_node4 = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "euckr", "other", NULL);
11032  }
11033 
11034  {
11035  /* IF (charset_id = 2, 'binary', IF_NODE_ 4) */

11037  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11038 
11039  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "charset_id", 2);
11040  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "binary");
11041 
11042  if_node3 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node4, NULL);
11043  }
11044 
11045  {
11046  /* IF (charset_id = 5, 'utf8', IF_NODE_ 3) */
11047  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11048  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11049 
11050  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "charset_id", 5);
11051  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "utf8");
11052 
11053  if_node2 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node3, NULL);
11054  }
11055 
11056  {
11057  /* IF (charset_id = 3, 'iso88591', IF_NODE_ 2) */
11058  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11059  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11060 
11061  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "charset_id", 3);
11062  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "iso88591");
11063 
11064  if_node1 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node2, "Charset");
11065  }
11066

11068  }
11069 
11070  pt_add_name_col_to_sel_list (parser, sub_query, "coll_id", "Id");
11071 
11072  /* Built_in */
11073  {
11074  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
11075  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11076 
11077  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "built_in", 0);
11078  if_node = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "No", "Yes", "Built_in");
11079  sub_query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (if_node, sub_query->info.query.q.select.list);
11080  }
11081 
11082  /* Expansions */
11083  {
11084  PT_NODE *if_node = NULL;
11085  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11086 
11087  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "expansions", 0);
11088  if_node = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "No", "Yes", "Expansions");
11089  sub_query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (if_node, sub_query->info.query.q.select.list);
11090  }
11091 
11092  /* Strength */
11093  {
11094  PT_NODE *if_node1 = NULL;
11095  PT_NODE *if_node2 = NULL;
11096  PT_NODE *if_node3 = NULL;
11097  PT_NODE *if_node4 = NULL;
11098  PT_NODE *if_node5 = NULL;
11099 
11100  {
11101  /* IF (uca_strength = 5, 'Identity', 'Not applicable') */
11102  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11103 
11104  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "uca_strength", 5);
11105  if_node5 = pt_make_if_with_strings (parser, pred, "Identity", "Not applicable", NULL);
11106  }
11107 
11108  {
11109  /* IF (uca_strength = 4,'Quaternary', IF_node_5) */
11110  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11111  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11112 
11113  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "uca_strength", 4);
11114  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "Quaternary");
11115 
11116  if_node4 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node5, NULL);
11117  }
11118 
11119  {
11120  /* IF (uca_strength = 3, 'Tertiary', IF_Node_4) */
11121  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11122  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11123 
11124  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "uca_strength", 3);
11125  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "Tertiary");
11126 
11127  if_node3 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node4, NULL);
11128  }
11129 
11130  {
11131  /* IF (uca_strength = 2,'Secondary', IF_Node_3) */
11132  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11133  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11134 
11135  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "uca_strength", 2);
11136  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "Secondary");
11137 
11138  if_node2 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node3, NULL);
11139  }
11140 
11141  {
11142  /* IF (uca_strength = 1,'Primary', IF_Node_2) */
11143  PT_NODE *pred = NULL;
11144  PT_NODE *string_node = NULL;
11145 
11146  pred = pt_make_pred_name_int_val (parser, PT_EQ, "uca_strength", 1);
11147  string_node = pt_make_string_value (parser, "Primary");
11148 
11149  if_node1 = pt_make_if_with_expressions (parser, pred, string_node, if_node2, "Strength");
11150  }
11151 
11152  sub_query->info.query.q.select.list = parser_append_node (if_node1, sub_query->info.query.q.select.list);
11153  }
11154 
11155  /* ------ SELECT ... FROM ------- */
11156  from_item = pt_add_table_name_to_from_list (parser, sub_query, "_db_collation", NULL, DB_AUTH_SELECT);
11157 
11158  if (from_item == NULL)
11159  {
11160  return NULL;
11161  }
11162 
11163  node = pt_make_outer_select_for_show_stmt (parser, sub_query, "show_columns");
11164  if (node == NULL)
11165  {
11166  return NULL;
11167  }
11168 
11169  {
11170  /* add ORDER BY (to outer select) */
11171  PT_NODE *order_by_item = NULL;
11172 
11173  assert (node->info.query.order_by == NULL);
11174  /* By Collation */
11175  order_by_item = pt_make_sort_spec_with_number (parser, 1, PT_ASC);
11176  node->info.query.order_by = parser_append_node (order_by_item, node->info.query.order_by);
11177  }
11178 
11179  if (like_or_where_expr != NULL)
11180  {
11181  PT_NODE *where_item = NULL;
11182 
11183  if (like_where_syntax == 1)
11184  {
11185  /* make LIKE */
11186  where_item = pt_make_like_col_expr (parser, like_or_where_expr, "Collation");
11187  }
11188  else
11189  {
11190  /* WHERE */
11191  assert (like_where_syntax == 2);
11192  where_item = like_or_where_expr;
11193  }
11194 
11195  node->info.query.q.select.where = parser_append_node (where_item, node->info.query.q.select.where);
11196  }
11197  else
11198  {
11199  assert (like_where_syntax == 0);
11200  }
11201 
11202  return node;
11203 }
11204 
11205 /*
11206  * pt_get_query_limit_from_limit () - get the value of the LIMIT clause of a query
11207  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
11208  * parser (in) : parser context
11209  * limit (in) : limit node
11210  * limit_val (in/out) : limit value
11211  *
11212  * Note: this function get the LIMIT clause value of a query as a
11213  * DB_TYPE_BIGINT value. If the LIMIT clause contains a lower limit, the
11214  * returned value is computed as lower bound + range. (i.e.: if it was
11215  * specified as LIMIT :offset, :row_count this function returns :offset + :row_count)
11216  */
11217 static int
11218 pt_get_query_limit_from_limit (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * limit, DB_VALUE * limit_val)
11219 {
11220  int save_set_host_var;
11221  TP_DOMAIN *domainp = NULL;
11222  int error = NO_ERROR;
11223 
11224  db_make_null (limit_val);
11225 
11226  if (limit == NULL)
11227  {
11228  return NO_ERROR;
11229  }
11230 
11231  domainp = tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_TYPE_BIGINT);
11232 
11233  save_set_host_var = parser->set_host_var;
11234  parser->set_host_var = 1;
11235 
11236  assert (limit->node_type == PT_VALUE || limit->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR || limit->node_type == PT_EXPR);
11237 
11238  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, limit, limit_val, 1);
11239  if (pt_has_error (parser))
11240  {
11241  error = ER_FAILED;
11242  goto cleanup;
11243  }
11244 
11245  if (DB_IS_NULL (limit_val))
11246  {
11247  /* probably value is not bound yet */
11248  goto cleanup;
11249  }
11250 
11251  if (tp_value_coerce (limit_val, limit_val, domainp) != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
11252  {
11253  error = ER_FAILED;
11254  goto cleanup;
11255  }
11256 
11257  if (limit->next)
11258  {
11259  DB_VALUE range;
11260 
11261  db_make_null (&range);
11262 
11263  /* LIMIT :offset, :row_count => return :offset + :row_count */
11264  assert (limit->next->node_type == PT_VALUE || limit->next->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR
11265  || limit->next->node_type == PT_EXPR);
11266 
11267  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, limit->next, &range, 1);
11268  if (pt_has_error (parser))
11269  {
11270  error = ER_FAILED;
11271  goto cleanup;
11272  }
11273 
11274  if (DB_IS_NULL (&range))
11275  {
11276  /* probably value is not bound yet */
11277  goto cleanup;
11278  }
11279 
11280  if (tp_value_coerce (&range, &range, domainp) != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
11281  {
11282  error = ER_FAILED;
11283  goto cleanup;
11284  }
11285 
11286  /* add range to current limit */
11287  db_make_bigint (limit_val, db_get_bigint (limit_val) + db_get_bigint (&range));
11288  }
11289 
11290 cleanup:
11291  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11292  {
11293  pr_clear_value (limit_val);
11294  db_make_null (limit_val);
11295  }
11296 
11297  parser->set_host_var = save_set_host_var;
11298  return error;
11299 }
11300 
11301 /*
11302  * pt_get_query_limit_value () - get the limit value from a query
11303  * return : error code or NO_ERROR
11304  * parser (in) : parser context
11305  * query (in) : query
11306  * limit_val (in/out) : limit value
11307  */
11308 int
11309 pt_get_query_limit_value (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query, DB_VALUE * limit_val)
11310 {
11311  assert_release (limit_val != NULL);
11312 
11313  db_make_null (limit_val);
11314 
11315  if (query == NULL || !PT_IS_QUERY (query))
11316  {
11317  return NO_ERROR;
11318  }
11319 
11320  if (query->info.query.limit)
11321  {
11322  return pt_get_query_limit_from_limit (parser, query->info.query.limit, limit_val);
11323  }
11324 
11325  if (query->info.query.orderby_for != NULL)
11326  {
11327  int error = NO_ERROR;
11328  bool has_limit = false;
11329 
11330  error = pt_get_query_limit_from_orderby_for (parser, query->info.query.orderby_for, limit_val, &has_limit);
11331  if (error != NO_ERROR || !has_limit)
11332  {
11333  return ER_FAILED;
11334  }
11335  }
11336 
11337  return NO_ERROR;
11338 }
11339 
11340 /*
11341  * pt_check_ordby_num_for_multi_range_opt () - checks if limit/order by for is valid for multi range opt
11342  *
11343  * return : true/false
11344  * parser (in) : parser context
11345  * query (in) : query
11346  * mro_candidate (out) : if the only failed condition is upper limit for
11347  * orderby_num (), this plan may still use multi range
11348  * optimization if that limit changes
11349  * cannot_eval (out) : upper limit is null or could not be evaluated
11350  */
11351 bool
11352 pt_check_ordby_num_for_multi_range_opt (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query, bool * mro_candidate,
11353  bool * cannot_eval)
11354 {
11355  DB_VALUE limit_val;
11356  int save_set_host_var;
11357  bool valid = false;
11358 
11359  assert_release (query != NULL);
11360 
11361  if (cannot_eval != NULL)
11362  {
11363  *cannot_eval = true;
11364  }
11365  if (mro_candidate != NULL)
11366  {
11367  *mro_candidate = false;
11368  }
11369 
11370  if (!PT_IS_QUERY (query))
11371  {
11372  return false;
11373  }
11374 
11375  db_make_null (&limit_val);
11376 
11377  save_set_host_var = parser->set_host_var;
11378  parser->set_host_var = 1;
11379 
11380  if (pt_get_query_limit_value (parser, query, &limit_val) != NO_ERROR)
11381  {
11382  goto end;
11383  }
11384 
11385  if (DB_IS_NULL (&limit_val))
11386  {
11387  goto end_mro_candidate;
11388  }
11389 
11390  if (cannot_eval)
11391  {
11392  /* upper limit was successfully evaluated */
11393  *cannot_eval = false;
11394  }
11395  if (db_get_bigint (&limit_val) > prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MULTI_RANGE_OPT_LIMIT))
11396  {
11397  goto end_mro_candidate;
11398  }
11399  else
11400  {
11401  valid = true;
11402  goto end;
11403  }
11404 
11405 end_mro_candidate:
11406  /* should be here if multi range optimization could not be validated because upper limit is too large or it could not
11407  * be evaluated. However, the query may still use optimization for different host variable values. */
11408  if (mro_candidate != NULL)
11409  {
11410  *mro_candidate = true;
11411  }
11412 
11413 end:
11414  parser->set_host_var = save_set_host_var;
11415  return valid;
11416 }
11417 
11418 /*
11419  * pt_get_query_limit_from_orderby_for () - get upper limit value for orderby_for expression
11420  *
11421  * return : true if a valid order by for expression, else false
11422  * parser (in) : parser context
11423  * orderby_for (in) : order by for node
11424  * upper_limit (out) : DB_VALUE pointer that will save the upper limit
11425  *
11426  * Note: Only operations that can reduce to ORDERBY_NUM () </<= VALUE are allowed:
11427  * 1. ORDERBY_NUM () LE/LT EXPR (which evaluates to a value).
11428  * 2. EXPR (which evaluates to a values) GE/GT ORDERBY_NUM ().
11429  * 3. Any number of #1 and #2 expressions linked by PT_AND logical operator.
11430  * Lower limits are allowed.
11431  */
11432 static int
11433 pt_get_query_limit_from_orderby_for (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * orderby_for, DB_VALUE * upper_limit,
11434  bool * has_limit)
11435 {
11436  int op;
11437  PT_NODE *arg_ordby_num = NULL;
11438  PT_NODE *rhs = NULL;
11439  PT_NODE *arg1 = NULL, *arg2 = NULL;
11440  PT_NODE *save_next = NULL;
11441  DB_VALUE limit;
11442  int error = NO_ERROR;
11443  bool lt = false;
11444 
11445  if (orderby_for == NULL || upper_limit == NULL)
11446  {
11447  return NO_ERROR;
11448  }
11449 
11450  assert_release (has_limit != NULL);
11451 
11452  if (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (orderby_for))
11453  {
11454  goto unusable_expr;
11455  }
11456 
11457  if (orderby_for->or_next != NULL)
11458  {
11459  /* OR operator is now useful */
11460  goto unusable_expr;
11461  }
11462 
11463  if (orderby_for->next)
11464  {
11465  /* AND operator */
11466  save_next = orderby_for->next;
11467  orderby_for->next = NULL;
11468  error = pt_get_query_limit_from_orderby_for (parser, orderby_for, upper_limit, has_limit);
11469  orderby_for->next = save_next;
11470  if (error != NO_ERROR)
11471  {
11472  goto unusable_expr;
11473  }
11474 
11475  return pt_get_query_limit_from_orderby_for (parser, orderby_for->next, upper_limit, has_limit);
11476  }
11477 
11478  op = orderby_for->info.expr.op;
11479 
11480  if (op != PT_LT && op != PT_LE && op != PT_GT && op != PT_GE && op != PT_BETWEEN)
11481  {
11482  goto unusable_expr;
11483  }
11484 
11485  arg1 = orderby_for->info.expr.arg1;
11486  arg2 = orderby_for->info.expr.arg2;
11487  if (arg1 == NULL || arg2 == NULL)
11488  {
11489  /* safe guard */
11490  goto unusable_expr;
11491  }
11492 
11493  /* look for orderby_for argument */
11494  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (arg1) && arg1->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)
11495  {
11496  arg_ordby_num = arg1;
11497  rhs = arg2;
11498  }
11499  else if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (arg2) && arg2->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)
11500  {
11501  arg_ordby_num = arg2;
11502  rhs = arg1;
11503  /* reverse operators */
11504  switch (op)
11505  {
11506  case PT_LE:
11507  op = PT_GT;
11508  break;
11509  case PT_LT:
11510  op = PT_GE;
11511  break;
11512  case PT_GT:
11513  op = PT_LE;
11514  break;
11515  case PT_GE:
11516  op = PT_LT;
11517  break;
11518  default:
11519  break;
11520  }
11521  }
11522  else
11523  {
11524  /* orderby_for argument was not found, this is not a valid expression */
11525  goto unusable_expr;
11526  }
11527 
11528  if (op == PT_GE || op == PT_GT)
11529  {
11530  /* lower limits are acceptable but not useful */
11531  return NO_ERROR;
11532  }
11533 
11534  if (op == PT_LT)
11535  {
11536  lt = true;
11537  }
11538  else if (op == PT_BETWEEN)
11539  {
11540  PT_NODE *between_and = orderby_for->info.expr.arg2;
11541  PT_NODE *between_upper = NULL;
11542  int between_op;
11543 
11544  assert (between_and != NULL && between_and->node_type == PT_EXPR);
11545  between_upper = between_and->info.expr.arg2;
11546  between_op = between_and->info.expr.op;
11547  switch (between_op)
11548  {
11549  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LT:
11550  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LT:
11551  lt = true;
11552  /* fall through */
11553  case PT_BETWEEN_AND:
11554  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LE:
11555  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LE:
11556  assert (between_and->info.expr.arg2 != NULL);
11557  rhs = between_and->info.expr.arg2;
11558  break;
11559  case PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA:
11560  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_INF:
11561  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_INF:
11562  /* lower limits are acceptable but not useful */
11563  return NO_ERROR;
11564  default:
11565  /* be conservative */
11566  goto unusable_expr;
11567  }
11568  }
11569 
11570  /* evaluate the rhs expression */
11571  db_make_null (&limit);
11572  if (PT_IS_CONST (rhs) || PT_IS_CAST_CONST_INPUT_HOSTVAR (rhs))
11573  {
11574  pt_evaluate_tree_having_serial (parser, rhs, &limit, 1);
11575  }
11576 
11577  if (DB_IS_NULL (&limit)
11578  || tp_value_coerce (&limit, &limit, tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_TYPE_BIGINT)) != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
11579  {
11580  /* has unusable upper_limit */
11581  pr_clear_value (upper_limit);
11582  *has_limit = true;
11583  return NO_ERROR;
11584  }
11585 
11586  if (lt)
11587  {
11588  /* ORDERBY_NUM () < n => ORDERBY_NUM <= n - 1 */
11589  db_make_bigint (&limit, (db_get_bigint (&limit) - 1));
11590  }
11591  if (DB_IS_NULL (upper_limit) || (db_get_bigint (upper_limit) > db_get_bigint (&limit)))
11592  {
11593  /* update upper limit */
11594  if (pr_clone_value (&limit, upper_limit) != NO_ERROR)
11595  {
11596  goto unusable_expr;
11597  }
11598  }
11599 
11600  *has_limit = true;
11601  return NO_ERROR;
11602 
11603 unusable_expr:
11604  *has_limit = false;
11605  pr_clear_value (upper_limit);
11606  return ER_FAILED;
11607 }
11608 
11609 /*
11610  * pt_find_node_type_pre () - Use parser_walk_tree to find a node with a
11611  * specific node type.
11612  *
11613  * return : node.
11614  * parser (in) : parser context.
11615  * node (in) : node in parse tree.
11616  * arg (in) : int array containing node type and found.
11617  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk.
11618  *
11619  * NOTE: Make sure to set found to 0 before calling parser_walk_tree.
11620  */
11621 PT_NODE *
11622 pt_find_node_type_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
11623 {
11624  int node_type = *((int *) arg);
11625  int *found_p = ((int *) arg) + 1;
11626 
11627  if (*found_p || *continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK || node == NULL)
11628  {
11629  return node;
11630  }
11631  if (node->node_type == node_type)
11632  {
11633  *found_p = 1;
11634  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
11635  }
11636  return node;
11637 }
11638 
11639 /*
11640  * pt_find_op_type_pre () - Use parser_walk_tree to find an operator of a
11641  * specific type.
11642  *
11643  * return : node.
11644  * parser (in) : parser context.
11645  * node (in) : node in parse tree.
11646  * arg (in) : int array containing expr type and found.
11647  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk.
11648  *
11649  * NOTE: Make sure to set found to 0 before calling parser_walk_tree.
11650  */
11651 PT_NODE *
11652 pt_find_op_type_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
11653 {
11654  int op_type = *((int *) arg);
11655  int *found_p = ((int *) arg) + 1;
11656 
11657  if (*found_p || *continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK || node == NULL)
11658  {
11659  return node;
11660  }
11661  if (node->node_type == PT_EXPR && node->info.expr.op == op_type)
11662  {
11663  *found_p = 1;
11664  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
11665  }
11666  return node;
11667 }

11669 /*
11670  * pt_partition_name - get actual class name of a partition from root class name
11671  * and partition suffix
11672  * return: partition class name
11673  * parser (in) : parser context
11674  * class_name (in): partitioned class name
11675  * partition (in) : partition suffix
11676  */
11677 const char *
11678 pt_partition_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *class_name, const char *partition)
11679 {
11680  char *name = NULL, *buf = NULL;
11681  int size = 0;
11682  size = strlen (class_name) + strlen (partition) + strlen (PARTITIONED_SUB_CLASS_TAG);
11683 
11684  buf = (char *) calloc (size + 1, sizeof (char));
11685  if (buf == NULL)
11686  {
11687  PT_ERRORm (parser, NULL, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
11688  return NULL;
11689  }
11690 
11691  sprintf (buf, "%s" PARTITIONED_SUB_CLASS_TAG "%s", class_name, partition);
11692  name = pt_append_string (parser, name, buf);
11693 
11694  free (buf);
11695  return name;
11696 }

11721  {

11730 /*
11731  * pt_check_enum_data_type - validate the ENUM data type
11732  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
11733  * parser (in) : parser context
11734  * dt (in/out) : ENUM data type
11735  *
11736  * NOTE: The function removes trailing pads for each ENUM element, checks that
11737  * the number of elements is lower or equal than DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX, checks
11738  * that the aggregate size of the ENUM elements is not greater than
11739  * DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX_AGG_SIZE and checks for duplicates
11740  */
11741 int
11742 pt_check_enum_data_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * dt)
11743 {
11744  int count = 0, err = NO_ERROR;
11745  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *temp = NULL;
11746  TP_DOMAIN *domain = NULL;
11747  int pad_size = 0, trimmed_length = 0, trimmed_size = 0;
11748  int char_count = 0;
11749  unsigned char pad[2];
11750 
11751  if (dt == NULL || dt->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE || dt->type_enum != PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
11752  {
11753  return NO_ERROR;
11754  }
11755 
11756  /* remove trailing pads for each element */
11757  intl_pad_char ((INTL_CODESET) dt->info.data_type.units, pad, &pad_size);
11758  node = dt->info.data_type.enumeration;
11759  while (node != NULL)
11760  {
11761  intl_char_count (node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes, node->info.value.data_value.str->length,
11762  (INTL_CODESET) dt->info.data_type.units, &char_count);
11763  qstr_trim_trailing (pad, pad_size, node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes, pt_node_to_db_type (node), char_count,
11764  node->info.value.data_value.str->length, (INTL_CODESET) dt->info.data_type.units,
11765  &trimmed_length, &trimmed_size, true);
11766  if (trimmed_size < node->info.value.data_value.str->length)
11767  {
11768  node->info.value.data_value.str =
11769  pt_append_bytes (parser, NULL, (const char *) node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes, trimmed_size);
11770  node->info.value.data_value.str->length = trimmed_size;
11771  if (node->info.value.db_value.need_clear)
11772  {
11773  pr_clear_value (&node->info.value.db_value);
11774  }
11775  if (node->info.value.db_value_is_initialized)
11776  {
11777  node->info.value.db_value_is_initialized = false;
11778  pt_value_to_db (parser, node);
11779  }
11780  }
11781 
11782  node = node->next;
11783  count++;
11784  }
11785 
11786  /* check that number of elements is lower or equal than DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX */
11787  if (count > DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX)
11788  {
11789  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, dt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ENUM_TYPE_TOO_MANY_VALUES, count,
11790  DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX);
11791  err = ER_FAILED;
11792  goto end;
11793  }
11794 
11795  /* check that the aggregate size of the ENUM elements is not greater than DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX_AGG_SIZE */
11796  domain = pt_data_type_to_db_domain (parser, dt, NULL);
11797  if (domain == NULL)
11798  {
11799  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Cannot create domain");
11800  return ER_FAILED;
11801  }
11802  count = or_packed_domain_size (domain, 0);
11803  if (count > (int) DB_ENUM_ELEMENTS_MAX_AGG_SIZE)
11804  {
11805  PT_ERRORm (parser, dt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ENUM_AGG_STRINGS_SIZE_TOO_LARGE);
11806  err = ER_FAILED;
11807  goto end;
11808  }
11809 
11810  /* check duplicates */
11811  node = dt->info.data_type.enumeration;
11812  while (node != NULL && err == NO_ERROR)
11813  {
11814  temp = node->next;
11815  while (temp != NULL)
11816  {
11817  if (QSTR_COMPARE (domain->collation_id, node->info.value.data_value.str->bytes,
11818  node->info.value.data_value.str->length, temp->info.value.data_value.str->bytes,
11819  temp->info.value.data_value.str->length) == 0)
11820  {
11821  PT_ERRORm (parser, temp, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ENUM_TYPE_DUPLICATE_VALUES);
11822 
11823  err = ER_FAILED;
11824  break;
11825  }
11826  temp = temp->next;
11827  }
11828  node = node->next;
11829  }
11830 
11831 end:
11832  if (domain != NULL)
11833  {
11834  tp_domain_free (domain);
11835  }
11836 
11837  return err;
11838 }
11839 
11840 /*
11841  * pt_recompile_for_limit_optimizations () - verify is query plan should be
11842  * regenerated for a query due to
11843  * limit change
11844  * return : true/false
11845  * parser (in) : parser context
11846  * statement (in) : statement
11847  * xasl_flag (in) : flag which contains plan information
11848  *
11849  * Note: before executing a query plan, we have to verify if the generated
11850  * plan is still valid with the new limit values. There are four cases:
11851  * I. MRO is used but the new limit value is either too large or invalid
11852  * for this plan. In this case we have to recompile.
11853  * II. MRO is not used but the new limit value is valid for generating such
11854  * a plan. In this case we have to recompile.
11855  * III. MRO is not used and the new limit value is invalid for generating this
11856  * plan. In this case we don't have to recompile
11857  * VI. MRO is used and the new limit value is valid for this plan. In this
11858  * case we don't have to recompile
11859  * The same rules apply to SORT-LIMIT plans
11860  */
11861 bool
11862 pt_recompile_for_limit_optimizations (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement, int xasl_flag)
11863 {
11864  DB_VALUE limit_val;
11865  DB_BIGINT val = 0;
11866  int limit_opt_flag = (MRO_CANDIDATE | MRO_IS_USED | SORT_LIMIT_CANDIDATE | SORT_LIMIT_USED);
11867 
11868  if (!(xasl_flag & limit_opt_flag))
11869  {
11870  return false;
11871  }
11872 
11873  if (pt_get_query_limit_value (parser, statement, &limit_val) != NO_ERROR)
11874  {
11875  val = 0;
11876  }
11877  else if (DB_IS_NULL (&limit_val))
11878  {
11879  val = 0;
11880  }
11881  else
11882  {
11883  val = db_get_bigint (&limit_val);
11884  }
11885 
11886  /* verify MRO */
11887  if (xasl_flag & (MRO_CANDIDATE | MRO_IS_USED))
11888  {
11889  if (val == 0 || val > (DB_BIGINT) prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MULTI_RANGE_OPT_LIMIT))
11890  {
11891  if (xasl_flag & MRO_IS_USED)
11892  {
11893  /* Need to recompile because limit is not suitable for MRO anymore */
11894  return true;
11895  }
11896  }
11897  else if ((xasl_flag & MRO_CANDIDATE) && !(xasl_flag & MRO_IS_USED))
11898  {
11899  /* Suitable limit for MRO but MRO is not used. Recompile to use MRO */
11900  return true;
11901  }
11902  return false;
11903  }
11904 
11905  /* verify SORT-LIMIT */
11906  if (xasl_flag & (SORT_LIMIT_CANDIDATE | SORT_LIMIT_USED))
11907  {
11908  if (val == 0 || val > (DB_BIGINT) prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_SORT_LIMIT_MAX_COUNT))
11909  {
11910  if (xasl_flag & SORT_LIMIT_USED)
11911  {
11912  /* Need to recompile because limit is not suitable for SORT-LIMIT anymore */
11913  return true;
11914  }
11915  }
11916  else if ((xasl_flag & SORT_LIMIT_CANDIDATE) && !(xasl_flag & SORT_LIMIT_USED))
11917  {
11918  /* Suitable limit for SORT-LIMIT but SORT-LIMIT is not used. Recompile to use SORT-LIMIT */
11919  return true;
11920  }
11921  return false;
11922  }
11923 
11924  return false;
11925 }

11959 /*
11960  * pt_has_non_groupby_column_node () - Use parser_walk_tree to check having
11961  * clause.
11962  * return : node.
11963  * parser (in) : parser context.
11964  * node (in) : name node in having clause.
11965  * arg (in) : pt_non_groupby_col_info
11966  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk.
11967  *
11968  * NOTE: Make sure to set has_non_groupby_col to false before calling
11969  * parser_walk_tree.

11971 PT_NODE *
11972 pt_has_non_groupby_column_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)

11978  {

11984  groupby_p = info->groupby;
11985

11987  {
11988  assert (false);
11989  return node;
11990  }
11991 
11992  if (!PT_IS_NAME_NODE (node))
11993  {
11994  return node;
11995  }
11996

11998  {

12000  {
12001  continue;
12002  }
12003 
12004  if (pt_name_equal (parser, groupby_p->info.sort_spec.expr, node))
12005  {
12006  return node;
12007  }
12008  }
12009 
12010  /* the name node is not associated with groupby columns. */
12011  info->has_non_groupby_col = true;
